4453 struct AAIsDeadReturned : public AAIsDeadValueImpl {
4454  AAIsDeadReturned(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
4455  : AAIsDeadValueImpl(IRP, A) {}
4456 
4457  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
4458  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
4459 
4460  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
4461  A.checkForAllInstructions([](Instruction &) { return true; }, *this,
4462  {Instruction::Ret}, UsedAssumedInformation);
4463 
4464  auto PredForCallSite = [&](AbstractCallSite ACS) {
4465  if (ACS.isCallbackCall() || !ACS.getInstruction())
4466  return false;
4467  return areAllUsesAssumedDead(A, *ACS.getInstruction());
4468  };
4469 
4470  if (!A.checkForAllCallSites(PredForCallSite, *this, true,
4471  UsedAssumedInformation))
4472  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
4473 
4474  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
4475  }
4476 
4477  /// See AbstractAttribute::manifest(...).
4478  ChangeStatus manifest(Attributor &A) override {
4479  // TODO: Rewrite the signature to return void?
4480  bool AnyChange = false;
4481  UndefValue &UV = *UndefValue::get(getAssociatedFunction()->getReturnType());
4482  auto RetInstPred = [&](Instruction &I) {
4483  ReturnInst &RI = cast<ReturnInst>(I);
4484  if (!isa<UndefValue>(RI.getReturnValue()))
4485  AnyChange |= A.changeUseAfterManifest(RI.getOperandUse(0), UV);
4486  return true;
4487  };
4488  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
4489  A.checkForAllInstructions(RetInstPred, *this, {Instruction::Ret},
4490  UsedAssumedInformation);
4491  return AnyChange ? ChangeStatus::CHANGED : ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
4492  }
4493 
4494  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
4495  void trackStatistics() const override { STATS_DECLTRACK_FNRET_ATTR(IsDead) }
4496 };
4497 
4498 struct AAIsDeadFunction : public AAIsDead {
4499  AAIsDeadFunction(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A) : AAIsDead(IRP, A) {}
4500 
4501  /// See AbstractAttribute::initialize(...).
4502  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
4503  Function *F = getAnchorScope();
4504  if (!F || F->isDeclaration() || !A.isRunOn(*F)) {
4505  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
4506  return;
4507  }
4508  if (!isAssumedDeadInternalFunction(A)) {
4509  ToBeExploredFrom.insert(&F->getEntryBlock().front());
4510  assumeLive(A, F->getEntryBlock());
4511  }
4512  }
4513 
4514  bool isAssumedDeadInternalFunction(Attributor &A) {
4515  if (!getAnchorScope()->hasLocalLinkage())
4516  return false;
4517  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
4518  return A.checkForAllCallSites([](AbstractCallSite) { return false; }, *this,
4519  true, UsedAssumedInformation);
4520  }
4521 
4522  /// See AbstractAttribute::getAsStr().
4523  const std::string getAsStr() const override {
4524  return "Live[#BB " + std::to_string(AssumedLiveBlocks.size()) + "/" +
4525  std::to_string(getAnchorScope()->size()) + "][#TBEP " +
4526  std::to_string(ToBeExploredFrom.size()) + "][#KDE " +
4527  std::to_string(KnownDeadEnds.size()) + "]";
4528  }
4529 
4530  /// See AbstractAttribute::manifest(...).
4531  ChangeStatus manifest(Attributor &A) override {
4532  assert(getState().isValidState() &&
4533  "Attempted to manifest an invalid state!");
4534 
4535  ChangeStatus HasChanged = ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
4536  Function &F = *getAnchorScope();
4537 
4538  if (AssumedLiveBlocks.empty()) {
4539  A.deleteAfterManifest(F);
4540  return ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
4541  }
4542 
4543  // Flag to determine if we can change an invoke to a call assuming the
4544  // callee is nounwind. This is not possible if the personality of the
4545  // function allows to catch asynchronous exceptions.
4546  bool Invoke2CallAllowed = !mayCatchAsynchronousExceptions(F);
4547 
4548  KnownDeadEnds.set_union(ToBeExploredFrom);
4549  for (const Instruction *DeadEndI : KnownDeadEnds) {
4550  auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(DeadEndI);
4551  if (!CB)
4552  continue;
4553  const auto &NoReturnAA = A.getAndUpdateAAFor<AANoReturn>(
4554  *this, IRPosition::callsite_function(*CB), DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
4555  bool MayReturn = !NoReturnAA.isAssumedNoReturn();
4556  if (MayReturn && (!Invoke2CallAllowed || !isa<InvokeInst>(CB)))
4557  continue;
4558 
4559  if (auto *II = dyn_cast<InvokeInst>(DeadEndI))
4560  A.registerInvokeWithDeadSuccessor(const_cast<InvokeInst &>(*II));
4561  else
4562  A.changeToUnreachableAfterManifest(
4563  const_cast<Instruction *>(DeadEndI->getNextNode()));
4564  HasChanged = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
4565  }
4566 
4567  STATS_DECL(AAIsDead, BasicBlock, "Number of dead basic blocks deleted.");
4568  for (BasicBlock &BB : F)
4569  if (!AssumedLiveBlocks.count(&BB)) {
4570  A.deleteAfterManifest(BB);
4571  ++BUILD_STAT_NAME(AAIsDead, BasicBlock);
4572  HasChanged = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
4573  }
4574 
4575  return HasChanged;
4576  }
4577 
4578  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
4579  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override;
4580 
4581  bool isEdgeDead(const BasicBlock *From, const BasicBlock *To) const override {
4582  assert(From->getParent() == getAnchorScope() &&
4583  To->getParent() == getAnchorScope() &&
4584  "Used AAIsDead of the wrong function");
4585  return isValidState() && !AssumedLiveEdges.count(std::make_pair(From, To));
4586  }
4587 
4588  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
4589  void trackStatistics() const override {}
4590 
4591  /// Returns true if the function is assumed dead.
4592  bool isAssumedDead() const override { return false; }
4593 
4594  /// See AAIsDead::isKnownDead().
4595  bool isKnownDead() const override { return false; }
4596 
4597  /// See AAIsDead::isAssumedDead(BasicBlock *).
4598  bool isAssumedDead(const BasicBlock *BB) const override {
4599  assert(BB->getParent() == getAnchorScope() &&
4600  "BB must be in the same anchor scope function.");
4601 
4602  if (!getAssumed())
4603  return false;
4604  return !AssumedLiveBlocks.count(BB);
4605  }
4606 
4607  /// See AAIsDead::isKnownDead(BasicBlock *).
4608  bool isKnownDead(const BasicBlock *BB) const override {
4609  return getKnown() && isAssumedDead(BB);
4610  }
4611 
4612  /// See AAIsDead::isAssumed(Instruction *I).
4613  bool isAssumedDead(const Instruction *I) const override {
4614  assert(I->getParent()->getParent() == getAnchorScope() &&
4615  "Instruction must be in the same anchor scope function.");
4616 
4617  if (!getAssumed())
4618  return false;
4619 
4620  // If it is not in AssumedLiveBlocks then it for sure dead.
4621  // Otherwise, it can still be after noreturn call in a live block.
4622  if (!AssumedLiveBlocks.count(I->getParent()))
4623  return true;
4624 
4625  // If it is not after a liveness barrier it is live.
4626  const Instruction *PrevI = I->getPrevNode();
4627  while (PrevI) {
4628  if (KnownDeadEnds.count(PrevI) || ToBeExploredFrom.count(PrevI))
4629  return true;
4630  PrevI = PrevI->getPrevNode();
4631  }
4632  return false;
4633  }
4634 
4635  /// See AAIsDead::isKnownDead(Instruction *I).
4636  bool isKnownDead(const Instruction *I) const override {
4637  return getKnown() && isAssumedDead(I);
4638  }
4639 
4640  /// Assume \p BB is (partially) live now and indicate to the Attributor \p A
4641  /// that internal function called from \p BB should now be looked at.
4642  bool assumeLive(Attributor &A, const BasicBlock &BB) {
4643  if (!AssumedLiveBlocks.insert(&BB).second)
4644  return false;
4645 
4646  // We assume that all of BB is (probably) live now and if there are calls to
4647  // internal functions we will assume that those are now live as well. This
4648  // is a performance optimization for blocks with calls to a lot of internal
4649  // functions. It can however cause dead functions to be treated as live.
4650  for (const Instruction &I : BB)
4651  if (const auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(&I))
4652  if (const Function *F = CB->getCalledFunction())
4653  if (F->hasLocalLinkage())
4654  A.markLiveInternalFunction(*F);
4655  return true;
4656  }
4657 
4658  /// Collection of instructions that need to be explored again, e.g., we
4659  /// did assume they do not transfer control to (one of their) successors.
4660  SmallSetVector<const Instruction *, 8> ToBeExploredFrom;
4661 
4662  /// Collection of instructions that are known to not transfer control.
4663  SmallSetVector<const Instruction *, 8> KnownDeadEnds;
4664 
4665  /// Collection of all assumed live edges
4666  DenseSet<std::pair<const BasicBlock *, const BasicBlock *>> AssumedLiveEdges;
4667 
4668  /// Collection of all assumed live BasicBlocks.
4669  DenseSet<const BasicBlock *> AssumedLiveBlocks;
4670 };
4671 
4672 static bool
4673 identifyAliveSuccessors(Attributor &A, const CallBase &CB,
4674  AbstractAttribute &AA,
4675  SmallVectorImpl<const Instruction *> &AliveSuccessors) {
4676  const IRPosition &IPos = IRPosition::callsite_function(CB);
4677 
4678  const auto &NoReturnAA =
4679  A.getAndUpdateAAFor<AANoReturn>(AA, IPos, DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
4680  if (NoReturnAA.isAssumedNoReturn())
4681  return !NoReturnAA.isKnownNoReturn();
4682  if (CB.isTerminator())
4683  AliveSuccessors.push_back(&CB.getSuccessor(0)->front());
4684  else
4685  AliveSuccessors.push_back(CB.getNextNode());
4686  return false;
4687 }
4688 
4689 static bool
4690 identifyAliveSuccessors(Attributor &A, const InvokeInst &II,
4691  AbstractAttribute &AA,
4692  SmallVectorImpl<const Instruction *> &AliveSuccessors) {
4693  bool UsedAssumedInformation =
4694  identifyAliveSuccessors(A, cast<CallBase>(II), AA, AliveSuccessors);
4695 
4696  // First, determine if we can change an invoke to a call assuming the
4697  // callee is nounwind. This is not possible if the personality of the
4698  // function allows to catch asynchronous exceptions.
4699  if (AAIsDeadFunction::mayCatchAsynchronousExceptions(*II.getFunction())) {
4700  AliveSuccessors.push_back(&II.getUnwindDest()->front());
4701  } else {
4702  const IRPosition &IPos = IRPosition::callsite_function(II);
4703  const auto &AANoUnw =
4704  A.getAndUpdateAAFor<AANoUnwind>(AA, IPos, DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
4705  if (AANoUnw.isAssumedNoUnwind()) {
4706  UsedAssumedInformation |= !AANoUnw.isKnownNoUnwind();
4707  } else {
4708  AliveSuccessors.push_back(&II.getUnwindDest()->front());
4709  }
4710  }
4711  return UsedAssumedInformation;
4712 }
4713 
4714 static bool
4715 identifyAliveSuccessors(Attributor &A, const BranchInst &BI,
4716  AbstractAttribute &AA,
4717  SmallVectorImpl<const Instruction *> &AliveSuccessors) {
4718  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
4719  if (BI.getNumSuccessors() == 1) {
4720  AliveSuccessors.push_back(&BI.getSuccessor(0)->front());
4721  } else {
4722  std::optional<Constant *> C =
4723  A.getAssumedConstant(*BI.getCondition(), AA, UsedAssumedInformation);
4724  if (!C || isa_and_nonnull<UndefValue>(*C)) {
4725  // No value yet, assume both edges are dead.
4726  } else if (isa_and_nonnull<ConstantInt>(*C)) {
4727  const BasicBlock *SuccBB =
4728  BI.getSuccessor(1 - cast<ConstantInt>(*C)->getValue().getZExtValue());
4729  AliveSuccessors.push_back(&SuccBB->front());
4730  } else {
4731  AliveSuccessors.push_back(&BI.getSuccessor(0)->front());
4732  AliveSuccessors.push_back(&BI.getSuccessor(1)->front());
4733  UsedAssumedInformation = false;
4734  }
4735  }
4736  return UsedAssumedInformation;
4737 }
4738 
4739 static bool
4740 identifyAliveSuccessors(Attributor &A, const SwitchInst &SI,
4741  AbstractAttribute &AA,
4742  SmallVectorImpl<const Instruction *> &AliveSuccessors) {
4743  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
4744  std::optional<Constant *> C =
4745  A.getAssumedConstant(*SI.getCondition(), AA, UsedAssumedInformation);
4746  if (!C || isa_and_nonnull<UndefValue>(*C)) {
4747  // No value yet, assume all edges are dead.
4748  } else if (isa_and_nonnull<ConstantInt>(*C)) {
4749  for (const auto &CaseIt : SI.cases()) {
4750  if (CaseIt.getCaseValue() == *C) {
4751  AliveSuccessors.push_back(&CaseIt.getCaseSuccessor()->front());
4752  return UsedAssumedInformation;
4753  }
4754  }
4755  AliveSuccessors.push_back(&SI.getDefaultDest()->front());
4756  return UsedAssumedInformation;
4757  } else {
4758  for (const BasicBlock *SuccBB : successors(SI.getParent()))
4759  AliveSuccessors.push_back(&SuccBB->front());
4760  }
4761  return UsedAssumedInformation;
4762 }
4763 
4764 ChangeStatus AAIsDeadFunction::updateImpl(Attributor &A) {
4765  ChangeStatus Change = ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
4766 
4767  if (AssumedLiveBlocks.empty()) {
4768  if (isAssumedDeadInternalFunction(A))
4769  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
4770 
4771  Function *F = getAnchorScope();
4772  ToBeExploredFrom.insert(&F->getEntryBlock().front());
4773  assumeLive(A, F->getEntryBlock());
4774  Change = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
4775  }
4776 
4777  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAIsDead] Live [" << AssumedLiveBlocks.size() << "/"
4778  << getAnchorScope()->size() << "] BBs and "
4779  << ToBeExploredFrom.size() << " exploration points and "
4780  << KnownDeadEnds.size() << " known dead ends\n");
4781 
4782  // Copy and clear the list of instructions we need to explore from. It is
4783  // refilled with instructions the next update has to look at.
4784  SmallVector<const Instruction *, 8> Worklist(ToBeExploredFrom.begin(),
4785  ToBeExploredFrom.end());
4786  decltype(ToBeExploredFrom) NewToBeExploredFrom;
4787 
4788  SmallVector<const Instruction *, 8> AliveSuccessors;
4789  while (!Worklist.empty()) {
4790  const Instruction *I = Worklist.pop_back_val();
4791  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAIsDead] Exploration inst: " << *I << "\n");
4792 
4793  // Fast forward for uninteresting instructions. We could look for UB here
4794  // though.
4795  while (!I->isTerminator() && !isa<CallBase>(I))
4796  I = I->getNextNode();
4797 
4798  AliveSuccessors.clear();
4799 
4800  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
4801  switch (I->getOpcode()) {
4802  // TODO: look for (assumed) UB to backwards propagate "deadness".
4803  default:
4804  assert(I->isTerminator() &&
4805  "Expected non-terminators to be handled already!");
4806  for (const BasicBlock *SuccBB : successors(I->getParent()))
4807  AliveSuccessors.push_back(&SuccBB->front());
4808  break;
4809  case Instruction::Call:
4810  UsedAssumedInformation = identifyAliveSuccessors(A, cast<CallInst>(*I),
4811  *this, AliveSuccessors);
4812  break;
4813  case Instruction::Invoke:
4814  UsedAssumedInformation = identifyAliveSuccessors(A, cast<InvokeInst>(*I),
4815  *this, AliveSuccessors);
4816  break;
4817  case Instruction::Br:
4818  UsedAssumedInformation = identifyAliveSuccessors(A, cast<BranchInst>(*I),
4819  *this, AliveSuccessors);
4820  break;
4821  case Instruction::Switch:
4822  UsedAssumedInformation = identifyAliveSuccessors(A, cast<SwitchInst>(*I),
4823  *this, AliveSuccessors);
4824  break;
4825  }
4826 
4827  if (UsedAssumedInformation) {
4828  NewToBeExploredFrom.insert(I);
4829  } else if (AliveSuccessors.empty() ||
4830  (I->isTerminator() &&
4831  AliveSuccessors.size() < I->getNumSuccessors())) {
4832  if (KnownDeadEnds.insert(I))
4833  Change = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
4834  }
4835 
4836  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAIsDead] #AliveSuccessors: "
4837  << AliveSuccessors.size() << " UsedAssumedInformation: "
4838  << UsedAssumedInformation << "\n");
4839 
4840  for (const Instruction *AliveSuccessor : AliveSuccessors) {
4841  if (!I->isTerminator()) {
4842  assert(AliveSuccessors.size() == 1 &&
4843  "Non-terminator expected to have a single successor!");
4844  Worklist.push_back(AliveSuccessor);
4845  } else {
4846  // record the assumed live edge
4847  auto Edge = std::make_pair(I->getParent(), AliveSuccessor->getParent());
4848  if (AssumedLiveEdges.insert(Edge).second)
4849  Change = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
4850  if (assumeLive(A, *AliveSuccessor->getParent()))
4851  Worklist.push_back(AliveSuccessor);
4852  }
4853  }
4854  }
4855 
4856  // Check if the content of ToBeExploredFrom changed, ignore the order.
4857  if (NewToBeExploredFrom.size() != ToBeExploredFrom.size() ||
4858  llvm::any_of(NewToBeExploredFrom, [&](const Instruction *I) {
4859  return !ToBeExploredFrom.count(I);
4860  })) {
4861  Change = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
4862  ToBeExploredFrom = std::move(NewToBeExploredFrom);
4863  }
4864 
4865  // If we know everything is live there is no need to query for liveness.
4866  // Instead, indicating a pessimistic fixpoint will cause the state to be
4867  // "invalid" and all queries to be answered conservatively without lookups.
4868  // To be in this state we have to (1) finished the exploration and (3) not
4869  // discovered any non-trivial dead end and (2) not ruled unreachable code
4870  // dead.
4871  if (ToBeExploredFrom.empty() &&
4872  getAnchorScope()->size() == AssumedLiveBlocks.size() &&
4873  llvm::all_of(KnownDeadEnds, [](const Instruction *DeadEndI) {
4874  return DeadEndI->isTerminator() && DeadEndI->getNumSuccessors() == 0;
4875  }))
4876  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
4877  return Change;
4878 }
4879 
4880 /// Liveness information for a call sites.
4881 struct AAIsDeadCallSite final : AAIsDeadFunction {

4883  : AAIsDeadFunction(IRP, A) {}
4884 
4885  /// See AbstractAttribute::initialize(...).
4886  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
4887  // TODO: Once we have call site specific value information we can provide
4888  // call site specific liveness information and then it makes
4889  // sense to specialize attributes for call sites instead of
4890  // redirecting requests to the callee.
4891  llvm_unreachable("Abstract attributes for liveness are not "
4892  "supported for call sites yet!");
4893  }
4894 
4895  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
4896  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
4897  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
4898  }

4902 };

4907 namespace {
4908 struct AADereferenceableImpl : AADereferenceable {
4909  AADereferenceableImpl(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
4910  : AADereferenceable(IRP, A) {}
4911  using StateType = DerefState;
4912 
4913  /// See AbstractAttribute::initialize(...).
4914  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
4915  Value &V = *getAssociatedValue().stripPointerCasts();
4916  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> Attrs;
4917  getAttrs({Attribute::Dereferenceable, Attribute::DereferenceableOrNull},
4918  Attrs, /* IgnoreSubsumingPositions */ false, &A);
4919  for (const Attribute &Attr : Attrs)
4920  takeKnownDerefBytesMaximum(Attr.getValueAsInt());
4921 
4922  const IRPosition &IRP = this->getIRPosition();
4923  NonNullAA = &A.getAAFor<AANonNull>(*this, IRP, DepClassTy::NONE);
4924 
4925  bool CanBeNull, CanBeFreed;
4926  takeKnownDerefBytesMaximum(V.getPointerDereferenceableBytes(
4927  A.getDataLayout(), CanBeNull, CanBeFreed));
4928 
4929  bool IsFnInterface = IRP.isFnInterfaceKind();
4930  Function *FnScope = IRP.getAnchorScope();
4931  if (IsFnInterface && (!FnScope || !A.isFunctionIPOAmendable(*FnScope))) {
4932  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
4933  return;
4934  }
4935 
4936  if (Instruction *CtxI = getCtxI())
4937  followUsesInMBEC(*this, A, getState(), *CtxI);
4938  }
4939 
4940  /// See AbstractAttribute::getState()
4941  /// {
4942  StateType &getState() override { return *this; }
4943  const StateType &getState() const override { return *this; }
4944  /// }
4945 
4946  /// Helper function for collecting accessed bytes in must-be-executed-context
4947  void addAccessedBytesForUse(Attributor &A, const Use *U, const Instruction *I,
4948  DerefState &State) {
4949  const Value *UseV = U->get();
4950  if (!UseV->getType()->isPointerTy())
4951  return;
4952 
4953  std::optional<MemoryLocation> Loc = MemoryLocation::getOrNone(I);
4954  if (!Loc || Loc->Ptr != UseV || !Loc->Size.isPrecise() || I->isVolatile())
4955  return;
4956 
4957  int64_t Offset;
4958  const Value *Base = GetPointerBaseWithConstantOffset(
4959  Loc->Ptr, Offset, A.getDataLayout(), /*AllowNonInbounds*/ true);
4960  if (Base && Base == &getAssociatedValue())
4961  State.addAccessedBytes(Offset, Loc->Size.getValue());
4962  }
4963 
4964  /// See followUsesInMBEC
4965  bool followUseInMBEC(Attributor &A, const Use *U, const Instruction *I,
4966  AADereferenceable::StateType &State) {
4967  bool IsNonNull = false;
4968  bool TrackUse = false;
4969  int64_t DerefBytes = getKnownNonNullAndDerefBytesForUse(
4970  A, *this, getAssociatedValue(), U, I, IsNonNull, TrackUse);
4971  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AADereferenceable] Deref bytes: " << DerefBytes
4972  << " for instruction " << *I << "\n");
4973 
4974  addAccessedBytesForUse(A, U, I, State);
4975  State.takeKnownDerefBytesMaximum(DerefBytes);
4976  return TrackUse;
4977  }
4978 
4979  /// See AbstractAttribute::manifest(...).
4980  ChangeStatus manifest(Attributor &A) override {
4981  ChangeStatus Change = AADereferenceable::manifest(A);
4982  if (isAssumedNonNull() && hasAttr(Attribute::DereferenceableOrNull)) {
4983  removeAttrs({Attribute::DereferenceableOrNull});
4984  return ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
4985  }
4986  return Change;
4987  }
4988 
4989  void getDeducedAttributes(LLVMContext &Ctx,
4990  SmallVectorImpl<Attribute> &Attrs) const override {
4991  // TODO: Add *_globally support
4992  if (isAssumedNonNull())
4993  Attrs.emplace_back(Attribute::getWithDereferenceableBytes(
4994  Ctx, getAssumedDereferenceableBytes()));
4995  else
4996  Attrs.emplace_back(Attribute::getWithDereferenceableOrNullBytes(
4997  Ctx, getAssumedDereferenceableBytes()));
4998  }
4999 
5000  /// See AbstractAttribute::getAsStr().
5001  const std::string getAsStr() const override {
5002  if (!getAssumedDereferenceableBytes())
5003  return "unknown-dereferenceable";
5004  return std::string("dereferenceable") +
5005  (isAssumedNonNull() ? "" : "_or_null") +
5006  (isAssumedGlobal() ? "_globally" : "") + "<" +
5007  std::to_string(getKnownDereferenceableBytes()) + "-" +
5008  std::to_string(getAssumedDereferenceableBytes()) + ">";
5009  }
5010 };

5012 /// Dereferenceable attribute for a floating value.
5013 struct AADereferenceableFloating : AADereferenceableImpl {
5014  AADereferenceableFloating(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
5015  : AADereferenceableImpl(IRP, A) {}
5016 
5017  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
5018  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
5019 
5020  bool Stripped;
5021  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
5022  SmallVector<AA::ValueAndContext> Values;
5023  if (!A.getAssumedSimplifiedValues(getIRPosition(), *this, Values,
5024  AA::AnyScope, UsedAssumedInformation)) {
5025  Values.push_back({getAssociatedValue(), getCtxI()});
5026  Stripped = false;
5027  } else {
5028  Stripped = Values.size() != 1 ||
5029  Values.front().getValue() != &getAssociatedValue();
5030  }
5031 
5032  const DataLayout &DL = A.getDataLayout();
5033  DerefState T;
5034 
5035  auto VisitValueCB = [&](const Value &V) -> bool {
5036  unsigned IdxWidth =
5037  DL.getIndexSizeInBits(V.getType()->getPointerAddressSpace());
5038  APInt Offset(IdxWidth, 0);
5039  const Value *Base = stripAndAccumulateOffsets(
5040  A, *this, &V, DL, Offset, /* GetMinOffset */ false,
5041  /* AllowNonInbounds */ true);
5042 
5043  const auto &AA = A.getAAFor<AADereferenceable>(
5044  *this, IRPosition::value(*Base), DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
5045  int64_t DerefBytes = 0;
5046  if (!Stripped && this == &AA) {
5047  // Use IR information if we did not strip anything.
5048  // TODO: track globally.
5049  bool CanBeNull, CanBeFreed;
5050  DerefBytes =
5051  Base->getPointerDereferenceableBytes(DL, CanBeNull, CanBeFreed);
5052  T.GlobalState.indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
5053  } else {
5054  const DerefState &DS = AA.getState();
5055  DerefBytes = DS.DerefBytesState.getAssumed();
5056  T.GlobalState &= DS.GlobalState;
5057  }
5058 
5059  // For now we do not try to "increase" dereferenceability due to negative
5060  // indices as we first have to come up with code to deal with loops and
5061  // for overflows of the dereferenceable bytes.
5062  int64_t OffsetSExt = Offset.getSExtValue();
5063  if (OffsetSExt < 0)
5064  OffsetSExt = 0;
5065 
5066  T.takeAssumedDerefBytesMinimum(
5067  std::max(int64_t(0), DerefBytes - OffsetSExt));
5068 
5069  if (this == &AA) {
5070  if (!Stripped) {
5071  // If nothing was stripped IR information is all we got.
5072  T.takeKnownDerefBytesMaximum(
5073  std::max(int64_t(0), DerefBytes - OffsetSExt));
5074  T.indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
5075  } else if (OffsetSExt > 0) {
5076  // If something was stripped but there is circular reasoning we look
5077  // for the offset. If it is positive we basically decrease the
5078  // dereferenceable bytes in a circular loop now, which will simply
5079  // drive them down to the known value in a very slow way which we
5080  // can accelerate.
5081  T.indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
5082  }
5083  }
5084 
5085  return T.isValidState();
5086  };
5087 
5088  for (const auto &VAC : Values)
5089  if (!VisitValueCB(*VAC.getValue()))
5090  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
5091 
5092  return clampStateAndIndicateChange(getState(), T);
5093  }
5094 
5095  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
5096  void trackStatistics() const override {
5097  STATS_DECLTRACK_FLOATING_ATTR(dereferenceable)
5098  }
5099 };

5155 // ------------------------ Align Argument Attribute ------------------------
5156 
5157 namespace {
5158 static unsigned getKnownAlignForUse(Attributor &A, AAAlign &QueryingAA,
5159  Value &AssociatedValue, const Use *U,
5160  const Instruction *I, bool &TrackUse) {
5161  // We need to follow common pointer manipulation uses to the accesses they
5162  // feed into.
5163  if (isa<CastInst>(I)) {
5164  // Follow all but ptr2int casts.
5165  TrackUse = !isa<PtrToIntInst>(I);
5166  return 0;
5167  }
5168  if (auto *GEP = dyn_cast<GetElementPtrInst>(I)) {
5169  if (GEP->hasAllConstantIndices())
5170  TrackUse = true;
5171  return 0;
5172  }
5173 
5174  MaybeAlign MA;
5175  if (const auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(I)) {
5176  if (CB->isBundleOperand(U) || CB->isCallee(U))
5177  return 0;
5178 
5179  unsigned ArgNo = CB->getArgOperandNo(U);
5180  IRPosition IRP = IRPosition::callsite_argument(*CB, ArgNo);
5181  // As long as we only use known information there is no need to track
5182  // dependences here.
5183  auto &AlignAA = A.getAAFor<AAAlign>(QueryingAA, IRP, DepClassTy::NONE);
5184  MA = MaybeAlign(AlignAA.getKnownAlign());
5185  }
5186 
5187  const DataLayout &DL = A.getDataLayout();
5188  const Value *UseV = U->get();
5189  if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(I)) {
5190  if (SI->getPointerOperand() == UseV)
5191  MA = SI->getAlign();
5192  } else if (auto *LI = dyn_cast<LoadInst>(I)) {
5193  if (LI->getPointerOperand() == UseV)
5194  MA = LI->getAlign();
5195  }
5196 
5197  if (!MA || *MA <= QueryingAA.getKnownAlign())
5198  return 0;
5199 
5200  unsigned Alignment = MA->value();
5201  int64_t Offset;
5202 
5203  if (const Value *Base = GetPointerBaseWithConstantOffset(UseV, Offset, DL)) {
5204  if (Base == &AssociatedValue) {
5205  // BasePointerAddr + Offset = Alignment * Q for some integer Q.
5206  // So we can say that the maximum power of two which is a divisor of
5207  // gcd(Offset, Alignment) is an alignment.
5208 
5209  uint32_t gcd = std::gcd(uint32_t(abs((int32_t)Offset)), Alignment);
5210  Alignment = llvm::bit_floor(gcd);
5211  }
5212  }
5213 
5214  return Alignment;
5215 }
5216 
5217 struct AAAlignImpl : AAAlign {
5218  AAAlignImpl(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A) : AAAlign(IRP, A) {}
5219 
5220  /// See AbstractAttribute::initialize(...).
5221  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
5222  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> Attrs;
5223  getAttrs({Attribute::Alignment}, Attrs);
5224  for (const Attribute &Attr : Attrs)
5225  takeKnownMaximum(Attr.getValueAsInt());
5226 
5227  Value &V = *getAssociatedValue().stripPointerCasts();
5228  takeKnownMaximum(V.getPointerAlignment(A.getDataLayout()).value());
5229 
5230  if (getIRPosition().isFnInterfaceKind() &&
5231  (!getAnchorScope() ||
5232  !A.isFunctionIPOAmendable(*getAssociatedFunction()))) {
5233  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
5234  return;
5235  }
5236 
5237  if (Instruction *CtxI = getCtxI())
5238  followUsesInMBEC(*this, A, getState(), *CtxI);
5239  }
5240 
5241  /// See AbstractAttribute::manifest(...).
5242  ChangeStatus manifest(Attributor &A) override {
5243  ChangeStatus LoadStoreChanged = ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
5244 
5245  // Check for users that allow alignment annotations.
5246  Value &AssociatedValue = getAssociatedValue();
5247  for (const Use &U : AssociatedValue.uses()) {
5248  if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(U.getUser())) {
5249  if (SI->getPointerOperand() == &AssociatedValue)
5250  if (SI->getAlign() < getAssumedAlign()) {
5251  STATS_DECLTRACK(AAAlign, Store,
5252  "Number of times alignment added to a store");
5253  SI->setAlignment(getAssumedAlign());
5254  LoadStoreChanged = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
5255  }
5256  } else if (auto *LI = dyn_cast<LoadInst>(U.getUser())) {
5257  if (LI->getPointerOperand() == &AssociatedValue)
5258  if (LI->getAlign() < getAssumedAlign()) {
5259  LI->setAlignment(getAssumedAlign());
5260  STATS_DECLTRACK(AAAlign, Load,
5261  "Number of times alignment added to a load");
5262  LoadStoreChanged = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
5263  }
5264  }
5265  }
5266 
5267  ChangeStatus Changed = AAAlign::manifest(A);
5268 
5269  Align InheritAlign =
5270  getAssociatedValue().getPointerAlignment(A.getDataLayout());
5271  if (InheritAlign >= getAssumedAlign())
5272  return LoadStoreChanged;
5273  return Changed | LoadStoreChanged;
5274  }
5275 
5276  // TODO: Provide a helper to determine the implied ABI alignment and check in
5277  // the existing manifest method and a new one for AAAlignImpl that value
5278  // to avoid making the alignment explicit if it did not improve.
5279 
5280  /// See AbstractAttribute::getDeducedAttributes
5281  void getDeducedAttributes(LLVMContext &Ctx,
5282  SmallVectorImpl<Attribute> &Attrs) const override {
5283  if (getAssumedAlign() > 1)
5284  Attrs.emplace_back(
5285  Attribute::getWithAlignment(Ctx, Align(getAssumedAlign())));
5286  }
5287 
5288  /// See followUsesInMBEC
5289  bool followUseInMBEC(Attributor &A, const Use *U, const Instruction *I,
5290  AAAlign::StateType &State) {
5291  bool TrackUse = false;
5292 
5293  unsigned int KnownAlign =
5294  getKnownAlignForUse(A, *this, getAssociatedValue(), U, I, TrackUse);
5295  State.takeKnownMaximum(KnownAlign);
5296 
5297  return TrackUse;
5298  }
5299 
5300  /// See AbstractAttribute::getAsStr().
5301  const std::string getAsStr() const override {
5302  return "align<" + std::to_string(getKnownAlign().value()) + "-" +
5303  std::to_string(getAssumedAlign().value()) + ">";
5304  }
5305 };
5306 
5307 /// Align attribute for a floating value.
5308 struct AAAlignFloating : AAAlignImpl {
5309  AAAlignFloating(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A) : AAAlignImpl(IRP, A) {}
5310 
5311  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
5312  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
5313  const DataLayout &DL = A.getDataLayout();
5314 
5315  bool Stripped;
5316  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
5317  SmallVector<AA::ValueAndContext> Values;
5318  if (!A.getAssumedSimplifiedValues(getIRPosition(), *this, Values,
5319  AA::AnyScope, UsedAssumedInformation)) {
5320  Values.push_back({getAssociatedValue(), getCtxI()});
5321  Stripped = false;
5322  } else {
5323  Stripped = Values.size() != 1 ||
5324  Values.front().getValue() != &getAssociatedValue();
5325  }
5326 
5327  StateType T;
5328  auto VisitValueCB = [&](Value &V) -> bool {
5329  if (isa<UndefValue>(V) || isa<ConstantPointerNull>(V))
5330  return true;
5331  const auto &AA = A.getAAFor<AAAlign>(*this, IRPosition::value(V),
5332  DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
5333  if (!Stripped && this == &AA) {
5334  int64_t Offset;
5335  unsigned Alignment = 1;
5336  if (const Value *Base =
5337  GetPointerBaseWithConstantOffset(&V, Offset, DL)) {
5338  // TODO: Use AAAlign for the base too.
5339  Align PA = Base->getPointerAlignment(DL);
5340  // BasePointerAddr + Offset = Alignment * Q for some integer Q.
5341  // So we can say that the maximum power of two which is a divisor of
5342  // gcd(Offset, Alignment) is an alignment.
5343 
5344  uint32_t gcd =
5345  std::gcd(uint32_t(abs((int32_t)Offset)), uint32_t(PA.value()));
5346  Alignment = llvm::bit_floor(gcd);
5347  } else {
5348  Alignment = V.getPointerAlignment(DL).value();
5349  }
5350  // Use only IR information if we did not strip anything.
5351  T.takeKnownMaximum(Alignment);
5352  T.indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
5353  } else {
5354  // Use abstract attribute information.
5355  const AAAlign::StateType &DS = AA.getState();
5356  T ^= DS;
5357  }
5358  return T.isValidState();
5359  };
5360 
5361  for (const auto &VAC : Values) {
5362  if (!VisitValueCB(*VAC.getValue()))
5363  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
5364  }
5365 
5366  // TODO: If we know we visited all incoming values, thus no are assumed
5367  // dead, we can take the known information from the state T.
5368  return clampStateAndIndicateChange(getState(), T);
5369  }
5370 
5371  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
5372  void trackStatistics() const override { STATS_DECLTRACK_FLOATING_ATTR(align) }
5373 };

5413 struct AAAlignCallSiteArgument final : AAAlignFloating {

5415  : AAAlignFloating(IRP, A) {}

5417  /// See AbstractAttribute::manifest(...).

5419  // If the associated argument is involved in a must-tail call we give up
5420  // because we would need to keep the argument alignments of caller and
5421  // callee in-sync. Just does not seem worth the trouble right now.
5422  if (Argument *Arg = getAssociatedArgument())
5423  if (A.getInfoCache().isInvolvedInMustTailCall(*Arg))

5438  // so we do not need to track a dependence.
5439  const auto &ArgAlignAA = A.getAAFor<AAAlign>(
5440  *this, IRPosition::argument(*Arg), DepClassTy::NONE);
5441  takeKnownMaximum(ArgAlignAA.getKnownAlign().value());
5442  }
5443  return Changed;
5444  }

5493  {(unsigned)Instruction::Ret},

5541 /// ----------------------- Instance Info ---------------------------------
5542 
5543 namespace {
5544 /// A class to hold the state of for no-capture attributes.
5545 struct AAInstanceInfoImpl : public AAInstanceInfo {
5546  AAInstanceInfoImpl(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
5547  : AAInstanceInfo(IRP, A) {}
5548 
5549  /// See AbstractAttribute::initialize(...).
5550  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
5551  Value &V = getAssociatedValue();
5552  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(&V)) {
5553  if (C->isThreadDependent())
5554  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
5555  else
5556  indicateOptimisticFixpoint();
5557  return;
5558  }
5559  if (auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(&V))
5560  if (CB->arg_size() == 0 && !CB->mayHaveSideEffects() &&
5561  !CB->mayReadFromMemory()) {
5562  indicateOptimisticFixpoint();
5563  return;
5564  }
5565  }
5566 
5567  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
5568  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
5569  ChangeStatus Changed = ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
5570 
5571  Value &V = getAssociatedValue();
5572  const Function *Scope = nullptr;
5573  if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(&V))
5574  Scope = I->getFunction();
5575  if (auto *A = dyn_cast<Argument>(&V)) {
5576  Scope = A->getParent();
5577  if (!Scope->hasLocalLinkage())
5578  return Changed;
5579  }
5580  if (!Scope)
5581  return indicateOptimisticFixpoint();
5582 
5583  auto &NoRecurseAA = A.getAAFor<AANoRecurse>(
5584  *this, IRPosition::function(*Scope), DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
5585  if (NoRecurseAA.isAssumedNoRecurse())
5586  return Changed;
5587 
5588  auto UsePred = [&](const Use &U, bool &Follow) {
5589  const Instruction *UserI = dyn_cast<Instruction>(U.getUser());
5590  if (!UserI || isa<GetElementPtrInst>(UserI) || isa<CastInst>(UserI) ||
5591  isa<PHINode>(UserI) || isa<SelectInst>(UserI)) {
5592  Follow = true;
5593  return true;
5594  }
5595  if (isa<LoadInst>(UserI) || isa<CmpInst>(UserI) ||
5596  (isa<StoreInst>(UserI) &&
5597  cast<StoreInst>(UserI)->getValueOperand() != U.get()))
5598  return true;
5599  if (auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(UserI)) {
5600  // This check is not guaranteeing uniqueness but for now that we cannot
5601  // end up with two versions of \p U thinking it was one.
5602  if (!CB->getCalledFunction() ||
5603  !CB->getCalledFunction()->hasLocalLinkage())
5604  return true;
5605  if (!CB->isArgOperand(&U))
5606  return false;
5607  const auto &ArgInstanceInfoAA = A.getAAFor<AAInstanceInfo>(
5608  *this, IRPosition::callsite_argument(*CB, CB->getArgOperandNo(&U)),
5609  DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
5610  if (!ArgInstanceInfoAA.isAssumedUniqueForAnalysis())
5611  return false;
5612  // If this call base might reach the scope again we might forward the
5613  // argument back here. This is very conservative.
5614  if (AA::isPotentiallyReachable(
5615  A, *CB, *Scope, *this, /* ExclusionSet */ nullptr,
5616  [Scope](const Function &Fn) { return &Fn != Scope; }))
5617  return false;
5618  return true;
5619  }
5620  return false;
5621  };
5622 
5623  auto EquivalentUseCB = [&](const Use &OldU, const Use &NewU) {
5624  if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(OldU.getUser())) {
5625  auto *Ptr = SI->getPointerOperand()->stripPointerCasts();
5626  if ((isa<AllocaInst>(Ptr) || isNoAliasCall(Ptr)) &&
5627  AA::isDynamicallyUnique(A, *this, *Ptr))
5628  return true;
5629  }
5630  return false;
5631  };
5632 
5633  if (!A.checkForAllUses(UsePred, *this, V, /* CheckBBLivenessOnly */ true,
5634  DepClassTy::OPTIONAL,
5635  /* IgnoreDroppableUses */ true, EquivalentUseCB))
5636  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
5637 
5638  return Changed;
5639  }
5640 
5641  /// See AbstractState::getAsStr().
5642  const std::string getAsStr() const override {
5643  return isAssumedUniqueForAnalysis() ? "<unique [fAa]>" : "<unknown>";
5644  }
5645 
5646  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
5647  void trackStatistics() const override {}
5648 };
5649

5707 
5708 /// ----------------------- Variable Capturing ---------------------------------
5709 
5710 namespace {
5711 /// A class to hold the state of for no-capture attributes.
5712 struct AANoCaptureImpl : public AANoCapture {
5713  AANoCaptureImpl(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A) : AANoCapture(IRP, A) {}
5714 
5715  /// See AbstractAttribute::initialize(...).
5716  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
5717  if (hasAttr(getAttrKind(), /* IgnoreSubsumingPositions */ true)) {
5718  indicateOptimisticFixpoint();
5719  return;
5720  }
5721  Function *AnchorScope = getAnchorScope();
5722  if (isFnInterfaceKind() &&
5723  (!AnchorScope || !A.isFunctionIPOAmendable(*AnchorScope))) {
5724  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
5725  return;
5726  }
5727 
5728  // You cannot "capture" null in the default address space.
5729  if (isa<ConstantPointerNull>(getAssociatedValue()) &&
5730  getAssociatedValue().getType()->getPointerAddressSpace() == 0) {
5731  indicateOptimisticFixpoint();
5732  return;
5733  }
5734 
5735  const Function *F =
5736  isArgumentPosition() ? getAssociatedFunction() : AnchorScope;
5737 
5738  // Check what state the associated function can actually capture.
5739  if (F)
5740  determineFunctionCaptureCapabilities(getIRPosition(), *F, *this);
5741  else
5742  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
5743  }
5744 
5745  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
5746  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override;
5747 
5748  /// see AbstractAttribute::isAssumedNoCaptureMaybeReturned(...).
5749  void getDeducedAttributes(LLVMContext &Ctx,
5750  SmallVectorImpl<Attribute> &Attrs) const override {
5751  if (!isAssumedNoCaptureMaybeReturned())
5752  return;
5753 
5754  if (isArgumentPosition()) {
5755  if (isAssumedNoCapture())
5756  Attrs.emplace_back(Attribute::get(Ctx, Attribute::NoCapture));
5757  else if (ManifestInternal)
5758  Attrs.emplace_back(Attribute::get(Ctx, "no-capture-maybe-returned"));
5759  }
5760  }
5761 
5762  /// Set the NOT_CAPTURED_IN_MEM and NOT_CAPTURED_IN_RET bits in \p Known
5763  /// depending on the ability of the function associated with \p IRP to capture
5764  /// state in memory and through "returning/throwing", respectively.
5765  static void determineFunctionCaptureCapabilities(const IRPosition &IRP,
5766  const Function &F,
5767  BitIntegerState &State) {
5768  // TODO: Once we have memory behavior attributes we should use them here.
5769 
5770  // If we know we cannot communicate or write to memory, we do not care about
5771  // ptr2int anymore.
5772  if (F.onlyReadsMemory() && F.doesNotThrow() &&
5773  F.getReturnType()->isVoidTy()) {
5774  State.addKnownBits(NO_CAPTURE);
5775  return;
5776  }
5777 
5778  // A function cannot capture state in memory if it only reads memory, it can
5779  // however return/throw state and the state might be influenced by the
5780  // pointer value, e.g., loading from a returned pointer might reveal a bit.
5781  if (F.onlyReadsMemory())
5782  State.addKnownBits(NOT_CAPTURED_IN_MEM);
5783 
5784  // A function cannot communicate state back if it does not through
5785  // exceptions and doesn not return values.
5786  if (F.doesNotThrow() && F.getReturnType()->isVoidTy())
5787  State.addKnownBits(NOT_CAPTURED_IN_RET);
5788 
5789  // Check existing "returned" attributes.
5790  int ArgNo = IRP.getCalleeArgNo();
5791  if (F.doesNotThrow() && ArgNo >= 0) {
5792  for (unsigned u = 0, e = F.arg_size(); u < e; ++u)
5793  if (F.hasParamAttribute(u, Attribute::Returned)) {
5794  if (u == unsigned(ArgNo))
5795  State.removeAssumedBits(NOT_CAPTURED_IN_RET);
5796  else if (F.onlyReadsMemory())
5797  State.addKnownBits(NO_CAPTURE);
5798  else
5799  State.addKnownBits(NOT_CAPTURED_IN_RET);
5800  break;
5801  }
5802  }
5803  }
5804 
5805  /// See AbstractState::getAsStr().
5806  const std::string getAsStr() const override {
5807  if (isKnownNoCapture())
5808  return "known not-captured";
5809  if (isAssumedNoCapture())
5810  return "assumed not-captured";
5811  if (isKnownNoCaptureMaybeReturned())
5812  return "known not-captured-maybe-returned";
5813  if (isAssumedNoCaptureMaybeReturned())
5814  return "assumed not-captured-maybe-returned";
5815  return "assumed-captured";
5816  }
5817 
5818  /// Check the use \p U and update \p State accordingly. Return true if we
5819  /// should continue to update the state.
5820  bool checkUse(Attributor &A, AANoCapture::StateType &State, const Use &U,
5821  bool &Follow) {
5822  Instruction *UInst = cast<Instruction>(U.getUser());
5823  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AANoCapture] Check use: " << *U.get() << " in "
5824  << *UInst << "\n");
5825 
5826  // Deal with ptr2int by following uses.
5827  if (isa<PtrToIntInst>(UInst)) {
5828  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " - ptr2int assume the worst!\n");
5829  return isCapturedIn(State, /* Memory */ true, /* Integer */ true,
5830  /* Return */ true);
5831  }
5832 
5833  // For stores we already checked if we can follow them, if they make it
5834  // here we give up.
5835  if (isa<StoreInst>(UInst))
5836  return isCapturedIn(State, /* Memory */ true, /* Integer */ false,
5837  /* Return */ false);
5838 
5839  // Explicitly catch return instructions.
5840  if (isa<ReturnInst>(UInst)) {
5841  if (UInst->getFunction() == getAnchorScope())
5842  return isCapturedIn(State, /* Memory */ false, /* Integer */ false,
5843  /* Return */ true);
5844  return isCapturedIn(State, /* Memory */ true, /* Integer */ true,
5845  /* Return */ true);
5846  }
5847 
5848  // For now we only use special logic for call sites. However, the tracker
5849  // itself knows about a lot of other non-capturing cases already.
5850  auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(UInst);
5851  if (!CB || !CB->isArgOperand(&U))
5852  return isCapturedIn(State, /* Memory */ true, /* Integer */ true,
5853  /* Return */ true);
5854 
5855  unsigned ArgNo = CB->getArgOperandNo(&U);
5856  const IRPosition &CSArgPos = IRPosition::callsite_argument(*CB, ArgNo);
5857  // If we have a abstract no-capture attribute for the argument we can use
5858  // it to justify a non-capture attribute here. This allows recursion!
5859  auto &ArgNoCaptureAA =
5860  A.getAAFor<AANoCapture>(*this, CSArgPos, DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
5861  if (ArgNoCaptureAA.isAssumedNoCapture())
5862  return isCapturedIn(State, /* Memory */ false, /* Integer */ false,
5863  /* Return */ false);
5864  if (ArgNoCaptureAA.isAssumedNoCaptureMaybeReturned()) {
5865  Follow = true;
5866  return isCapturedIn(State, /* Memory */ false, /* Integer */ false,
5867  /* Return */ false);
5868  }
5869 
5870  // Lastly, we could not find a reason no-capture can be assumed so we don't.
5871  return isCapturedIn(State, /* Memory */ true, /* Integer */ true,
5872  /* Return */ true);
5873  }
5874 
5875  /// Update \p State according to \p CapturedInMem, \p CapturedInInt, and
5876  /// \p CapturedInRet, then return true if we should continue updating the
5877  /// state.
5878  static bool isCapturedIn(AANoCapture::StateType &State, bool CapturedInMem,
5879  bool CapturedInInt, bool CapturedInRet) {
5880  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " - captures [Mem " << CapturedInMem << "|Int "
5881  << CapturedInInt << "|Ret " << CapturedInRet << "]\n");
5882  if (CapturedInMem)
5883  State.removeAssumedBits(AANoCapture::NOT_CAPTURED_IN_MEM);
5884  if (CapturedInInt)
5885  State.removeAssumedBits(AANoCapture::NOT_CAPTURED_IN_INT);
5886  if (CapturedInRet)
5887  State.removeAssumedBits(AANoCapture::NOT_CAPTURED_IN_RET);
5888  return State.isAssumed(AANoCapture::NO_CAPTURE_MAYBE_RETURNED);
5889  }
5890 };
5891 
5892 ChangeStatus AANoCaptureImpl::updateImpl(Attributor &A) {
5893  const IRPosition &IRP = getIRPosition();
5894  Value *V = isArgumentPosition() ? IRP.getAssociatedArgument()
5895  : &IRP.getAssociatedValue();
5896  if (!V)
5897  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
5898 
5899  const Function *F =
5900  isArgumentPosition() ? IRP.getAssociatedFunction() : IRP.getAnchorScope();
5901  assert(F && "Expected a function!");
5902  const IRPosition &FnPos = IRPosition::function(*F);
5903 
5904  AANoCapture::StateType T;
5905 
5906  // Readonly means we cannot capture through memory.
5907  bool IsKnown;
5908  if (AA::isAssumedReadOnly(A, FnPos, *this, IsKnown)) {
5909  T.addKnownBits(NOT_CAPTURED_IN_MEM);
5910  if (IsKnown)
5911  addKnownBits(NOT_CAPTURED_IN_MEM);
5912  }
5913 
5914  // Make sure all returned values are different than the underlying value.
5915  // TODO: we could do this in a more sophisticated way inside
5916  // AAReturnedValues, e.g., track all values that escape through returns
5917  // directly somehow.
5918  auto CheckReturnedArgs = [&](const AAReturnedValues &RVAA) {
5919  if (!RVAA.getState().isValidState())
5920  return false;
5921  bool SeenConstant = false;
5922  for (const auto &It : RVAA.returned_values()) {
5923  if (isa<Constant>(It.first)) {
5924  if (SeenConstant)
5925  return false;
5926  SeenConstant = true;
5927  } else if (!isa<Argument>(It.first) ||
5928  It.first == getAssociatedArgument())
5929  return false;
5930  }
5931  return true;
5932  };
5933 
5934  const auto &NoUnwindAA =
5935  A.getAAFor<AANoUnwind>(*this, FnPos, DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
5936  if (NoUnwindAA.isAssumedNoUnwind()) {
5937  bool IsVoidTy = F->getReturnType()->isVoidTy();
5938  const AAReturnedValues *RVAA =
5939  IsVoidTy ? nullptr
5940  : &A.getAAFor<AAReturnedValues>(*this, FnPos,
5941 
5942  DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
5943  if (IsVoidTy || CheckReturnedArgs(*RVAA)) {
5944  T.addKnownBits(NOT_CAPTURED_IN_RET);
5945  if (T.isKnown(NOT_CAPTURED_IN_MEM))
5946  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
5947  if (NoUnwindAA.isKnownNoUnwind() &&
5948  (IsVoidTy || RVAA->getState().isAtFixpoint())) {
5949  addKnownBits(NOT_CAPTURED_IN_RET);
5950  if (isKnown(NOT_CAPTURED_IN_MEM))
5951  return indicateOptimisticFixpoint();
5952  }
5953  }
5954  }
5955 
5956  auto IsDereferenceableOrNull = [&](Value *O, const DataLayout &DL) {
5957  const auto &DerefAA = A.getAAFor<AADereferenceable>(
5958  *this, IRPosition::value(*O), DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
5959  return DerefAA.getAssumedDereferenceableBytes();
5960  };
5961 
5962  auto UseCheck = [&](const Use &U, bool &Follow) -> bool {
5963  switch (DetermineUseCaptureKind(U, IsDereferenceableOrNull)) {
5964  case UseCaptureKind::NO_CAPTURE:
5965  return true;
5966  case UseCaptureKind::MAY_CAPTURE:
5967  return checkUse(A, T, U, Follow);
5968  case UseCaptureKind::PASSTHROUGH:
5969  Follow = true;
5970  return true;
5971  }
5972  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected use capture kind!");
5973  };
5974 
5975  if (!A.checkForAllUses(UseCheck, *this, *V))
5976  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
5977 
5978  AANoCapture::StateType &S = getState();
5979  auto Assumed = S.getAssumed();
5980  S.intersectAssumedBits(T.getAssumed());
5981  if (!isAssumedNoCaptureMaybeReturned())
5982  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
5983  return Assumed == S.getAssumed() ? ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED
5984  : ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
5985 }
5986

6079 
6080 bool ValueSimplifyStateType::unionAssumed(std::optional<Value *> Other) {
6081  // FIXME: Add a typecast support.
6082  SimplifiedAssociatedValue = AA::combineOptionalValuesInAAValueLatice(
6083  SimplifiedAssociatedValue, Other, Ty);
6084  if (SimplifiedAssociatedValue == std::optional<Value *>(nullptr))
6085  return false;
6086 
6087  LLVM_DEBUG({
6088  if (SimplifiedAssociatedValue)
6089  dbgs() << "[ValueSimplify] is assumed to be "
6090  << **SimplifiedAssociatedValue << "\n";
6091  else
6092  dbgs() << "[ValueSimplify] is assumed to be <none>\n";
6093  });
6094  return true;
6095 }
6096 
6097 namespace {
6098 struct AAValueSimplifyImpl : AAValueSimplify {
6099  AAValueSimplifyImpl(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
6100  : AAValueSimplify(IRP, A) {}
6101 
6102  /// See AbstractAttribute::initialize(...).
6103  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
6104  if (getAssociatedValue().getType()->isVoidTy())
6105  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
6106  if (A.hasSimplificationCallback(getIRPosition()))
6107  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
6108  }
6109 
6110  /// See AbstractAttribute::getAsStr().
6111  const std::string getAsStr() const override {
6112  LLVM_DEBUG({
6113  dbgs() << "SAV: " << (bool)SimplifiedAssociatedValue << " ";
6114  if (SimplifiedAssociatedValue && *SimplifiedAssociatedValue)
6115  dbgs() << "SAV: " << **SimplifiedAssociatedValue << " ";
6116  });
6117  return isValidState() ? (isAtFixpoint() ? "simplified" : "maybe-simple")
6118  : "not-simple";
6119  }
6120 
6121  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
6122  void trackStatistics() const override {}
6123 
6124  /// See AAValueSimplify::getAssumedSimplifiedValue()
6125  std::optional<Value *>
6126  getAssumedSimplifiedValue(Attributor &A) const override {
6127  return SimplifiedAssociatedValue;
6128  }
6129 
6130  /// Ensure the return value is \p V with type \p Ty, if not possible return
6131  /// nullptr. If \p Check is true we will only verify such an operation would
6132  /// suceed and return a non-nullptr value if that is the case. No IR is
6133  /// generated or modified.
6134  static Value *ensureType(Attributor &A, Value &V, Type &Ty, Instruction *CtxI,
6135  bool Check) {
6136  if (auto *TypedV = AA::getWithType(V, Ty))
6137  return TypedV;
6138  if (CtxI && V.getType()->canLosslesslyBitCastTo(&Ty))
6139  return Check ? &V
6140  : BitCastInst::CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(&V, &Ty,
6141  "", CtxI);
6142  return nullptr;
6143  }
6144 
6145  /// Reproduce \p I with type \p Ty or return nullptr if that is not posisble.
6146  /// If \p Check is true we will only verify such an operation would suceed and
6147  /// return a non-nullptr value if that is the case. No IR is generated or
6148  /// modified.
6149  static Value *reproduceInst(Attributor &A,
6150  const AbstractAttribute &QueryingAA,
6151  Instruction &I, Type &Ty, Instruction *CtxI,
6152  bool Check, ValueToValueMapTy &VMap) {
6153  assert(CtxI && "Cannot reproduce an instruction without context!");
6154  if (Check && (I.mayReadFromMemory() ||
6155  !isSafeToSpeculativelyExecute(&I, CtxI, /* DT */ nullptr,
6156  /* TLI */ nullptr)))
6157  return nullptr;
6158  for (Value *Op : I.operands()) {
6159  Value *NewOp = reproduceValue(A, QueryingAA, *Op, Ty, CtxI, Check, VMap);
6160  if (!NewOp) {
6161  assert(Check && "Manifest of new value unexpectedly failed!");
6162  return nullptr;
6163  }
6164  if (!Check)
6165  VMap[Op] = NewOp;
6166  }
6167  if (Check)
6168  return &I;
6169 
6170  Instruction *CloneI = I.clone();
6171  // TODO: Try to salvage debug information here.
6172  CloneI->setDebugLoc(DebugLoc());
6173  VMap[&I] = CloneI;
6174  CloneI->insertBefore(CtxI);
6175  RemapInstruction(CloneI, VMap);
6176  return CloneI;
6177  }
6178 
6179  /// Reproduce \p V with type \p Ty or return nullptr if that is not posisble.
6180  /// If \p Check is true we will only verify such an operation would suceed and
6181  /// return a non-nullptr value if that is the case. No IR is generated or
6182  /// modified.
6183  static Value *reproduceValue(Attributor &A,
6184  const AbstractAttribute &QueryingAA, Value &V,
6185  Type &Ty, Instruction *CtxI, bool Check,
6186  ValueToValueMapTy &VMap) {
6187  if (const auto &NewV = VMap.lookup(&V))
6188  return NewV;
6189  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
6190  std::optional<Value *> SimpleV = A.getAssumedSimplified(
6191  V, QueryingAA, UsedAssumedInformation, AA::Interprocedural);
6192  if (!SimpleV.has_value())
6193  return PoisonValue::get(&Ty);
6194  Value *EffectiveV = &V;
6195  if (*SimpleV)
6196  EffectiveV = *SimpleV;
6197  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(EffectiveV))
6198  return C;
6199  if (CtxI && AA::isValidAtPosition(AA::ValueAndContext(*EffectiveV, *CtxI),
6200  A.getInfoCache()))
6201  return ensureType(A, *EffectiveV, Ty, CtxI, Check);
6202  if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(EffectiveV))
6203  if (Value *NewV = reproduceInst(A, QueryingAA, *I, Ty, CtxI, Check, VMap))
6204  return ensureType(A, *NewV, Ty, CtxI, Check);
6205  return nullptr;
6206  }
6207 
6208  /// Return a value we can use as replacement for the associated one, or
6209  /// nullptr if we don't have one that makes sense.
6210  Value *manifestReplacementValue(Attributor &A, Instruction *CtxI) const {
6211  Value *NewV = SimplifiedAssociatedValue
6212  ? *SimplifiedAssociatedValue
6213  : UndefValue::get(getAssociatedType());
6214  if (NewV && NewV != &getAssociatedValue()) {
6215  ValueToValueMapTy VMap;
6216  // First verify we can reprduce the value with the required type at the
6217  // context location before we actually start modifying the IR.
6218  if (reproduceValue(A, *this, *NewV, *getAssociatedType(), CtxI,
6219  /* CheckOnly */ true, VMap))
6220  return reproduceValue(A, *this, *NewV, *getAssociatedType(), CtxI,
6221  /* CheckOnly */ false, VMap);
6222  }
6223  return nullptr;
6224  }
6225 
6226  /// Helper function for querying AAValueSimplify and updating candidate.
6227  /// \param IRP The value position we are trying to unify with SimplifiedValue
6228  bool checkAndUpdate(Attributor &A, const AbstractAttribute &QueryingAA,
6229  const IRPosition &IRP, bool Simplify = true) {
6230  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
6231  std::optional<Value *> QueryingValueSimplified = &IRP.getAssociatedValue();
6232  if (Simplify)
6233  QueryingValueSimplified = A.getAssumedSimplified(
6234  IRP, QueryingAA, UsedAssumedInformation, AA::Interprocedural);
6235  return unionAssumed(QueryingValueSimplified);
6236  }
6237 
6238  /// Returns a candidate is found or not
6239  template <typename AAType> bool askSimplifiedValueFor(Attributor &A) {
6240  if (!getAssociatedValue().getType()->isIntegerTy())
6241  return false;
6242 
6243  // This will also pass the call base context.
6244  const auto &AA =
6245  A.getAAFor<AAType>(*this, getIRPosition(), DepClassTy::NONE);
6246 
6247  std::optional<Constant *> COpt = AA.getAssumedConstant(A);
6248 
6249  if (!COpt) {
6250  SimplifiedAssociatedValue = std::nullopt;
6251  A.recordDependence(AA, *this, DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
6252  return true;
6253  }
6254  if (auto *C = *COpt) {
6255  SimplifiedAssociatedValue = C;
6256  A.recordDependence(AA, *this, DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
6257  return true;
6258  }
6259  return false;
6260  }
6261 
6262  bool askSimplifiedValueForOtherAAs(Attributor &A) {
6263  if (askSimplifiedValueFor<AAValueConstantRange>(A))
6264  return true;
6265  if (askSimplifiedValueFor<AAPotentialConstantValues>(A))
6266  return true;
6267  return false;
6268  }
6269 
6270  /// See AbstractAttribute::manifest(...).
6271  ChangeStatus manifest(Attributor &A) override {
6272  ChangeStatus Changed = ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
6273  for (auto &U : getAssociatedValue().uses()) {
6274  // Check if we need to adjust the insertion point to make sure the IR is
6275  // valid.
6276  Instruction *IP = dyn_cast<Instruction>(U.getUser());
6277  if (auto *PHI = dyn_cast_or_null<PHINode>(IP))
6278  IP = PHI->getIncomingBlock(U)->getTerminator();
6279  if (auto *NewV = manifestReplacementValue(A, IP)) {
6280  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[ValueSimplify] " << getAssociatedValue()
6281  << " -> " << *NewV << " :: " << *this << "\n");
6282  if (A.changeUseAfterManifest(U, *NewV))
6283  Changed = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
6284  }
6285  }
6286 
6287  return Changed | AAValueSimplify::manifest(A);
6288  }
6289 
6290  /// See AbstractState::indicatePessimisticFixpoint(...).
6291  ChangeStatus indicatePessimisticFixpoint() override {
6292  SimplifiedAssociatedValue = &getAssociatedValue();
6293  return AAValueSimplify::indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
6294  }
6295 };
6296 
6297 struct AAValueSimplifyArgument final : AAValueSimplifyImpl {
6298  AAValueSimplifyArgument(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
6299  : AAValueSimplifyImpl(IRP, A) {}
6300 
6301  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
6302  AAValueSimplifyImpl::initialize(A);
6303  if (!getAnchorScope() || getAnchorScope()->isDeclaration())
6304  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
6305  if (hasAttr({Attribute::InAlloca, Attribute::Preallocated,
6306  Attribute::StructRet, Attribute::Nest, Attribute::ByVal},
6307  /* IgnoreSubsumingPositions */ true))
6308  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
6309  }
6310 
6311  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
6312  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
6313  // Byval is only replacable if it is readonly otherwise we would write into
6314  // the replaced value and not the copy that byval creates implicitly.
6315  Argument *Arg = getAssociatedArgument();
6316  if (Arg->hasByValAttr()) {
6317  // TODO: We probably need to verify synchronization is not an issue, e.g.,
6318  // there is no race by not copying a constant byval.
6319  bool IsKnown;
6320  if (!AA::isAssumedReadOnly(A, getIRPosition(), *this, IsKnown))
6321  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
6322  }
6323 
6324  auto Before = SimplifiedAssociatedValue;
6325 
6326  auto PredForCallSite = [&](AbstractCallSite ACS) {
6327  const IRPosition &ACSArgPos =
6328  IRPosition::callsite_argument(ACS, getCallSiteArgNo());
6329  // Check if a coresponding argument was found or if it is on not
6330  // associated (which can happen for callback calls).
6331  if (ACSArgPos.getPositionKind() == IRPosition::IRP_INVALID)
6332  return false;
6333 
6334  // Simplify the argument operand explicitly and check if the result is
6335  // valid in the current scope. This avoids refering to simplified values
6336  // in other functions, e.g., we don't want to say a an argument in a
6337  // static function is actually an argument in a different function.
6338  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
6339  std::optional<Constant *> SimpleArgOp =
6340  A.getAssumedConstant(ACSArgPos, *this, UsedAssumedInformation);
6341  if (!SimpleArgOp)
6342  return true;
6343  if (!*SimpleArgOp)
6344  return false;
6345  if (!AA::isDynamicallyUnique(A, *this, **SimpleArgOp))
6346  return false;
6347  return unionAssumed(*SimpleArgOp);
6348  };
6349 
6350  // Generate a answer specific to a call site context.
6351  bool Success;
6352  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
6353  if (hasCallBaseContext() &&
6354  getCallBaseContext()->getCalledFunction() == Arg->getParent())
6355  Success = PredForCallSite(
6356  AbstractCallSite(&getCallBaseContext()->getCalledOperandUse()));
6357  else
6358  Success = A.checkForAllCallSites(PredForCallSite, *this, true,
6359  UsedAssumedInformation);
6360 
6361  if (!Success)
6362  if (!askSimplifiedValueForOtherAAs(A))
6363  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
6364 
6365  // If a candidate was found in this update, return CHANGED.
6366  return Before == SimplifiedAssociatedValue ? ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED
6367  : ChangeStatus ::CHANGED;
6368  }
6369 
6370  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
6371  void trackStatistics() const override {
6372  STATS_DECLTRACK_ARG_ATTR(value_simplify)
6373  }
6374 };
6375 
6376 struct AAValueSimplifyReturned : AAValueSimplifyImpl {
6377  AAValueSimplifyReturned(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
6378  : AAValueSimplifyImpl(IRP, A) {}
6379 
6380  /// See AAValueSimplify::getAssumedSimplifiedValue()
6381  std::optional<Value *>
6382  getAssumedSimplifiedValue(Attributor &A) const override {
6383  if (!isValidState())
6384  return nullptr;
6385  return SimplifiedAssociatedValue;
6386  }
6387 
6388  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
6389  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
6390  auto Before = SimplifiedAssociatedValue;
6391 
6392  auto ReturnInstCB = [&](Instruction &I) {
6393  auto &RI = cast<ReturnInst>(I);
6394  return checkAndUpdate(
6395  A, *this,
6396  IRPosition::value(*RI.getReturnValue(), getCallBaseContext()));
6397  };
6398 
6399  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
6400  if (!A.checkForAllInstructions(ReturnInstCB, *this, {Instruction::Ret},
6401  UsedAssumedInformation))
6402  if (!askSimplifiedValueForOtherAAs(A))
6403  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
6404 
6405  // If a candidate was found in this update, return CHANGED.
6406  return Before == SimplifiedAssociatedValue ? ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED
6407  : ChangeStatus ::CHANGED;
6408  }
6409 
6410  ChangeStatus manifest(Attributor &A) override {
6411  // We queried AAValueSimplify for the returned values so they will be
6412  // replaced if a simplified form was found. Nothing to do here.
6413  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
6414  }
6415 
6416  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
6417  void trackStatistics() const override {
6418  STATS_DECLTRACK_FNRET_ATTR(value_simplify)
6419  }
6420 };

6482 struct AAValueSimplifyCallSiteReturned : AAValueSimplifyImpl {
6483  AAValueSimplifyCallSiteReturned(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
6484  : AAValueSimplifyImpl(IRP, A) {}
6485 
6486  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
6487  AAValueSimplifyImpl::initialize(A);
6488  Function *Fn = getAssociatedFunction();
6489  if (!Fn) {
6490  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
6491  return;
6492  }
6493  for (Argument &Arg : Fn->args()) {
6494  if (Arg.hasReturnedAttr()) {
6495  auto IRP = IRPosition::callsite_argument(*cast<CallBase>(getCtxI()),
6496  Arg.getArgNo());
6497  if (IRP.getPositionKind() == IRPosition::IRP_CALL_SITE_ARGUMENT &&
6498  checkAndUpdate(A, *this, IRP))
6499  indicateOptimisticFixpoint();
6500  else
6501  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
6502  return;
6503  }
6504  }
6505  }
6506 
6507  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
6508  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
6509  auto Before = SimplifiedAssociatedValue;
6510  auto &RetAA = A.getAAFor<AAReturnedValues>(
6511  *this, IRPosition::function(*getAssociatedFunction()),
6512  DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
6513  auto PredForReturned =
6514  [&](Value &RetVal, const SmallSetVector<ReturnInst *, 4> &RetInsts) {
6515  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
6516  std::optional<Value *> CSRetVal =
6517  A.translateArgumentToCallSiteContent(
6518  &RetVal, *cast<CallBase>(getCtxI()), *this,
6519  UsedAssumedInformation);
6520  SimplifiedAssociatedValue = AA::combineOptionalValuesInAAValueLatice(
6521  SimplifiedAssociatedValue, CSRetVal, getAssociatedType());
6522  return SimplifiedAssociatedValue != std::optional<Value *>(nullptr);
6523  };
6524  if (!RetAA.checkForAllReturnedValuesAndReturnInsts(PredForReturned))
6525  if (!askSimplifiedValueForOtherAAs(A))
6526  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
6527  return Before == SimplifiedAssociatedValue ? ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED
6528  : ChangeStatus ::CHANGED;
6529  }
6530 
6531  void trackStatistics() const override {
6532  STATS_DECLTRACK_CSRET_ATTR(value_simplify)
6533  }
6534 };
6535 
6536 struct AAValueSimplifyCallSiteArgument : AAValueSimplifyFloating {
6537  AAValueSimplifyCallSiteArgument(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
6538  : AAValueSimplifyFloating(IRP, A) {}
6539 
6540  /// See AbstractAttribute::manifest(...).
6541  ChangeStatus manifest(Attributor &A) override {
6542  ChangeStatus Changed = ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
6543  // TODO: We should avoid simplification duplication to begin with.
6544  auto *FloatAA = A.lookupAAFor<AAValueSimplify>(
6545  IRPosition::value(getAssociatedValue()), this, DepClassTy::NONE);
6546  if (FloatAA && FloatAA->getState().isValidState())
6547  return Changed;
6548 
6549  if (auto *NewV = manifestReplacementValue(A, getCtxI())) {
6550  Use &U = cast<CallBase>(&getAnchorValue())
6551  ->getArgOperandUse(getCallSiteArgNo());
6552  if (A.changeUseAfterManifest(U, *NewV))
6553  Changed = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
6554  }
6555 
6556  return Changed | AAValueSimplify::manifest(A);
6557  }
6558 
6559  void trackStatistics() const override {
6560  STATS_DECLTRACK_CSARG_ATTR(value_simplify)
6561  }
6562 };
