6564 
6565 /// ----------------------- Heap-To-Stack Conversion ---------------------------
6566 namespace {
6567 struct AAHeapToStackFunction final : public AAHeapToStack {
6568 
6569  struct AllocationInfo {
6570  /// The call that allocates the memory.
6571  CallBase *const CB;
6572 
6573  /// The library function id for the allocation.
6574  LibFunc LibraryFunctionId = NotLibFunc;
6575 
6576  /// The status wrt. a rewrite.
6577  enum {
6578  STACK_DUE_TO_USE,
6579  STACK_DUE_TO_FREE,
6580  INVALID,
6581  } Status = STACK_DUE_TO_USE;
6582 
6583  /// Flag to indicate if we encountered a use that might free this allocation
6584  /// but which is not in the deallocation infos.
6585  bool HasPotentiallyFreeingUnknownUses = false;
6586 
6587  /// Flag to indicate that we should place the new alloca in the function
6588  /// entry block rather than where the call site (CB) is.
6589  bool MoveAllocaIntoEntry = true;
6590 
6591  /// The set of free calls that use this allocation.
6592  SmallSetVector<CallBase *, 1> PotentialFreeCalls{};
6593  };
6594 
6595  struct DeallocationInfo {
6596  /// The call that deallocates the memory.
6597  CallBase *const CB;
6598  /// The value freed by the call.
6599  Value *FreedOp;
6600 
6601  /// Flag to indicate if we don't know all objects this deallocation might
6602  /// free.
6603  bool MightFreeUnknownObjects = false;
6604 
6605  /// The set of allocation calls that are potentially freed.
6606  SmallSetVector<CallBase *, 1> PotentialAllocationCalls{};
6607  };
6608 
6609  AAHeapToStackFunction(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
6610  : AAHeapToStack(IRP, A) {}
6611 
6612  ~AAHeapToStackFunction() {
6613  // Ensure we call the destructor so we release any memory allocated in the
6614  // sets.
6615  for (auto &It : AllocationInfos)
6616  It.second->~AllocationInfo();
6617  for (auto &It : DeallocationInfos)
6618  It.second->~DeallocationInfo();
6619  }
6620 
6621  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
6622  AAHeapToStack::initialize(A);
6623 
6624  const Function *F = getAnchorScope();
6625  const auto *TLI = A.getInfoCache().getTargetLibraryInfoForFunction(*F);
6626 
6627  auto AllocationIdentifierCB = [&](Instruction &I) {
6628  CallBase *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(&I);
6629  if (!CB)
6630  return true;
6631  if (Value *FreedOp = getFreedOperand(CB, TLI)) {
6632  DeallocationInfos[CB] = new (A.Allocator) DeallocationInfo{CB, FreedOp};
6633  return true;
6634  }
6635  // To do heap to stack, we need to know that the allocation itself is
6636  // removable once uses are rewritten, and that we can initialize the
6637  // alloca to the same pattern as the original allocation result.
6638  if (isRemovableAlloc(CB, TLI)) {
6639  auto *I8Ty = Type::getInt8Ty(CB->getParent()->getContext());
6640  if (nullptr != getInitialValueOfAllocation(CB, TLI, I8Ty)) {
6641  AllocationInfo *AI = new (A.Allocator) AllocationInfo{CB};
6642  AllocationInfos[CB] = AI;
6643  if (TLI)
6644  TLI->getLibFunc(*CB, AI->LibraryFunctionId);
6645  }
6646  }
6647  return true;
6648  };
6649 
6650  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
6651  bool Success = A.checkForAllCallLikeInstructions(
6652  AllocationIdentifierCB, *this, UsedAssumedInformation,
6653  /* CheckBBLivenessOnly */ false,
6654  /* CheckPotentiallyDead */ true);
6655  (void)Success;
6656  assert(Success && "Did not expect the call base visit callback to fail!");
6657 
6658  Attributor::SimplifictionCallbackTy SCB =
6659  [](const IRPosition &, const AbstractAttribute *,
6660  bool &) -> std::optional<Value *> { return nullptr; };
6661  for (const auto &It : AllocationInfos)
6662  A.registerSimplificationCallback(IRPosition::callsite_returned(*It.first),
6663  SCB);
6664  for (const auto &It : DeallocationInfos)
6665  A.registerSimplificationCallback(IRPosition::callsite_returned(*It.first),
6666  SCB);
6667  }
6668 
6669  const std::string getAsStr() const override {
6670  unsigned NumH2SMallocs = 0, NumInvalidMallocs = 0;
6671  for (const auto &It : AllocationInfos) {
6672  if (It.second->Status == AllocationInfo::INVALID)
6673  ++NumInvalidMallocs;
6674  else
6675  ++NumH2SMallocs;
6676  }
6677  return "[H2S] Mallocs Good/Bad: " + std::to_string(NumH2SMallocs) + "/" +
6678  std::to_string(NumInvalidMallocs);
6679  }
6680 
6681  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics().
6682  void trackStatistics() const override {
6683  STATS_DECL(
6684  MallocCalls, Function,
6685  "Number of malloc/calloc/aligned_alloc calls converted to allocas");
6686  for (const auto &It : AllocationInfos)
6687  if (It.second->Status != AllocationInfo::INVALID)
6688  ++BUILD_STAT_NAME(MallocCalls, Function);
6689  }
6690 
6691  bool isAssumedHeapToStack(const CallBase &CB) const override {
6692  if (isValidState())
6693  if (AllocationInfo *AI =
6694  AllocationInfos.lookup(const_cast<CallBase *>(&CB)))
6695  return AI->Status != AllocationInfo::INVALID;
6696  return false;
6697  }
6698 
6699  bool isAssumedHeapToStackRemovedFree(CallBase &CB) const override {
6700  if (!isValidState())
6701  return false;
6702 
6703  for (const auto &It : AllocationInfos) {
6704  AllocationInfo &AI = *It.second;
6705  if (AI.Status == AllocationInfo::INVALID)
6706  continue;
6707 
6708  if (AI.PotentialFreeCalls.count(&CB))
6709  return true;
6710  }
6711 
6712  return false;
6713  }
6714 
6715  ChangeStatus manifest(Attributor &A) override {
6716  assert(getState().isValidState() &&
6717  "Attempted to manifest an invalid state!");
6718 
6719  ChangeStatus HasChanged = ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
6720  Function *F = getAnchorScope();
6721  const auto *TLI = A.getInfoCache().getTargetLibraryInfoForFunction(*F);
6722 
6723  for (auto &It : AllocationInfos) {
6724  AllocationInfo &AI = *It.second;
6725  if (AI.Status == AllocationInfo::INVALID)
6726  continue;
6727 
6728  for (CallBase *FreeCall : AI.PotentialFreeCalls) {
6729  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "H2S: Removing free call: " << *FreeCall << "\n");
6730  A.deleteAfterManifest(*FreeCall);
6731  HasChanged = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
6732  }
6733 
6734  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "H2S: Removing malloc-like call: " << *AI.CB
6735  << "\n");
6736 
6737  auto Remark = [&](OptimizationRemark OR) {
6738  LibFunc IsAllocShared;
6739  if (TLI->getLibFunc(*AI.CB, IsAllocShared))
6740  if (IsAllocShared == LibFunc___kmpc_alloc_shared)
6741  return OR << "Moving globalized variable to the stack.";
6742  return OR << "Moving memory allocation from the heap to the stack.";
6743  };
6744  if (AI.LibraryFunctionId == LibFunc___kmpc_alloc_shared)
6745  A.emitRemark<OptimizationRemark>(AI.CB, "OMP110", Remark);
6746  else
6747  A.emitRemark<OptimizationRemark>(AI.CB, "HeapToStack", Remark);
6748 
6749  const DataLayout &DL = A.getInfoCache().getDL();
6750  Value *Size;
6751  std::optional<APInt> SizeAPI = getSize(A, *this, AI);
6752  if (SizeAPI) {
6753  Size = ConstantInt::get(AI.CB->getContext(), *SizeAPI);
6754  } else {
6755  LLVMContext &Ctx = AI.CB->getContext();
6756  ObjectSizeOpts Opts;
6757  ObjectSizeOffsetEvaluator Eval(DL, TLI, Ctx, Opts);
6758  SizeOffsetEvalType SizeOffsetPair = Eval.compute(AI.CB);
6759  assert(SizeOffsetPair != ObjectSizeOffsetEvaluator::unknown() &&
6760  cast<ConstantInt>(SizeOffsetPair.second)->isZero());
6761  Size = SizeOffsetPair.first;
6762  }
6763 
6764  Instruction *IP =
6765  AI.MoveAllocaIntoEntry ? &F->getEntryBlock().front() : AI.CB;
6766 
6767  Align Alignment(1);
6768  if (MaybeAlign RetAlign = AI.CB->getRetAlign())
6769  Alignment = std::max(Alignment, *RetAlign);
6770  if (Value *Align = getAllocAlignment(AI.CB, TLI)) {
6771  std::optional<APInt> AlignmentAPI = getAPInt(A, *this, *Align);
6772  assert(AlignmentAPI && AlignmentAPI->getZExtValue() > 0 &&
6773  "Expected an alignment during manifest!");
6774  Alignment =
6775  std::max(Alignment, assumeAligned(AlignmentAPI->getZExtValue()));
6776  }
6777 
6778  // TODO: Hoist the alloca towards the function entry.
6779  unsigned AS = DL.getAllocaAddrSpace();
6780  Instruction *Alloca =
6781  new AllocaInst(Type::getInt8Ty(F->getContext()), AS, Size, Alignment,
6782  AI.CB->getName() + ".h2s", IP);
6783 
6784  if (Alloca->getType() != AI.CB->getType())
6785  Alloca = BitCastInst::CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
6786  Alloca, AI.CB->getType(), "malloc_cast", AI.CB);
6787 
6788  auto *I8Ty = Type::getInt8Ty(F->getContext());
6789  auto *InitVal = getInitialValueOfAllocation(AI.CB, TLI, I8Ty);
6790  assert(InitVal &&
6791  "Must be able to materialize initial memory state of allocation");
6792 
6793  A.changeAfterManifest(IRPosition::inst(*AI.CB), *Alloca);
6794 
6795  if (auto *II = dyn_cast<InvokeInst>(AI.CB)) {
6796  auto *NBB = II->getNormalDest();
6797  BranchInst::Create(NBB, AI.CB->getParent());
6798  A.deleteAfterManifest(*AI.CB);
6799  } else {
6800  A.deleteAfterManifest(*AI.CB);
6801  }
6802 
6803  // Initialize the alloca with the same value as used by the allocation
6804  // function. We can skip undef as the initial value of an alloc is
6805  // undef, and the memset would simply end up being DSEd.
6806  if (!isa<UndefValue>(InitVal)) {
6807  IRBuilder<> Builder(Alloca->getNextNode());
6808  // TODO: Use alignment above if align!=1
6809  Builder.CreateMemSet(Alloca, InitVal, Size, std::nullopt);
6810  }
6811  HasChanged = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
6812  }
6813 
6814  return HasChanged;
6815  }
6816 
6817  std::optional<APInt> getAPInt(Attributor &A, const AbstractAttribute &AA,
6818  Value &V) {
6819  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
6820  std::optional<Constant *> SimpleV =
6821  A.getAssumedConstant(V, AA, UsedAssumedInformation);
6822  if (!SimpleV)
6823  return APInt(64, 0);
6824  if (auto *CI = dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantInt>(*SimpleV))
6825  return CI->getValue();
6826  return std::nullopt;
6827  }
6828 
6829  std::optional<APInt> getSize(Attributor &A, const AbstractAttribute &AA,
6830  AllocationInfo &AI) {
6831  auto Mapper = [&](const Value *V) -> const Value * {
6832  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
6833  if (std::optional<Constant *> SimpleV =
6834  A.getAssumedConstant(*V, AA, UsedAssumedInformation))
6835  if (*SimpleV)
6836  return *SimpleV;
6837  return V;
6838  };
6839 
6840  const Function *F = getAnchorScope();
6841  const auto *TLI = A.getInfoCache().getTargetLibraryInfoForFunction(*F);
6842  return getAllocSize(AI.CB, TLI, Mapper);
6843  }
6844 
6845  /// Collection of all malloc-like calls in a function with associated
6846  /// information.
6847  MapVector<CallBase *, AllocationInfo *> AllocationInfos;
6848 
6849  /// Collection of all free-like calls in a function with associated
6850  /// information.
6851  MapVector<CallBase *, DeallocationInfo *> DeallocationInfos;
6852 
6853  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override;
6854 };
6855 
6856 ChangeStatus AAHeapToStackFunction::updateImpl(Attributor &A) {
6857  ChangeStatus Changed = ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
6858  const Function *F = getAnchorScope();
6859  const auto *TLI = A.getInfoCache().getTargetLibraryInfoForFunction(*F);
6860 
6861  const auto &LivenessAA =
6862  A.getAAFor<AAIsDead>(*this, IRPosition::function(*F), DepClassTy::NONE);
6863 
6864  MustBeExecutedContextExplorer &Explorer =
6865  A.getInfoCache().getMustBeExecutedContextExplorer();
6866 
6867  bool StackIsAccessibleByOtherThreads =
6868  A.getInfoCache().stackIsAccessibleByOtherThreads();
6869 
6870  LoopInfo *LI =
6871  A.getInfoCache().getAnalysisResultForFunction<LoopAnalysis>(*F);
6872  std::optional<bool> MayContainIrreducibleControl;
6873  auto IsInLoop = [&](BasicBlock &BB) {
6874  if (&F->getEntryBlock() == &BB)
6875  return false;
6876  if (!MayContainIrreducibleControl.has_value())
6877  MayContainIrreducibleControl = mayContainIrreducibleControl(*F, LI);
6878  if (*MayContainIrreducibleControl)
6879  return true;
6880  if (!LI)
6881  return true;
6882  return LI->getLoopFor(&BB) != nullptr;
6883  };
6884 
6885  // Flag to ensure we update our deallocation information at most once per
6886  // updateImpl call and only if we use the free check reasoning.
6887  bool HasUpdatedFrees = false;
6888 
6889  auto UpdateFrees = [&]() {
6890  HasUpdatedFrees = true;
6891 
6892  for (auto &It : DeallocationInfos) {
6893  DeallocationInfo &DI = *It.second;
6894  // For now we cannot use deallocations that have unknown inputs, skip
6895  // them.
6896  if (DI.MightFreeUnknownObjects)
6897  continue;
6898 
6899  // No need to analyze dead calls, ignore them instead.
6900  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
6901  if (A.isAssumedDead(*DI.CB, this, &LivenessAA, UsedAssumedInformation,
6902  /* CheckBBLivenessOnly */ true))
6903  continue;
6904 
6905  // Use the non-optimistic version to get the freed object.
6906  Value *Obj = getUnderlyingObject(DI.FreedOp);
6907  if (!Obj) {
6908  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[H2S] Unknown underlying object for free!\n");
6909  DI.MightFreeUnknownObjects = true;
6910  continue;
6911  }
6912 
6913  // Free of null and undef can be ignored as no-ops (or UB in the latter
6914  // case).
6915  if (isa<ConstantPointerNull>(Obj) || isa<UndefValue>(Obj))
6916  continue;
6917 
6918  CallBase *ObjCB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(Obj);
6919  if (!ObjCB) {
6920  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[H2S] Free of a non-call object: " << *Obj
6921  << "\n");
6922  DI.MightFreeUnknownObjects = true;
6923  continue;
6924  }
6925 
6926  AllocationInfo *AI = AllocationInfos.lookup(ObjCB);
6927  if (!AI) {
6928  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[H2S] Free of a non-allocation object: " << *Obj
6929  << "\n");
6930  DI.MightFreeUnknownObjects = true;
6931  continue;
6932  }
6933 
6934  DI.PotentialAllocationCalls.insert(ObjCB);
6935  }
6936  };
6937 
6938  auto FreeCheck = [&](AllocationInfo &AI) {
6939  // If the stack is not accessible by other threads, the "must-free" logic
6940  // doesn't apply as the pointer could be shared and needs to be places in
6941  // "shareable" memory.
6942  if (!StackIsAccessibleByOtherThreads) {
6943  auto &NoSyncAA =
6944  A.getAAFor<AANoSync>(*this, getIRPosition(), DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
6945  if (!NoSyncAA.isAssumedNoSync()) {
6946  LLVM_DEBUG(
6947  dbgs() << "[H2S] found an escaping use, stack is not accessible by "
6948  "other threads and function is not nosync:\n");
6949  return false;
6950  }
6951  }
6952  if (!HasUpdatedFrees)
6953  UpdateFrees();
6954 
6955  // TODO: Allow multi exit functions that have different free calls.
6956  if (AI.PotentialFreeCalls.size() != 1) {
6957  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[H2S] did not find one free call but "
6958  << AI.PotentialFreeCalls.size() << "\n");
6959  return false;
6960  }
6961  CallBase *UniqueFree = *AI.PotentialFreeCalls.begin();
6962  DeallocationInfo *DI = DeallocationInfos.lookup(UniqueFree);
6963  if (!DI) {
6964  LLVM_DEBUG(
6965  dbgs() << "[H2S] unique free call was not known as deallocation call "
6966  << *UniqueFree << "\n");
6967  return false;
6968  }
6969  if (DI->MightFreeUnknownObjects) {
6970  LLVM_DEBUG(
6971  dbgs() << "[H2S] unique free call might free unknown allocations\n");
6972  return false;
6973  }
6974  if (DI->PotentialAllocationCalls.empty())
6975  return true;
6976  if (DI->PotentialAllocationCalls.size() > 1) {
6977  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[H2S] unique free call might free "
6978  << DI->PotentialAllocationCalls.size()
6979  << " different allocations\n");
6980  return false;
6981  }
6982  if (*DI->PotentialAllocationCalls.begin() != AI.CB) {
6983  LLVM_DEBUG(
6984  dbgs()
6985  << "[H2S] unique free call not known to free this allocation but "
6986  << **DI->PotentialAllocationCalls.begin() << "\n");
6987  return false;
6988  }
6989  Instruction *CtxI = isa<InvokeInst>(AI.CB) ? AI.CB : AI.CB->getNextNode();
6990  if (!Explorer.findInContextOf(UniqueFree, CtxI)) {
6991  LLVM_DEBUG(
6992  dbgs()
6993  << "[H2S] unique free call might not be executed with the allocation "
6994  << *UniqueFree << "\n");
6995  return false;
6996  }
6997  return true;
6998  };
6999 
7000  auto UsesCheck = [&](AllocationInfo &AI) {
7001  bool ValidUsesOnly = true;
7002 
7003  auto Pred = [&](const Use &U, bool &Follow) -> bool {
7004  Instruction *UserI = cast<Instruction>(U.getUser());
7005  if (isa<LoadInst>(UserI))
7006  return true;
7007  if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(UserI)) {
7008  if (SI->getValueOperand() == U.get()) {
7009  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs()
7010  << "[H2S] escaping store to memory: " << *UserI << "\n");
7011  ValidUsesOnly = false;
7012  } else {
7013  // A store into the malloc'ed memory is fine.
7014  }
7015  return true;
7016  }
7017  if (auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(UserI)) {
7018  if (!CB->isArgOperand(&U) || CB->isLifetimeStartOrEnd())
7019  return true;
7020  if (DeallocationInfos.count(CB)) {
7021  AI.PotentialFreeCalls.insert(CB);
7022  return true;
7023  }
7024 
7025  unsigned ArgNo = CB->getArgOperandNo(&U);
7026 
7027  const auto &NoCaptureAA = A.getAAFor<AANoCapture>(
7028  *this, IRPosition::callsite_argument(*CB, ArgNo),
7029  DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
7030 
7031  // If a call site argument use is nofree, we are fine.
7032  const auto &ArgNoFreeAA = A.getAAFor<AANoFree>(
7033  *this, IRPosition::callsite_argument(*CB, ArgNo),
7034  DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
7035 
7036  bool MaybeCaptured = !NoCaptureAA.isAssumedNoCapture();
7037  bool MaybeFreed = !ArgNoFreeAA.isAssumedNoFree();
7038  if (MaybeCaptured ||
7039  (AI.LibraryFunctionId != LibFunc___kmpc_alloc_shared &&
7040  MaybeFreed)) {
7041  AI.HasPotentiallyFreeingUnknownUses |= MaybeFreed;
7042 
7043  // Emit a missed remark if this is missed OpenMP globalization.
7044  auto Remark = [&](OptimizationRemarkMissed ORM) {
7045  return ORM
7046  << "Could not move globalized variable to the stack. "
7047  "Variable is potentially captured in call. Mark "
7048  "parameter as `__attribute__((noescape))` to override.";
7049  };
7050 
7051  if (ValidUsesOnly &&
7052  AI.LibraryFunctionId == LibFunc___kmpc_alloc_shared)
7053  A.emitRemark<OptimizationRemarkMissed>(CB, "OMP113", Remark);
7054 
7055  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[H2S] Bad user: " << *UserI << "\n");
7056  ValidUsesOnly = false;
7057  }
7058  return true;
7059  }
7060 
7061  if (isa<GetElementPtrInst>(UserI) || isa<BitCastInst>(UserI) ||
7062  isa<PHINode>(UserI) || isa<SelectInst>(UserI)) {
7063  Follow = true;
7064  return true;
7065  }
7066  // Unknown user for which we can not track uses further (in a way that
7067  // makes sense).
7068  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[H2S] Unknown user: " << *UserI << "\n");
7069  ValidUsesOnly = false;
7070  return true;
7071  };
7072  if (!A.checkForAllUses(Pred, *this, *AI.CB))
7073  return false;
7074  return ValidUsesOnly;
7075  };
7076 
7077  // The actual update starts here. We look at all allocations and depending on
7078  // their status perform the appropriate check(s).
7079  for (auto &It : AllocationInfos) {
7080  AllocationInfo &AI = *It.second;
7081  if (AI.Status == AllocationInfo::INVALID)
7082  continue;
7083 
7084  if (Value *Align = getAllocAlignment(AI.CB, TLI)) {
7085  std::optional<APInt> APAlign = getAPInt(A, *this, *Align);
7086  if (!APAlign) {
7087  // Can't generate an alloca which respects the required alignment
7088  // on the allocation.
7089  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[H2S] Unknown allocation alignment: " << *AI.CB
7090  << "\n");
7091  AI.Status = AllocationInfo::INVALID;
7092  Changed = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
7093  continue;
7094  }
7095  if (APAlign->ugt(llvm::Value::MaximumAlignment) ||
7096  !APAlign->isPowerOf2()) {
7097  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[H2S] Invalid allocation alignment: " << APAlign
7098  << "\n");
7099  AI.Status = AllocationInfo::INVALID;
7100  Changed = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
7101  continue;
7102  }
7103  }
7104 
7105  std::optional<APInt> Size = getSize(A, *this, AI);
7106  if (MaxHeapToStackSize != -1) {
7107  if (!Size || Size->ugt(MaxHeapToStackSize)) {
7108  LLVM_DEBUG({
7109  if (!Size)
7110  dbgs() << "[H2S] Unknown allocation size: " << *AI.CB << "\n";
7111  else
7112  dbgs() << "[H2S] Allocation size too large: " << *AI.CB << " vs. "
7113  << MaxHeapToStackSize << "\n";
7114  });
7115 
7116  AI.Status = AllocationInfo::INVALID;
7117  Changed = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
7118  continue;
7119  }
7120  }
7121 
7122  switch (AI.Status) {
7123  case AllocationInfo::STACK_DUE_TO_USE:
7124  if (UsesCheck(AI))
7125  break;
7126  AI.Status = AllocationInfo::STACK_DUE_TO_FREE;
7127  [[fallthrough]];
7128  case AllocationInfo::STACK_DUE_TO_FREE:
7129  if (FreeCheck(AI))
7130  break;
7131  AI.Status = AllocationInfo::INVALID;
7132  Changed = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
7133  break;
7134  case AllocationInfo::INVALID:
7135  llvm_unreachable("Invalid allocations should never reach this point!");
7136  };
7137 
7138  // Check if we still think we can move it into the entry block. If the
7139  // alloca comes from a converted __kmpc_alloc_shared then we can usually
7140  // ignore the potential compilations associated with loops.
7141  bool IsGlobalizedLocal =
7142  AI.LibraryFunctionId == LibFunc___kmpc_alloc_shared;
7143  if (AI.MoveAllocaIntoEntry &&
7144  (!Size.has_value() ||
7145  (!IsGlobalizedLocal && IsInLoop(*AI.CB->getParent()))))
7146  AI.MoveAllocaIntoEntry = false;
7147  }
7148 
7149  return Changed;
7150 }
7151 } // namespace
7152 
7153 /// ----------------------- Privatizable Pointers ------------------------------
7154 namespace {
7155 struct AAPrivatizablePtrImpl : public AAPrivatizablePtr {
7156  AAPrivatizablePtrImpl(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
7157  : AAPrivatizablePtr(IRP, A), PrivatizableType(std::nullopt) {}
7158 
7159  ChangeStatus indicatePessimisticFixpoint() override {
7160  AAPrivatizablePtr::indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
7161  PrivatizableType = nullptr;
7162  return ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
7163  }
7164 
7165  /// Identify the type we can chose for a private copy of the underlying
7166  /// argument. None means it is not clear yet, nullptr means there is none.
7167  virtual std::optional<Type *> identifyPrivatizableType(Attributor &A) = 0;
7168 
7169  /// Return a privatizable type that encloses both T0 and T1.
7170  /// TODO: This is merely a stub for now as we should manage a mapping as well.
7171  std::optional<Type *> combineTypes(std::optional<Type *> T0,
7172  std::optional<Type *> T1) {
7173  if (!T0)
7174  return T1;
7175  if (!T1)
7176  return T0;
7177  if (T0 == T1)
7178  return T0;
7179  return nullptr;
7180  }
7181 
7182  std::optional<Type *> getPrivatizableType() const override {
7183  return PrivatizableType;
7184  }
7185 
7186  const std::string getAsStr() const override {
7187  return isAssumedPrivatizablePtr() ? "[priv]" : "[no-priv]";
7188  }
7189 
7190 protected:
7191  std::optional<Type *> PrivatizableType;
7192 };
7193 
7194 // TODO: Do this for call site arguments (probably also other values) as well.
7195 
7196 struct AAPrivatizablePtrArgument final : public AAPrivatizablePtrImpl {
7197  AAPrivatizablePtrArgument(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
7198  : AAPrivatizablePtrImpl(IRP, A) {}
7199 
7200  /// See AAPrivatizablePtrImpl::identifyPrivatizableType(...)
7201  std::optional<Type *> identifyPrivatizableType(Attributor &A) override {
7202  // If this is a byval argument and we know all the call sites (so we can
7203  // rewrite them), there is no need to check them explicitly.
7204  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
7205  SmallVector<Attribute, 1> Attrs;
7206  getAttrs({Attribute::ByVal}, Attrs, /* IgnoreSubsumingPositions */ true);
7207  if (!Attrs.empty() &&
7208  A.checkForAllCallSites([](AbstractCallSite ACS) { return true; }, *this,
7209  true, UsedAssumedInformation))
7210  return Attrs[0].getValueAsType();
7211 
7212  std::optional<Type *> Ty;
7213  unsigned ArgNo = getIRPosition().getCallSiteArgNo();
7214 
7215  // Make sure the associated call site argument has the same type at all call
7216  // sites and it is an allocation we know is safe to privatize, for now that
7217  // means we only allow alloca instructions.
7218  // TODO: We can additionally analyze the accesses in the callee to create
7219  // the type from that information instead. That is a little more
7220  // involved and will be done in a follow up patch.
7221  auto CallSiteCheck = [&](AbstractCallSite ACS) {
7222  IRPosition ACSArgPos = IRPosition::callsite_argument(ACS, ArgNo);
7223  // Check if a coresponding argument was found or if it is one not
7224  // associated (which can happen for callback calls).
7225  if (ACSArgPos.getPositionKind() == IRPosition::IRP_INVALID)
7226  return false;
7227 
7228  // Check that all call sites agree on a type.
7229  auto &PrivCSArgAA =
7230  A.getAAFor<AAPrivatizablePtr>(*this, ACSArgPos, DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
7231  std::optional<Type *> CSTy = PrivCSArgAA.getPrivatizableType();
7232 
7233  LLVM_DEBUG({
7234  dbgs() << "[AAPrivatizablePtr] ACSPos: " << ACSArgPos << ", CSTy: ";
7235  if (CSTy && *CSTy)
7236  (*CSTy)->print(dbgs());
7237  else if (CSTy)
7238  dbgs() << "<nullptr>";
7239  else
7240  dbgs() << "<none>";
7241  });
7242 
7243  Ty = combineTypes(Ty, CSTy);
7244 
7245  LLVM_DEBUG({
7246  dbgs() << " : New Type: ";
7247  if (Ty && *Ty)
7248  (*Ty)->print(dbgs());
7249  else if (Ty)
7250  dbgs() << "<nullptr>";
7251  else
7252  dbgs() << "<none>";
7253  dbgs() << "\n";
7254  });
7255 
7256  return !Ty || *Ty;
7257  };
7258 
7259  if (!A.checkForAllCallSites(CallSiteCheck, *this, true,
7260  UsedAssumedInformation))
7261  return nullptr;
7262  return Ty;
7263  }
7264 
7265  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
7266  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
7267  PrivatizableType = identifyPrivatizableType(A);
7268  if (!PrivatizableType)
7269  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
7270  if (!*PrivatizableType)
7271  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
7272 
7273  // The dependence is optional so we don't give up once we give up on the
7274  // alignment.
7275  A.getAAFor<AAAlign>(*this, IRPosition::value(getAssociatedValue()),
7276  DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
7277 
7278  // Avoid arguments with padding for now.
7279  if (!getIRPosition().hasAttr(Attribute::ByVal) &&
7280  !isDenselyPacked(*PrivatizableType, A.getInfoCache().getDL())) {
7281  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAPrivatizablePtr] Padding detected\n");
7282  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
7283  }
7284 
7285  // Collect the types that will replace the privatizable type in the function
7286  // signature.
7287  SmallVector<Type *, 16> ReplacementTypes;
7288  identifyReplacementTypes(*PrivatizableType, ReplacementTypes);
7289 
7290  // Verify callee and caller agree on how the promoted argument would be
7291  // passed.
7292  Function &Fn = *getIRPosition().getAnchorScope();
7293  const auto *TTI =
7294  A.getInfoCache().getAnalysisResultForFunction<TargetIRAnalysis>(Fn);
7295  if (!TTI) {
7296  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAPrivatizablePtr] Missing TTI for function "
7297  << Fn.getName() << "\n");
7298  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
7299  }
7300 
7301  auto CallSiteCheck = [&](AbstractCallSite ACS) {
7302  CallBase *CB = ACS.getInstruction();
7303  return TTI->areTypesABICompatible(
7304  CB->getCaller(), CB->getCalledFunction(), ReplacementTypes);
7305  };
7306  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
7307  if (!A.checkForAllCallSites(CallSiteCheck, *this, true,
7308  UsedAssumedInformation)) {
7309  LLVM_DEBUG(
7310  dbgs() << "[AAPrivatizablePtr] ABI incompatibility detected for "
7311  << Fn.getName() << "\n");
7312  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
7313  }
7314 
7315  // Register a rewrite of the argument.
7316  Argument *Arg = getAssociatedArgument();
7317  if (!A.isValidFunctionSignatureRewrite(*Arg, ReplacementTypes)) {
7318  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAPrivatizablePtr] Rewrite not valid\n");
7319  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
7320  }
7321 
7322  unsigned ArgNo = Arg->getArgNo();
7323 
7324  // Helper to check if for the given call site the associated argument is
7325  // passed to a callback where the privatization would be different.
7326  auto IsCompatiblePrivArgOfCallback = [&](CallBase &CB) {
7327  SmallVector<const Use *, 4> CallbackUses;
7328  AbstractCallSite::getCallbackUses(CB, CallbackUses);
7329  for (const Use *U : CallbackUses) {
7330  AbstractCallSite CBACS(U);
7331  assert(CBACS && CBACS.isCallbackCall());
7332  for (Argument &CBArg : CBACS.getCalledFunction()->args()) {
7333  int CBArgNo = CBACS.getCallArgOperandNo(CBArg);
7334 
7335  LLVM_DEBUG({
7336  dbgs()
7337  << "[AAPrivatizablePtr] Argument " << *Arg
7338  << "check if can be privatized in the context of its parent ("
7339  << Arg->getParent()->getName()
7340  << ")\n[AAPrivatizablePtr] because it is an argument in a "
7341  "callback ("
7342  << CBArgNo << "@" << CBACS.getCalledFunction()->getName()
7343  << ")\n[AAPrivatizablePtr] " << CBArg << " : "
7344  << CBACS.getCallArgOperand(CBArg) << " vs "
7345  << CB.getArgOperand(ArgNo) << "\n"
7346  << "[AAPrivatizablePtr] " << CBArg << " : "
7347  << CBACS.getCallArgOperandNo(CBArg) << " vs " << ArgNo << "\n";
7348  });
7349 
7350  if (CBArgNo != int(ArgNo))
7351  continue;
7352  const auto &CBArgPrivAA = A.getAAFor<AAPrivatizablePtr>(
7353  *this, IRPosition::argument(CBArg), DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
7354  if (CBArgPrivAA.isValidState()) {
7355  auto CBArgPrivTy = CBArgPrivAA.getPrivatizableType();
7356  if (!CBArgPrivTy)
7357  continue;
7358  if (*CBArgPrivTy == PrivatizableType)
7359  continue;
7360  }
7361 
7362  LLVM_DEBUG({
7363  dbgs() << "[AAPrivatizablePtr] Argument " << *Arg
7364  << " cannot be privatized in the context of its parent ("
7365  << Arg->getParent()->getName()
7366  << ")\n[AAPrivatizablePtr] because it is an argument in a "
7367  "callback ("
7368  << CBArgNo << "@" << CBACS.getCalledFunction()->getName()
7369  << ").\n[AAPrivatizablePtr] for which the argument "
7370  "privatization is not compatible.\n";
7371  });
7372  return false;
7373  }
7374  }
7375  return true;
7376  };
7377 
7378  // Helper to check if for the given call site the associated argument is
7379  // passed to a direct call where the privatization would be different.
7380  auto IsCompatiblePrivArgOfDirectCS = [&](AbstractCallSite ACS) {
7381  CallBase *DC = cast<CallBase>(ACS.getInstruction());
7382  int DCArgNo = ACS.getCallArgOperandNo(ArgNo);
7383  assert(DCArgNo >= 0 && unsigned(DCArgNo) < DC->arg_size() &&
7384  "Expected a direct call operand for callback call operand");
7385 
7386  LLVM_DEBUG({
7387  dbgs() << "[AAPrivatizablePtr] Argument " << *Arg
7388  << " check if be privatized in the context of its parent ("
7389  << Arg->getParent()->getName()
7390  << ")\n[AAPrivatizablePtr] because it is an argument in a "
7391  "direct call of ("
7392  << DCArgNo << "@" << DC->getCalledFunction()->getName()
7393  << ").\n";
7394  });
7395 
7396  Function *DCCallee = DC->getCalledFunction();
7397  if (unsigned(DCArgNo) < DCCallee->arg_size()) {
7398  const auto &DCArgPrivAA = A.getAAFor<AAPrivatizablePtr>(
7399  *this, IRPosition::argument(*DCCallee->getArg(DCArgNo)),
7400  DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
7401  if (DCArgPrivAA.isValidState()) {
7402  auto DCArgPrivTy = DCArgPrivAA.getPrivatizableType();
7403  if (!DCArgPrivTy)
7404  return true;
7405  if (*DCArgPrivTy == PrivatizableType)
7406  return true;
7407  }
7408  }
7409 
7410  LLVM_DEBUG({
7411  dbgs() << "[AAPrivatizablePtr] Argument " << *Arg
7412  << " cannot be privatized in the context of its parent ("
7413  << Arg->getParent()->getName()
7414  << ")\n[AAPrivatizablePtr] because it is an argument in a "
7415  "direct call of ("
7416  << ACS.getInstruction()->getCalledFunction()->getName()
7417  << ").\n[AAPrivatizablePtr] for which the argument "
7418  "privatization is not compatible.\n";
7419  });
7420  return false;
7421  };
7422 
7423  // Helper to check if the associated argument is used at the given abstract
7424  // call site in a way that is incompatible with the privatization assumed
7425  // here.
7426  auto IsCompatiblePrivArgOfOtherCallSite = [&](AbstractCallSite ACS) {
7427  if (ACS.isDirectCall())
7428  return IsCompatiblePrivArgOfCallback(*ACS.getInstruction());
7429  if (ACS.isCallbackCall())
7430  return IsCompatiblePrivArgOfDirectCS(ACS);
7431  return false;
7432  };
7433 
7434  if (!A.checkForAllCallSites(IsCompatiblePrivArgOfOtherCallSite, *this, true,
7435  UsedAssumedInformation))
7436  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
7437 
7438  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
7439  }
7440 
7441  /// Given a type to private \p PrivType, collect the constituates (which are
7442  /// used) in \p ReplacementTypes.
7443  static void
7444  identifyReplacementTypes(Type *PrivType,
7445  SmallVectorImpl<Type *> &ReplacementTypes) {
7446  // TODO: For now we expand the privatization type to the fullest which can
7447  // lead to dead arguments that need to be removed later.
7448  assert(PrivType && "Expected privatizable type!");
7449 
7450  // Traverse the type, extract constituate types on the outermost level.
7451  if (auto *PrivStructType = dyn_cast<StructType>(PrivType)) {
7452  for (unsigned u = 0, e = PrivStructType->getNumElements(); u < e; u++)
7453  ReplacementTypes.push_back(PrivStructType->getElementType(u));
7454  } else if (auto *PrivArrayType = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(PrivType)) {
7455  ReplacementTypes.append(PrivArrayType->getNumElements(),
7456  PrivArrayType->getElementType());
7457  } else {
7458  ReplacementTypes.push_back(PrivType);
7459  }
7460  }
7461 
7462  /// Initialize \p Base according to the type \p PrivType at position \p IP.
7463  /// The values needed are taken from the arguments of \p F starting at
7464  /// position \p ArgNo.
7465  static void createInitialization(Type *PrivType, Value &Base, Function &F,
7466  unsigned ArgNo, Instruction &IP) {
7467  assert(PrivType && "Expected privatizable type!");
7468 
7469  IRBuilder<NoFolder> IRB(&IP);
7470  const DataLayout &DL = F.getParent()->getDataLayout();
7471 
7472  // Traverse the type, build GEPs and stores.
7473  if (auto *PrivStructType = dyn_cast<StructType>(PrivType)) {
7474  const StructLayout *PrivStructLayout = DL.getStructLayout(PrivStructType);
7475  for (unsigned u = 0, e = PrivStructType->getNumElements(); u < e; u++) {
7476  Type *PointeeTy = PrivStructType->getElementType(u)->getPointerTo();
7477  Value *Ptr =
7478  constructPointer(PointeeTy, PrivType, &Base,
7479  PrivStructLayout->getElementOffset(u), IRB, DL);
7480  new StoreInst(F.getArg(ArgNo + u), Ptr, &IP);
7481  }
7482  } else if (auto *PrivArrayType = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(PrivType)) {
7483  Type *PointeeTy = PrivArrayType->getElementType();
7484  Type *PointeePtrTy = PointeeTy->getPointerTo();
7485  uint64_t PointeeTySize = DL.getTypeStoreSize(PointeeTy);
7486  for (unsigned u = 0, e = PrivArrayType->getNumElements(); u < e; u++) {
7487  Value *Ptr = constructPointer(PointeePtrTy, PrivType, &Base,
7488  u * PointeeTySize, IRB, DL);
7489  new StoreInst(F.getArg(ArgNo + u), Ptr, &IP);
7490  }
7491  } else {
7492  new StoreInst(F.getArg(ArgNo), &Base, &IP);
7493  }
7494  }
7495 
7496  /// Extract values from \p Base according to the type \p PrivType at the
7497  /// call position \p ACS. The values are appended to \p ReplacementValues.
7498  void createReplacementValues(Align Alignment, Type *PrivType,
7499  AbstractCallSite ACS, Value *Base,
7500  SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &ReplacementValues) {
7501  assert(Base && "Expected base value!");
7502  assert(PrivType && "Expected privatizable type!");
7503  Instruction *IP = ACS.getInstruction();
7504 
7505  IRBuilder<NoFolder> IRB(IP);
7506  const DataLayout &DL = IP->getModule()->getDataLayout();
7507 
7508  Type *PrivPtrType = PrivType->getPointerTo();
7509  if (Base->getType() != PrivPtrType)
7510  Base = BitCastInst::CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
7511  Base, PrivPtrType, "", ACS.getInstruction());
7512 
7513  // Traverse the type, build GEPs and loads.
7514  if (auto *PrivStructType = dyn_cast<StructType>(PrivType)) {
7515  const StructLayout *PrivStructLayout = DL.getStructLayout(PrivStructType);
7516  for (unsigned u = 0, e = PrivStructType->getNumElements(); u < e; u++) {
7517  Type *PointeeTy = PrivStructType->getElementType(u);
7518  Value *Ptr =
7519  constructPointer(PointeeTy->getPointerTo(), PrivType, Base,
7520  PrivStructLayout->getElementOffset(u), IRB, DL);
7521  LoadInst *L = new LoadInst(PointeeTy, Ptr, "", IP);
7522  L->setAlignment(Alignment);
7523  ReplacementValues.push_back(L);
7524  }
7525  } else if (auto *PrivArrayType = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(PrivType)) {
7526  Type *PointeeTy = PrivArrayType->getElementType();
7527  uint64_t PointeeTySize = DL.getTypeStoreSize(PointeeTy);
7528  Type *PointeePtrTy = PointeeTy->getPointerTo();
7529  for (unsigned u = 0, e = PrivArrayType->getNumElements(); u < e; u++) {
7530  Value *Ptr = constructPointer(PointeePtrTy, PrivType, Base,
7531  u * PointeeTySize, IRB, DL);
7532  LoadInst *L = new LoadInst(PointeeTy, Ptr, "", IP);
7533  L->setAlignment(Alignment);
7534  ReplacementValues.push_back(L);
7535  }
7536  } else {
7537  LoadInst *L = new LoadInst(PrivType, Base, "", IP);
7538  L->setAlignment(Alignment);
7539  ReplacementValues.push_back(L);
7540  }
7541  }
7542 
7543  /// See AbstractAttribute::manifest(...)
7544  ChangeStatus manifest(Attributor &A) override {
7545  if (!PrivatizableType)
7546  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
7547  assert(*PrivatizableType && "Expected privatizable type!");
7548 
7549  // Collect all tail calls in the function as we cannot allow new allocas to
7550  // escape into tail recursion.
7551  // TODO: Be smarter about new allocas escaping into tail calls.
7552  SmallVector<CallInst *, 16> TailCalls;
7553  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
7554  if (!A.checkForAllInstructions(
7555  [&](Instruction &I) {
7556  CallInst &CI = cast<CallInst>(I);
7557  if (CI.isTailCall())
7558  TailCalls.push_back(&CI);
7559  return true;
7560  },
7561  *this, {Instruction::Call}, UsedAssumedInformation))
7562  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
7563 
7564  Argument *Arg = getAssociatedArgument();
7565  // Query AAAlign attribute for alignment of associated argument to
7566  // determine the best alignment of loads.
7567  const auto &AlignAA =
7568  A.getAAFor<AAAlign>(*this, IRPosition::value(*Arg), DepClassTy::NONE);
7569 
7570  // Callback to repair the associated function. A new alloca is placed at the
7571  // beginning and initialized with the values passed through arguments. The
7572  // new alloca replaces the use of the old pointer argument.
7573  Attributor::ArgumentReplacementInfo::CalleeRepairCBTy FnRepairCB =
7574  [=](const Attributor::ArgumentReplacementInfo &ARI,
7575  Function &ReplacementFn, Function::arg_iterator ArgIt) {
7576  BasicBlock &EntryBB = ReplacementFn.getEntryBlock();
7577  Instruction *IP = &*EntryBB.getFirstInsertionPt();
7578  const DataLayout &DL = IP->getModule()->getDataLayout();
7579  unsigned AS = DL.getAllocaAddrSpace();
7580  Instruction *AI = new AllocaInst(*PrivatizableType, AS,
7581  Arg->getName() + ".priv", IP);
7582  createInitialization(*PrivatizableType, *AI, ReplacementFn,
7583  ArgIt->getArgNo(), *IP);
7584 
7585  if (AI->getType() != Arg->getType())
7586  AI = BitCastInst::CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
7587  AI, Arg->getType(), "", IP);
7588  Arg->replaceAllUsesWith(AI);
7589 
7590  for (CallInst *CI : TailCalls)
7591  CI->setTailCall(false);
7592  };
7593 
7594  // Callback to repair a call site of the associated function. The elements
7595  // of the privatizable type are loaded prior to the call and passed to the
7596  // new function version.
7597  Attributor::ArgumentReplacementInfo::ACSRepairCBTy ACSRepairCB =
7598  [=, &AlignAA](const Attributor::ArgumentReplacementInfo &ARI,
7599  AbstractCallSite ACS,
7600  SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &NewArgOperands) {
7601  // When no alignment is specified for the load instruction,
7602  // natural alignment is assumed.
7603  createReplacementValues(
7604  AlignAA.getAssumedAlign(), *PrivatizableType, ACS,
7605  ACS.getCallArgOperand(ARI.getReplacedArg().getArgNo()),
7606  NewArgOperands);
7607  };
7608 
7609  // Collect the types that will replace the privatizable type in the function
7610  // signature.
7611  SmallVector<Type *, 16> ReplacementTypes;
7612  identifyReplacementTypes(*PrivatizableType, ReplacementTypes);
7613 
7614  // Register a rewrite of the argument.
7615  if (A.registerFunctionSignatureRewrite(*Arg, ReplacementTypes,
7616  std::move(FnRepairCB),
7617  std::move(ACSRepairCB)))
7618  return ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
7619  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
7620  }
7621 
7622  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
7623  void trackStatistics() const override {
7624  STATS_DECLTRACK_ARG_ATTR(privatizable_ptr);
7625  }
7626 };
7627 
7628 struct AAPrivatizablePtrFloating : public AAPrivatizablePtrImpl {
7629  AAPrivatizablePtrFloating(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
7630  : AAPrivatizablePtrImpl(IRP, A) {}
7631 
7632  /// See AbstractAttribute::initialize(...).
7633  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
7634  // TODO: We can privatize more than arguments.
7635  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
7636  }
7637 
7638  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
7639  llvm_unreachable("AAPrivatizablePtr(Floating|Returned|CallSiteReturned)::"
7640  "updateImpl will not be called");
7641  }
7642 
7643  /// See AAPrivatizablePtrImpl::identifyPrivatizableType(...)
7644  std::optional<Type *> identifyPrivatizableType(Attributor &A) override {
7645  Value *Obj = getUnderlyingObject(&getAssociatedValue());
7646  if (!Obj) {
7647  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAPrivatizablePtr] No underlying object found!\n");
7648  return nullptr;
7649  }
7650 
7651  if (auto *AI = dyn_cast<AllocaInst>(Obj))
7652  if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(AI->getArraySize()))
7653  if (CI->isOne())
7654  return AI->getAllocatedType();
7655  if (auto *Arg = dyn_cast<Argument>(Obj)) {
7656  auto &PrivArgAA = A.getAAFor<AAPrivatizablePtr>(
7657  *this, IRPosition::argument(*Arg), DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
7658  if (PrivArgAA.isAssumedPrivatizablePtr())
7659  return PrivArgAA.getPrivatizableType();
7660  }
7661 
7662  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAPrivatizablePtr] Underlying object neither valid "
7663  "alloca nor privatizable argument: "
7664  << *Obj << "!\n");
7665  return nullptr;
7666  }
7667 
7668  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
7669  void trackStatistics() const override {
7670  STATS_DECLTRACK_FLOATING_ATTR(privatizable_ptr);
7671  }
7672 };
7673 
7674 struct AAPrivatizablePtrCallSiteArgument final
7675  : public AAPrivatizablePtrFloating {
7676  AAPrivatizablePtrCallSiteArgument(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
7677  : AAPrivatizablePtrFloating(IRP, A) {}
7678 
7679  /// See AbstractAttribute::initialize(...).
7680  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
7681  if (getIRPosition().hasAttr(Attribute::ByVal))
7682  indicateOptimisticFixpoint();
7683  }
7684 
7685  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
7686  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
7687  PrivatizableType = identifyPrivatizableType(A);
7688  if (!PrivatizableType)
7689  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
7690  if (!*PrivatizableType)
7691  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
7692 
7693  const IRPosition &IRP = getIRPosition();
7694  auto &NoCaptureAA =
7695  A.getAAFor<AANoCapture>(*this, IRP, DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
7696  if (!NoCaptureAA.isAssumedNoCapture()) {
7697  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAPrivatizablePtr] pointer might be captured!\n");
7698  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
7699  }
7700 
7701  auto &NoAliasAA = A.getAAFor<AANoAlias>(*this, IRP, DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
7702  if (!NoAliasAA.isAssumedNoAlias()) {
7703  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAPrivatizablePtr] pointer might alias!\n");
7704  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
7705  }
7706 
7707  bool IsKnown;
7708  if (!AA::isAssumedReadOnly(A, IRP, *this, IsKnown)) {
7709  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAPrivatizablePtr] pointer is written!\n");
7710  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
7711  }
7712 
7713  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
7714  }
7715 
7716  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
7717  void trackStatistics() const override {
7718  STATS_DECLTRACK_CSARG_ATTR(privatizable_ptr);
7719  }
7720 };

7756 /// -------------------- Memory Behavior Attributes ----------------------------
7757 /// Includes read-none, read-only, and write-only.
7758 /// ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
7759 namespace {
7760 struct AAMemoryBehaviorImpl : public AAMemoryBehavior {
7761  AAMemoryBehaviorImpl(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
7762  : AAMemoryBehavior(IRP, A) {}
7763 
7764  /// See AbstractAttribute::initialize(...).
7765  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
7766  intersectAssumedBits(BEST_STATE);
7767  getKnownStateFromValue(getIRPosition(), getState());
7768  AAMemoryBehavior::initialize(A);
7769  }
7770 
7771  /// Return the memory behavior information encoded in the IR for \p IRP.
7772  static void getKnownStateFromValue(const IRPosition &IRP,
7773  BitIntegerState &State,
7774  bool IgnoreSubsumingPositions = false) {
7775  SmallVector<Attribute, 2> Attrs;
7776  IRP.getAttrs(AttrKinds, Attrs, IgnoreSubsumingPositions);
7777  for (const Attribute &Attr : Attrs) {
7778  switch (Attr.getKindAsEnum()) {
7779  case Attribute::ReadNone:
7780  State.addKnownBits(NO_ACCESSES);
7781  break;
7782  case Attribute::ReadOnly:
7783  State.addKnownBits(NO_WRITES);
7784  break;
7785  case Attribute::WriteOnly:
7786  State.addKnownBits(NO_READS);
7787  break;
7788  default:
7789  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected attribute!");
7790  }
7791  }
7792 
7793  if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(&IRP.getAnchorValue())) {
7794  if (!I->mayReadFromMemory())
7795  State.addKnownBits(NO_READS);
7796  if (!I->mayWriteToMemory())
7797  State.addKnownBits(NO_WRITES);
7798  }
7799  }
7800 
7801  /// See AbstractAttribute::getDeducedAttributes(...).
7802  void getDeducedAttributes(LLVMContext &Ctx,
7803  SmallVectorImpl<Attribute> &Attrs) const override {
7804  assert(Attrs.size() == 0);
7805  if (isAssumedReadNone())
7806  Attrs.push_back(Attribute::get(Ctx, Attribute::ReadNone));
7807  else if (isAssumedReadOnly())
7808  Attrs.push_back(Attribute::get(Ctx, Attribute::ReadOnly));
7809  else if (isAssumedWriteOnly())
7810  Attrs.push_back(Attribute::get(Ctx, Attribute::WriteOnly));
7811  assert(Attrs.size() <= 1);
7812  }
7813 
7814  /// See AbstractAttribute::manifest(...).
7815  ChangeStatus manifest(Attributor &A) override {
7816  if (hasAttr(Attribute::ReadNone, /* IgnoreSubsumingPositions */ true))
7817  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
7818 
7819  const IRPosition &IRP = getIRPosition();
7820 
7821  // Check if we would improve the existing attributes first.
7822  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> DeducedAttrs;
7823  getDeducedAttributes(IRP.getAnchorValue().getContext(), DeducedAttrs);
7824  if (llvm::all_of(DeducedAttrs, [&](const Attribute &Attr) {
7825  return IRP.hasAttr(Attr.getKindAsEnum(),
7826  /* IgnoreSubsumingPositions */ true);
7827  }))
7828  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
7829 
7830  // Clear existing attributes.
7831  IRP.removeAttrs(AttrKinds);
7832 
7833  // Use the generic manifest method.
7834  return IRAttribute::manifest(A);
7835  }
7836 
7837  /// See AbstractState::getAsStr().
7838  const std::string getAsStr() const override {
7839  if (isAssumedReadNone())
7840  return "readnone";
7841  if (isAssumedReadOnly())
7842  return "readonly";
7843  if (isAssumedWriteOnly())
7844  return "writeonly";
7845  return "may-read/write";
7846  }
7847 
7848  /// The set of IR attributes AAMemoryBehavior deals with.
7849  static const Attribute::AttrKind AttrKinds[3];
7850 };
7851 
7852 const Attribute::AttrKind AAMemoryBehaviorImpl::AttrKinds[] = {
7853  Attribute::ReadNone, Attribute::ReadOnly, Attribute::WriteOnly};
7854 
7855 /// Memory behavior attribute for a floating value.
7856 struct AAMemoryBehaviorFloating : AAMemoryBehaviorImpl {
7857  AAMemoryBehaviorFloating(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
7858  : AAMemoryBehaviorImpl(IRP, A) {}
7859 
7860  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
7861  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override;
7862 
7863  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
7864  void trackStatistics() const override {
7865  if (isAssumedReadNone())
7866  STATS_DECLTRACK_FLOATING_ATTR(readnone)
7867  else if (isAssumedReadOnly())
7868  STATS_DECLTRACK_FLOATING_ATTR(readonly)
7869  else if (isAssumedWriteOnly())
7870  STATS_DECLTRACK_FLOATING_ATTR(writeonly)
7871  }
7872 
7873 private:
7874  /// Return true if users of \p UserI might access the underlying
7875  /// variable/location described by \p U and should therefore be analyzed.
7876  bool followUsersOfUseIn(Attributor &A, const Use &U,
7877  const Instruction *UserI);
7878 
7879  /// Update the state according to the effect of use \p U in \p UserI.
7880  void analyzeUseIn(Attributor &A, const Use &U, const Instruction *UserI);
7881 };
7882 
7883 /// Memory behavior attribute for function argument.
7884 struct AAMemoryBehaviorArgument : AAMemoryBehaviorFloating {
7885  AAMemoryBehaviorArgument(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
7886  : AAMemoryBehaviorFloating(IRP, A) {}
7887 
7888  /// See AbstractAttribute::initialize(...).
7889  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
7890  intersectAssumedBits(BEST_STATE);
7891  const IRPosition &IRP = getIRPosition();
7892  // TODO: Make IgnoreSubsumingPositions a property of an IRAttribute so we
7893  // can query it when we use has/getAttr. That would allow us to reuse the
7894  // initialize of the base class here.
7895  bool HasByVal =
7896  IRP.hasAttr({Attribute::ByVal}, /* IgnoreSubsumingPositions */ true);
7897  getKnownStateFromValue(IRP, getState(),
7898  /* IgnoreSubsumingPositions */ HasByVal);
7899 
7900  // Initialize the use vector with all direct uses of the associated value.
7901  Argument *Arg = getAssociatedArgument();
7902  if (!Arg || !A.isFunctionIPOAmendable(*(Arg->getParent())))
7903  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
7904  }
7905 
7906  ChangeStatus manifest(Attributor &A) override {
7907  // TODO: Pointer arguments are not supported on vectors of pointers yet.
7908  if (!getAssociatedValue().getType()->isPointerTy())
7909  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
7910 
7911  // TODO: From readattrs.ll: "inalloca parameters are always
7912  // considered written"
7913  if (hasAttr({Attribute::InAlloca, Attribute::Preallocated})) {
7914  removeKnownBits(NO_WRITES);
7915  removeAssumedBits(NO_WRITES);
7916  }
7917  return AAMemoryBehaviorFloating::manifest(A);
7918  }
7919 
7920  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
7921  void trackStatistics() const override {
7922  if (isAssumedReadNone())
7923  STATS_DECLTRACK_ARG_ATTR(readnone)
7924  else if (isAssumedReadOnly())
7925  STATS_DECLTRACK_ARG_ATTR(readonly)
7926  else if (isAssumedWriteOnly())
7927  STATS_DECLTRACK_ARG_ATTR(writeonly)
7928  }
7929 };

7931 struct AAMemoryBehaviorCallSiteArgument final : AAMemoryBehaviorArgument {
7932  AAMemoryBehaviorCallSiteArgument(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
7933  : AAMemoryBehaviorArgument(IRP, A) {}
7934 
7935  /// See AbstractAttribute::initialize(...).
7936  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
7937  // If we don't have an associated attribute this is either a variadic call
7938  // or an indirect call, either way, nothing to do here.
7939  Argument *Arg = getAssociatedArgument();
7940  if (!Arg) {
7941  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
7942  return;
7943  }
7944  if (Arg->hasByValAttr()) {
7945  addKnownBits(NO_WRITES);
7946  removeKnownBits(NO_READS);
7947  removeAssumedBits(NO_READS);
7948  }
7949  AAMemoryBehaviorArgument::initialize(A);
7950  if (getAssociatedFunction()->isDeclaration())
7951  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
7952  }
7953 
7954  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
7955  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
7956  // TODO: Once we have call site specific value information we can provide
7957  // call site specific liveness liveness information and then it makes
7958  // sense to specialize attributes for call sites arguments instead of
7959  // redirecting requests to the callee argument.
7960  Argument *Arg = getAssociatedArgument();
7961  const IRPosition &ArgPos = IRPosition::argument(*Arg);
7962  auto &ArgAA =
7963  A.getAAFor<AAMemoryBehavior>(*this, ArgPos, DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
7964  return clampStateAndIndicateChange(getState(), ArgAA.getState());
7965  }
7966 
7967  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
7968  void trackStatistics() const override {
7969  if (isAssumedReadNone())
7970  STATS_DECLTRACK_CSARG_ATTR(readnone)
7971  else if (isAssumedReadOnly())
7972  STATS_DECLTRACK_CSARG_ATTR(readonly)
7973  else if (isAssumedWriteOnly())
7974  STATS_DECLTRACK_CSARG_ATTR(writeonly)
7975  }
7976 };

7978 /// Memory behavior attribute for a call site return position.

7991  /// See AbstractAttribute::manifest(...).

7995  }

8001 /// An AA to represent the memory behavior function attributes.
8002 struct AAMemoryBehaviorFunction final : public AAMemoryBehaviorImpl {
8003  AAMemoryBehaviorFunction(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
8004  : AAMemoryBehaviorImpl(IRP, A) {}
8005 
8006  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(Attributor &A).
8007  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override;
8008 
8009  /// See AbstractAttribute::manifest(...).
8010  ChangeStatus manifest(Attributor &A) override {
8011  // TODO: It would be better to merge this with AAMemoryLocation, so that
8012  // we could determine read/write per location. This would also have the
8013  // benefit of only one place trying to manifest the memory attribute.
8014  Function &F = cast<Function>(getAnchorValue());
8015  MemoryEffects ME = MemoryEffects::unknown();
8016  if (isAssumedReadNone())
8017  ME = MemoryEffects::none();
8018  else if (isAssumedReadOnly())
8019  ME = MemoryEffects::readOnly();
8020  else if (isAssumedWriteOnly())
8021  ME = MemoryEffects::writeOnly();
8022 
8023  // Intersect with existing memory attribute, as we currently deduce the
8024  // location and modref portion separately.
8025  MemoryEffects ExistingME = F.getMemoryEffects();
8026  ME &= ExistingME;
8027  if (ME == ExistingME)
8028  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
8029 
8030  return IRAttributeManifest::manifestAttrs(
8031  A, getIRPosition(), Attribute::getWithMemoryEffects(F.getContext(), ME),
8032  /*ForceReplace*/ true);
8033  }
8034 
8035  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
8036  void trackStatistics() const override {
8037  if (isAssumedReadNone())
8038  STATS_DECLTRACK_FN_ATTR(readnone)
8039  else if (isAssumedReadOnly())
8040  STATS_DECLTRACK_FN_ATTR(readonly)
8041  else if (isAssumedWriteOnly())
8042  STATS_DECLTRACK_FN_ATTR(writeonly)
8043  }
8044 };

8046 /// AAMemoryBehavior attribute for call sites.
8047 struct AAMemoryBehaviorCallSite final : AAMemoryBehaviorImpl {
8048  AAMemoryBehaviorCallSite(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)

8059  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
8060  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
8061  // TODO: Once we have call site specific value information we can provide
8062  // call site specific liveness liveness information and then it makes
8063  // sense to specialize attributes for call sites arguments instead of
8064  // redirecting requests to the callee argument.
8065  Function *F = getAssociatedFunction();
8066  const IRPosition &FnPos = IRPosition::function(*F);
8067  auto &FnAA =
8068  A.getAAFor<AAMemoryBehavior>(*this, FnPos, DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
8069  return clampStateAndIndicateChange(getState(), FnAA.getState());
8070  }
8071 
8072  /// See AbstractAttribute::manifest(...).
8073  ChangeStatus manifest(Attributor &A) override {
8074  // TODO: Deduplicate this with AAMemoryBehaviorFunction.
8075  CallBase &CB = cast<CallBase>(getAnchorValue());
8076  MemoryEffects ME = MemoryEffects::unknown();
8077  if (isAssumedReadNone())
8078  ME = MemoryEffects::none();
8079  else if (isAssumedReadOnly())
8080  ME = MemoryEffects::readOnly();
8081  else if (isAssumedWriteOnly())
8082  ME = MemoryEffects::writeOnly();
8083 
8084  // Intersect with existing memory attribute, as we currently deduce the
8085  // location and modref portion separately.
8086  MemoryEffects ExistingME = CB.getMemoryEffects();
8087  ME &= ExistingME;
8088  if (ME == ExistingME)
8089  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
8090 
8091  return IRAttributeManifest::manifestAttrs(
8092  A, getIRPosition(),
8093  Attribute::getWithMemoryEffects(CB.getContext(), ME),
8094  /*ForceReplace*/ true);
8095  }
