8098  void trackStatistics() const override {
8099  if (isAssumedReadNone())
8100  STATS_DECLTRACK_CS_ATTR(readnone)
8101  else if (isAssumedReadOnly())
8102  STATS_DECLTRACK_CS_ATTR(readonly)
8103  else if (isAssumedWriteOnly())
8104  STATS_DECLTRACK_CS_ATTR(writeonly)
8105  }
8106 };
8107 
8108 ChangeStatus AAMemoryBehaviorFunction::updateImpl(Attributor &A) {
8109 
8110  // The current assumed state used to determine a change.
8111  auto AssumedState = getAssumed();
8112 
8113  auto CheckRWInst = [&](Instruction &I) {
8114  // If the instruction has an own memory behavior state, use it to restrict
8115  // the local state. No further analysis is required as the other memory
8116  // state is as optimistic as it gets.
8117  if (const auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(&I)) {
8118  const auto &MemBehaviorAA = A.getAAFor<AAMemoryBehavior>(
8119  *this, IRPosition::callsite_function(*CB), DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
8120  intersectAssumedBits(MemBehaviorAA.getAssumed());
8121  return !isAtFixpoint();
8122  }
8123 
8124  // Remove access kind modifiers if necessary.
8125  if (I.mayReadFromMemory())
8126  removeAssumedBits(NO_READS);
8127  if (I.mayWriteToMemory())
8128  removeAssumedBits(NO_WRITES);
8129  return !isAtFixpoint();
8130  };
8131 
8132  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
8133  if (!A.checkForAllReadWriteInstructions(CheckRWInst, *this,
8134  UsedAssumedInformation))
8135  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
8136 
8137  return (AssumedState != getAssumed()) ? ChangeStatus::CHANGED
8138  : ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
8139 }
8140 
8141 ChangeStatus AAMemoryBehaviorFloating::updateImpl(Attributor &A) {
8142 
8143  const IRPosition &IRP = getIRPosition();
8144  const IRPosition &FnPos = IRPosition::function_scope(IRP);
8145  AAMemoryBehavior::StateType &S = getState();
8146 
8147  // First, check the function scope. We take the known information and we avoid
8148  // work if the assumed information implies the current assumed information for
8149  // this attribute. This is a valid for all but byval arguments.
8150  Argument *Arg = IRP.getAssociatedArgument();
8151  AAMemoryBehavior::base_t FnMemAssumedState =
8152  AAMemoryBehavior::StateType::getWorstState();
8153  if (!Arg || !Arg->hasByValAttr()) {
8154  const auto &FnMemAA =
8155  A.getAAFor<AAMemoryBehavior>(*this, FnPos, DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
8156  FnMemAssumedState = FnMemAA.getAssumed();
8157  S.addKnownBits(FnMemAA.getKnown());
8158  if ((S.getAssumed() & FnMemAA.getAssumed()) == S.getAssumed())
8159  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
8160  }
8161 
8162  // The current assumed state used to determine a change.
8163  auto AssumedState = S.getAssumed();
8164 
8165  // Make sure the value is not captured (except through "return"), if
8166  // it is, any information derived would be irrelevant anyway as we cannot
8167  // check the potential aliases introduced by the capture. However, no need
8168  // to fall back to anythign less optimistic than the function state.
8169  const auto &ArgNoCaptureAA =
8170  A.getAAFor<AANoCapture>(*this, IRP, DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
8171  if (!ArgNoCaptureAA.isAssumedNoCaptureMaybeReturned()) {
8172  S.intersectAssumedBits(FnMemAssumedState);
8173  return (AssumedState != getAssumed()) ? ChangeStatus::CHANGED
8174  : ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
8175  }
8176 
8177  // Visit and expand uses until all are analyzed or a fixpoint is reached.
8178  auto UsePred = [&](const Use &U, bool &Follow) -> bool {
8179  Instruction *UserI = cast<Instruction>(U.getUser());
8180  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAMemoryBehavior] Use: " << *U << " in " << *UserI
8181  << " \n");
8182 
8183  // Droppable users, e.g., llvm::assume does not actually perform any action.
8184  if (UserI->isDroppable())
8185  return true;
8186 
8187  // Check if the users of UserI should also be visited.
8188  Follow = followUsersOfUseIn(A, U, UserI);
8189 
8190  // If UserI might touch memory we analyze the use in detail.
8191  if (UserI->mayReadOrWriteMemory())
8192  analyzeUseIn(A, U, UserI);
8193 
8194  return !isAtFixpoint();
8195  };
8196 
8197  if (!A.checkForAllUses(UsePred, *this, getAssociatedValue()))
8198  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
8199 
8200  return (AssumedState != getAssumed()) ? ChangeStatus::CHANGED
8201  : ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
8202 }
8203 
8204 bool AAMemoryBehaviorFloating::followUsersOfUseIn(Attributor &A, const Use &U,
8205  const Instruction *UserI) {
8206  // The loaded value is unrelated to the pointer argument, no need to
8207  // follow the users of the load.
8208  if (isa<LoadInst>(UserI) || isa<ReturnInst>(UserI))
8209  return false;
8210 
8211  // By default we follow all uses assuming UserI might leak information on U,
8212  // we have special handling for call sites operands though.
8213  const auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(UserI);
8214  if (!CB || !CB->isArgOperand(&U))
8215  return true;
8216 
8217  // If the use is a call argument known not to be captured, the users of
8218  // the call do not need to be visited because they have to be unrelated to
8219  // the input. Note that this check is not trivial even though we disallow
8220  // general capturing of the underlying argument. The reason is that the
8221  // call might the argument "through return", which we allow and for which we
8222  // need to check call users.
8223  if (U.get()->getType()->isPointerTy()) {
8224  unsigned ArgNo = CB->getArgOperandNo(&U);
8225  const auto &ArgNoCaptureAA = A.getAAFor<AANoCapture>(
8226  *this, IRPosition::callsite_argument(*CB, ArgNo), DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
8227  return !ArgNoCaptureAA.isAssumedNoCapture();
8228  }
8229 
8230  return true;
8231 }
8232 
8233 void AAMemoryBehaviorFloating::analyzeUseIn(Attributor &A, const Use &U,
8234  const Instruction *UserI) {
8235  assert(UserI->mayReadOrWriteMemory());
8236 
8237  switch (UserI->getOpcode()) {
8238  default:
8239  // TODO: Handle all atomics and other side-effect operations we know of.
8240  break;
8241  case Instruction::Load:
8242  // Loads cause the NO_READS property to disappear.
8243  removeAssumedBits(NO_READS);
8244  return;
8245 
8246  case Instruction::Store:
8247  // Stores cause the NO_WRITES property to disappear if the use is the
8248  // pointer operand. Note that while capturing was taken care of somewhere
8249  // else we need to deal with stores of the value that is not looked through.
8250  if (cast<StoreInst>(UserI)->getPointerOperand() == U.get())
8251  removeAssumedBits(NO_WRITES);
8252  else
8253  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
8254  return;
8255 
8256  case Instruction::Call:
8257  case Instruction::CallBr:
8258  case Instruction::Invoke: {
8259  // For call sites we look at the argument memory behavior attribute (this
8260  // could be recursive!) in order to restrict our own state.
8261  const auto *CB = cast<CallBase>(UserI);
8262 
8263  // Give up on operand bundles.
8264  if (CB->isBundleOperand(&U)) {
8265  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
8266  return;
8267  }
8268 
8269  // Calling a function does read the function pointer, maybe write it if the
8270  // function is self-modifying.
8271  if (CB->isCallee(&U)) {
8272  removeAssumedBits(NO_READS);
8273  break;
8274  }
8275 
8276  // Adjust the possible access behavior based on the information on the
8277  // argument.
8278  IRPosition Pos;
8279  if (U.get()->getType()->isPointerTy())
8280  Pos = IRPosition::callsite_argument(*CB, CB->getArgOperandNo(&U));
8281  else
8282  Pos = IRPosition::callsite_function(*CB);
8283  const auto &MemBehaviorAA =
8284  A.getAAFor<AAMemoryBehavior>(*this, Pos, DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
8285  // "assumed" has at most the same bits as the MemBehaviorAA assumed
8286  // and at least "known".
8287  intersectAssumedBits(MemBehaviorAA.getAssumed());
8288  return;
8289  }
8290  };
8291 
8292  // Generally, look at the "may-properties" and adjust the assumed state if we
8293  // did not trigger special handling before.
8294  if (UserI->mayReadFromMemory())
8295  removeAssumedBits(NO_READS);
8296  if (UserI->mayWriteToMemory())
8297  removeAssumedBits(NO_WRITES);
8298 }
8299 } // namespace
8300 
8301 /// -------------------- Memory Locations Attributes ---------------------------
8302 /// Includes read-none, argmemonly, inaccessiblememonly,
8303 /// inaccessiblememorargmemonly
8304 /// ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
8305 
8306 std::string AAMemoryLocation::getMemoryLocationsAsStr(
8307  AAMemoryLocation::MemoryLocationsKind MLK) {
8308  if (0 == (MLK & AAMemoryLocation::NO_LOCATIONS))
8309  return "all memory";
8310  if (MLK == AAMemoryLocation::NO_LOCATIONS)
8311  return "no memory";
8312  std::string S = "memory:";
8313  if (0 == (MLK & AAMemoryLocation::NO_LOCAL_MEM))
8314  S += "stack,";
8315  if (0 == (MLK & AAMemoryLocation::NO_CONST_MEM))
8316  S += "constant,";
8317  if (0 == (MLK & AAMemoryLocation::NO_GLOBAL_INTERNAL_MEM))
8318  S += "internal global,";
8319  if (0 == (MLK & AAMemoryLocation::NO_GLOBAL_EXTERNAL_MEM))
8320  S += "external global,";
8321  if (0 == (MLK & AAMemoryLocation::NO_ARGUMENT_MEM))
8322  S += "argument,";
8323  if (0 == (MLK & AAMemoryLocation::NO_INACCESSIBLE_MEM))
8324  S += "inaccessible,";
8325  if (0 == (MLK & AAMemoryLocation::NO_MALLOCED_MEM))
8326  S += "malloced,";
8327  if (0 == (MLK & AAMemoryLocation::NO_UNKOWN_MEM))
8328  S += "unknown,";
8329  S.pop_back();
8330  return S;
8331 }
8332 
8333 namespace {
8334 struct AAMemoryLocationImpl : public AAMemoryLocation {
8335 
8336  AAMemoryLocationImpl(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
8337  : AAMemoryLocation(IRP, A), Allocator(A.Allocator) {
8338  AccessKind2Accesses.fill(nullptr);
8339  }
8340 
8341  ~AAMemoryLocationImpl() {
8342  // The AccessSets are allocated via a BumpPtrAllocator, we call
8343  // the destructor manually.
8344  for (AccessSet *AS : AccessKind2Accesses)
8345  if (AS)
8346  AS->~AccessSet();
8347  }
8348 
8349  /// See AbstractAttribute::initialize(...).
8350  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
8351  intersectAssumedBits(BEST_STATE);
8352  getKnownStateFromValue(A, getIRPosition(), getState());
8353  AAMemoryLocation::initialize(A);
8354  }
8355 
8356  /// Return the memory behavior information encoded in the IR for \p IRP.
8357  static void getKnownStateFromValue(Attributor &A, const IRPosition &IRP,
8358  BitIntegerState &State,
8359  bool IgnoreSubsumingPositions = false) {
8360  // For internal functions we ignore `argmemonly` and
8361  // `inaccessiblememorargmemonly` as we might break it via interprocedural
8362  // constant propagation. It is unclear if this is the best way but it is
8363  // unlikely this will cause real performance problems. If we are deriving
8364  // attributes for the anchor function we even remove the attribute in
8365  // addition to ignoring it.
8366  // TODO: A better way to handle this would be to add ~NO_GLOBAL_MEM /
8367  // MemoryEffects::Other as a possible location.
8368  bool UseArgMemOnly = true;
8369  Function *AnchorFn = IRP.getAnchorScope();
8370  if (AnchorFn && A.isRunOn(*AnchorFn))
8371  UseArgMemOnly = !AnchorFn->hasLocalLinkage();
8372 
8373  SmallVector<Attribute, 2> Attrs;
8374  IRP.getAttrs({Attribute::Memory}, Attrs, IgnoreSubsumingPositions);
8375  for (const Attribute &Attr : Attrs) {
8376  // TODO: We can map MemoryEffects to Attributor locations more precisely.
8377  MemoryEffects ME = Attr.getMemoryEffects();
8378  if (ME.doesNotAccessMemory()) {
8379  State.addKnownBits(NO_LOCAL_MEM | NO_CONST_MEM);
8380  continue;
8381  }
8382  if (ME.onlyAccessesInaccessibleMem()) {
8383  State.addKnownBits(inverseLocation(NO_INACCESSIBLE_MEM, true, true));
8384  continue;
8385  }
8386  if (ME.onlyAccessesArgPointees()) {
8387  if (UseArgMemOnly)
8388  State.addKnownBits(inverseLocation(NO_ARGUMENT_MEM, true, true));
8389  else {
8390  // Remove location information, only keep read/write info.
8391  ME = MemoryEffects(ME.getModRef());
8392  IRAttributeManifest::manifestAttrs(
8393  A, IRP,
8394  Attribute::getWithMemoryEffects(IRP.getAnchorValue().getContext(),
8395  ME),
8396  /*ForceReplace*/ true);
8397  }
8398  continue;
8399  }
8400  if (ME.onlyAccessesInaccessibleOrArgMem()) {
8401  if (UseArgMemOnly)
8402  State.addKnownBits(inverseLocation(
8403  NO_INACCESSIBLE_MEM | NO_ARGUMENT_MEM, true, true));
8404  else {
8405  // Remove location information, only keep read/write info.
8406  ME = MemoryEffects(ME.getModRef());
8407  IRAttributeManifest::manifestAttrs(
8408  A, IRP,
8409  Attribute::getWithMemoryEffects(IRP.getAnchorValue().getContext(),
8410  ME),
8411  /*ForceReplace*/ true);
8412  }
8413  continue;
8414  }
8415  }
8416  }
8417 
8418  /// See AbstractAttribute::getDeducedAttributes(...).
8419  void getDeducedAttributes(LLVMContext &Ctx,
8420  SmallVectorImpl<Attribute> &Attrs) const override {
8421  // TODO: We can map Attributor locations to MemoryEffects more precisely.
8422  assert(Attrs.size() == 0);
8423  if (getIRPosition().getPositionKind() == IRPosition::IRP_FUNCTION) {
8424  if (isAssumedReadNone())
8425  Attrs.push_back(
8426  Attribute::getWithMemoryEffects(Ctx, MemoryEffects::none()));
8427  else if (isAssumedInaccessibleMemOnly())
8428  Attrs.push_back(Attribute::getWithMemoryEffects(
8429  Ctx, MemoryEffects::inaccessibleMemOnly()));
8430  else if (isAssumedArgMemOnly())
8431  Attrs.push_back(
8432  Attribute::getWithMemoryEffects(Ctx, MemoryEffects::argMemOnly()));
8433  else if (isAssumedInaccessibleOrArgMemOnly())
8434  Attrs.push_back(Attribute::getWithMemoryEffects(
8435  Ctx, MemoryEffects::inaccessibleOrArgMemOnly()));
8436  }
8437  assert(Attrs.size() <= 1);
8438  }
8439 
8440  /// See AbstractAttribute::manifest(...).
8441  ChangeStatus manifest(Attributor &A) override {
8442  // TODO: If AAMemoryLocation and AAMemoryBehavior are merged, we could
8443  // provide per-location modref information here.
8444  const IRPosition &IRP = getIRPosition();
8445 
8446  SmallVector<Attribute, 1> DeducedAttrs;
8447  getDeducedAttributes(IRP.getAnchorValue().getContext(), DeducedAttrs);
8448  if (DeducedAttrs.size() != 1)
8449  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
8450  MemoryEffects ME = DeducedAttrs[0].getMemoryEffects();
8451 
8452  // Intersect with existing memory attribute, as we currently deduce the
8453  // location and modref portion separately.
8454  SmallVector<Attribute, 1> ExistingAttrs;
8455  IRP.getAttrs({Attribute::Memory}, ExistingAttrs,
8456  /* IgnoreSubsumingPositions */ true);
8457  if (ExistingAttrs.size() == 1) {
8458  MemoryEffects ExistingME = ExistingAttrs[0].getMemoryEffects();
8459  ME &= ExistingME;
8460  if (ME == ExistingME)
8461  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
8462  }
8463 
8464  return IRAttributeManifest::manifestAttrs(
8465  A, IRP,
8466  Attribute::getWithMemoryEffects(IRP.getAnchorValue().getContext(), ME),
8467  /*ForceReplace*/ true);
8468  }
8469 
8470  /// See AAMemoryLocation::checkForAllAccessesToMemoryKind(...).
8471  bool checkForAllAccessesToMemoryKind(
8472  function_ref<bool(const Instruction *, const Value *, AccessKind,
8473  MemoryLocationsKind)>
8474  Pred,
8475  MemoryLocationsKind RequestedMLK) const override {
8476  if (!isValidState())
8477  return false;
8478 
8479  MemoryLocationsKind AssumedMLK = getAssumedNotAccessedLocation();
8480  if (AssumedMLK == NO_LOCATIONS)
8481  return true;
8482 
8483  unsigned Idx = 0;
8484  for (MemoryLocationsKind CurMLK = 1; CurMLK < NO_LOCATIONS;
8485  CurMLK *= 2, ++Idx) {
8486  if (CurMLK & RequestedMLK)
8487  continue;
8488 
8489  if (const AccessSet *Accesses = AccessKind2Accesses[Idx])
8490  for (const AccessInfo &AI : *Accesses)
8491  if (!Pred(AI.I, AI.Ptr, AI.Kind, CurMLK))
8492  return false;
8493  }
8494 
8495  return true;
8496  }
8497 
8498  ChangeStatus indicatePessimisticFixpoint() override {
8499  // If we give up and indicate a pessimistic fixpoint this instruction will
8500  // become an access for all potential access kinds:
8501  // TODO: Add pointers for argmemonly and globals to improve the results of
8502  // checkForAllAccessesToMemoryKind.
8503  bool Changed = false;
8504  MemoryLocationsKind KnownMLK = getKnown();
8505  Instruction *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(&getAssociatedValue());
8506  for (MemoryLocationsKind CurMLK = 1; CurMLK < NO_LOCATIONS; CurMLK *= 2)
8507  if (!(CurMLK & KnownMLK))
8508  updateStateAndAccessesMap(getState(), CurMLK, I, nullptr, Changed,
8509  getAccessKindFromInst(I));
8510  return AAMemoryLocation::indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
8511  }
8512 
8513 protected:
8514  /// Helper struct to tie together an instruction that has a read or write
8515  /// effect with the pointer it accesses (if any).
8516  struct AccessInfo {
8517 
8518  /// The instruction that caused the access.
8519  const Instruction *I;
8520 
8521  /// The base pointer that is accessed, or null if unknown.
8522  const Value *Ptr;
8523 
8524  /// The kind of access (read/write/read+write).
8525  AccessKind Kind;
8526 
8527  bool operator==(const AccessInfo &RHS) const {
8528  return I == RHS.I && Ptr == RHS.Ptr && Kind == RHS.Kind;
8529  }
8530  bool operator()(const AccessInfo &LHS, const AccessInfo &RHS) const {
8531  if (LHS.I != RHS.I)
8532  return LHS.I < RHS.I;
8533  if (LHS.Ptr != RHS.Ptr)
8534  return LHS.Ptr < RHS.Ptr;
8535  if (LHS.Kind != RHS.Kind)
8536  return LHS.Kind < RHS.Kind;
8537  return false;
8538  }
8539  };
8540 
8541  /// Mapping from *single* memory location kinds, e.g., LOCAL_MEM with the
8542  /// value of NO_LOCAL_MEM, to the accesses encountered for this memory kind.
8543  using AccessSet = SmallSet<AccessInfo, 2, AccessInfo>;
8544  std::array<AccessSet *, llvm::CTLog2<VALID_STATE>()> AccessKind2Accesses;
8545 
8546  /// Categorize the pointer arguments of CB that might access memory in
8547  /// AccessedLoc and update the state and access map accordingly.
8548  void
8549  categorizeArgumentPointerLocations(Attributor &A, CallBase &CB,
8550  AAMemoryLocation::StateType &AccessedLocs,
8551  bool &Changed);
8552 
8553  /// Return the kind(s) of location that may be accessed by \p V.
8554  AAMemoryLocation::MemoryLocationsKind
8555  categorizeAccessedLocations(Attributor &A, Instruction &I, bool &Changed);
8556 
8557  /// Return the access kind as determined by \p I.
8558  AccessKind getAccessKindFromInst(const Instruction *I) {
8559  AccessKind AK = READ_WRITE;
8560  if (I) {
8561  AK = I->mayReadFromMemory() ? READ : NONE;
8562  AK = AccessKind(AK | (I->mayWriteToMemory() ? WRITE : NONE));
8563  }
8564  return AK;
8565  }
8566 
8567  /// Update the state \p State and the AccessKind2Accesses given that \p I is
8568  /// an access of kind \p AK to a \p MLK memory location with the access
8569  /// pointer \p Ptr.
8570  void updateStateAndAccessesMap(AAMemoryLocation::StateType &State,
8571  MemoryLocationsKind MLK, const Instruction *I,
8572  const Value *Ptr, bool &Changed,
8573  AccessKind AK = READ_WRITE) {
8574 
8575  assert(isPowerOf2_32(MLK) && "Expected a single location set!");
8576  auto *&Accesses = AccessKind2Accesses[llvm::Log2_32(MLK)];
8577  if (!Accesses)
8578  Accesses = new (Allocator) AccessSet();
8579  Changed |= Accesses->insert(AccessInfo{I, Ptr, AK}).second;
8580  State.removeAssumedBits(MLK);
8581  }
8582 
8583  /// Determine the underlying locations kinds for \p Ptr, e.g., globals or
8584  /// arguments, and update the state and access map accordingly.
8585  void categorizePtrValue(Attributor &A, const Instruction &I, const Value &Ptr,
8586  AAMemoryLocation::StateType &State, bool &Changed);
8587 
8588  /// Used to allocate access sets.
8589  BumpPtrAllocator &Allocator;
8590 };
8591 
8592 void AAMemoryLocationImpl::categorizePtrValue(
8593  Attributor &A, const Instruction &I, const Value &Ptr,
8594  AAMemoryLocation::StateType &State, bool &Changed) {
8595  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAMemoryLocation] Categorize pointer locations for "
8596  << Ptr << " ["
8597  << getMemoryLocationsAsStr(State.getAssumed()) << "]\n");
8598 
8599  auto Pred = [&](Value &Obj) {
8600  // TODO: recognize the TBAA used for constant accesses.
8601  MemoryLocationsKind MLK = NO_LOCATIONS;
8602  if (isa<UndefValue>(&Obj))
8603  return true;
8604  if (isa<Argument>(&Obj)) {
8605  // TODO: For now we do not treat byval arguments as local copies performed
8606  // on the call edge, though, we should. To make that happen we need to
8607  // teach various passes, e.g., DSE, about the copy effect of a byval. That
8608  // would also allow us to mark functions only accessing byval arguments as
8609  // readnone again, arguably their accesses have no effect outside of the
8610  // function, like accesses to allocas.
8611  MLK = NO_ARGUMENT_MEM;
8612  } else if (auto *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalValue>(&Obj)) {
8613  // Reading constant memory is not treated as a read "effect" by the
8614  // function attr pass so we won't neither. Constants defined by TBAA are
8615  // similar. (We know we do not write it because it is constant.)
8616  if (auto *GVar = dyn_cast<GlobalVariable>(GV))
8617  if (GVar->isConstant())
8618  return true;
8619 
8620  if (GV->hasLocalLinkage())
8621  MLK = NO_GLOBAL_INTERNAL_MEM;
8622  else
8623  MLK = NO_GLOBAL_EXTERNAL_MEM;
8624  } else if (isa<ConstantPointerNull>(&Obj) &&
8625  !NullPointerIsDefined(getAssociatedFunction(),
8626  Ptr.getType()->getPointerAddressSpace())) {
8627  return true;
8628  } else if (isa<AllocaInst>(&Obj)) {
8629  MLK = NO_LOCAL_MEM;
8630  } else if (const auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(&Obj)) {
8631  const auto &NoAliasAA = A.getAAFor<AANoAlias>(
8632  *this, IRPosition::callsite_returned(*CB), DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
8633  if (NoAliasAA.isAssumedNoAlias())
8634  MLK = NO_MALLOCED_MEM;
8635  else
8636  MLK = NO_UNKOWN_MEM;
8637  } else {
8638  MLK = NO_UNKOWN_MEM;
8639  }
8640 
8641  assert(MLK != NO_LOCATIONS && "No location specified!");
8642  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAMemoryLocation] Ptr value can be categorized: "
8643  << Obj << " -> " << getMemoryLocationsAsStr(MLK) << "\n");
8644  updateStateAndAccessesMap(getState(), MLK, &I, &Obj, Changed,
8645  getAccessKindFromInst(&I));
8646 
8647  return true;
8648  };
8649 
8650  const auto &AA = A.getAAFor<AAUnderlyingObjects>(
8651  *this, IRPosition::value(Ptr), DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
8652  if (!AA.forallUnderlyingObjects(Pred, AA::Intraprocedural)) {
8653  LLVM_DEBUG(
8654  dbgs() << "[AAMemoryLocation] Pointer locations not categorized\n");
8655  updateStateAndAccessesMap(State, NO_UNKOWN_MEM, &I, nullptr, Changed,
8656  getAccessKindFromInst(&I));
8657  return;
8658  }
8659 
8660  LLVM_DEBUG(
8661  dbgs() << "[AAMemoryLocation] Accessed locations with pointer locations: "
8662  << getMemoryLocationsAsStr(State.getAssumed()) << "\n");
8663 }
8664 
8665 void AAMemoryLocationImpl::categorizeArgumentPointerLocations(
8666  Attributor &A, CallBase &CB, AAMemoryLocation::StateType &AccessedLocs,
8667  bool &Changed) {
8668  for (unsigned ArgNo = 0, E = CB.arg_size(); ArgNo < E; ++ArgNo) {
8669 
8670  // Skip non-pointer arguments.
8671  const Value *ArgOp = CB.getArgOperand(ArgNo);
8672  if (!ArgOp->getType()->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy())
8673  continue;
8674 
8675  // Skip readnone arguments.
8676  const IRPosition &ArgOpIRP = IRPosition::callsite_argument(CB, ArgNo);
8677  const auto &ArgOpMemLocationAA =
8678  A.getAAFor<AAMemoryBehavior>(*this, ArgOpIRP, DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
8679 
8680  if (ArgOpMemLocationAA.isAssumedReadNone())
8681  continue;
8682 
8683  // Categorize potentially accessed pointer arguments as if there was an
8684  // access instruction with them as pointer.
8685  categorizePtrValue(A, CB, *ArgOp, AccessedLocs, Changed);
8686  }
8687 }
8688 
8689 AAMemoryLocation::MemoryLocationsKind
8690 AAMemoryLocationImpl::categorizeAccessedLocations(Attributor &A, Instruction &I,
8691  bool &Changed) {
8692  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAMemoryLocation] Categorize accessed locations for "
8693  << I << "\n");
8694 
8695  AAMemoryLocation::StateType AccessedLocs;
8696  AccessedLocs.intersectAssumedBits(NO_LOCATIONS);
8697 
8698  if (auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(&I)) {
8699 
8700  // First check if we assume any memory is access is visible.
8701  const auto &CBMemLocationAA = A.getAAFor<AAMemoryLocation>(
8702  *this, IRPosition::callsite_function(*CB), DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
8703  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAMemoryLocation] Categorize call site: " << I
8704  << " [" << CBMemLocationAA << "]\n");
8705 
8706  if (CBMemLocationAA.isAssumedReadNone())
8707  return NO_LOCATIONS;
8708 
8709  if (CBMemLocationAA.isAssumedInaccessibleMemOnly()) {
8710  updateStateAndAccessesMap(AccessedLocs, NO_INACCESSIBLE_MEM, &I, nullptr,
8711  Changed, getAccessKindFromInst(&I));
8712  return AccessedLocs.getAssumed();
8713  }
8714 
8715  uint32_t CBAssumedNotAccessedLocs =
8716  CBMemLocationAA.getAssumedNotAccessedLocation();
8717 
8718  // Set the argmemonly and global bit as we handle them separately below.
8719  uint32_t CBAssumedNotAccessedLocsNoArgMem =
8720  CBAssumedNotAccessedLocs | NO_ARGUMENT_MEM | NO_GLOBAL_MEM;
8721 
8722  for (MemoryLocationsKind CurMLK = 1; CurMLK < NO_LOCATIONS; CurMLK *= 2) {
8723  if (CBAssumedNotAccessedLocsNoArgMem & CurMLK)
8724  continue;
8725  updateStateAndAccessesMap(AccessedLocs, CurMLK, &I, nullptr, Changed,
8726  getAccessKindFromInst(&I));
8727  }
8728 
8729  // Now handle global memory if it might be accessed. This is slightly tricky
8730  // as NO_GLOBAL_MEM has multiple bits set.
8731  bool HasGlobalAccesses = ((~CBAssumedNotAccessedLocs) & NO_GLOBAL_MEM);
8732  if (HasGlobalAccesses) {
8733  auto AccessPred = [&](const Instruction *, const Value *Ptr,
8734  AccessKind Kind, MemoryLocationsKind MLK) {
8735  updateStateAndAccessesMap(AccessedLocs, MLK, &I, Ptr, Changed,
8736  getAccessKindFromInst(&I));
8737  return true;
8738  };
8739  if (!CBMemLocationAA.checkForAllAccessesToMemoryKind(
8740  AccessPred, inverseLocation(NO_GLOBAL_MEM, false, false)))
8741  return AccessedLocs.getWorstState();
8742  }
8743 
8744  LLVM_DEBUG(
8745  dbgs() << "[AAMemoryLocation] Accessed state before argument handling: "
8746  << getMemoryLocationsAsStr(AccessedLocs.getAssumed()) << "\n");
8747 
8748  // Now handle argument memory if it might be accessed.
8749  bool HasArgAccesses = ((~CBAssumedNotAccessedLocs) & NO_ARGUMENT_MEM);
8750  if (HasArgAccesses)
8751  categorizeArgumentPointerLocations(A, *CB, AccessedLocs, Changed);
8752 
8753  LLVM_DEBUG(
8754  dbgs() << "[AAMemoryLocation] Accessed state after argument handling: "
8755  << getMemoryLocationsAsStr(AccessedLocs.getAssumed()) << "\n");
8756 
8757  return AccessedLocs.getAssumed();
8758  }
8759 
8760  if (const Value *Ptr = getPointerOperand(&I, /* AllowVolatile */ true)) {
8761  LLVM_DEBUG(
8762  dbgs() << "[AAMemoryLocation] Categorize memory access with pointer: "
8763  << I << " [" << *Ptr << "]\n");
8764  categorizePtrValue(A, I, *Ptr, AccessedLocs, Changed);
8765  return AccessedLocs.getAssumed();
8766  }
8767 
8768  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAMemoryLocation] Failed to categorize instruction: "
8769  << I << "\n");
8770  updateStateAndAccessesMap(AccessedLocs, NO_UNKOWN_MEM, &I, nullptr, Changed,
8771  getAccessKindFromInst(&I));
8772  return AccessedLocs.getAssumed();
8773 }
8774 
8775 /// An AA to represent the memory behavior function attributes.
8776 struct AAMemoryLocationFunction final : public AAMemoryLocationImpl {
8777  AAMemoryLocationFunction(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
8778  : AAMemoryLocationImpl(IRP, A) {}
8779 
8780  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(Attributor &A).
8781  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
8782 
8783  const auto &MemBehaviorAA =
8784  A.getAAFor<AAMemoryBehavior>(*this, getIRPosition(), DepClassTy::NONE);
8785  if (MemBehaviorAA.isAssumedReadNone()) {
8786  if (MemBehaviorAA.isKnownReadNone())
8787  return indicateOptimisticFixpoint();
8788  assert(isAssumedReadNone() &&
8789  "AAMemoryLocation was not read-none but AAMemoryBehavior was!");
8790  A.recordDependence(MemBehaviorAA, *this, DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
8791  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
8792  }
8793 
8794  // The current assumed state used to determine a change.
8795  auto AssumedState = getAssumed();
8796  bool Changed = false;
8797 
8798  auto CheckRWInst = [&](Instruction &I) {
8799  MemoryLocationsKind MLK = categorizeAccessedLocations(A, I, Changed);
8800  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAMemoryLocation] Accessed locations for " << I
8801  << ": " << getMemoryLocationsAsStr(MLK) << "\n");
8802  removeAssumedBits(inverseLocation(MLK, false, false));
8803  // Stop once only the valid bit set in the *not assumed location*, thus
8804  // once we don't actually exclude any memory locations in the state.
8805  return getAssumedNotAccessedLocation() != VALID_STATE;
8806  };
8807 
8808  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
8809  if (!A.checkForAllReadWriteInstructions(CheckRWInst, *this,
8810  UsedAssumedInformation))
8811  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
8812 
8813  Changed |= AssumedState != getAssumed();
8814  return Changed ? ChangeStatus::CHANGED : ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
8815  }
8816 
8817  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
8818  void trackStatistics() const override {
8819  if (isAssumedReadNone())
8820  STATS_DECLTRACK_FN_ATTR(readnone)
8821  else if (isAssumedArgMemOnly())
8822  STATS_DECLTRACK_FN_ATTR(argmemonly)
8823  else if (isAssumedInaccessibleMemOnly())
8824  STATS_DECLTRACK_FN_ATTR(inaccessiblememonly)
8825  else if (isAssumedInaccessibleOrArgMemOnly())
8826  STATS_DECLTRACK_FN_ATTR(inaccessiblememorargmemonly)
8827  }
8828 };
8829 
8830 /// AAMemoryLocation attribute for call sites.
8831 struct AAMemoryLocationCallSite final : AAMemoryLocationImpl {
8832  AAMemoryLocationCallSite(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
8833  : AAMemoryLocationImpl(IRP, A) {}
8834 
8835  /// See AbstractAttribute::initialize(...).
8836  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
8837  AAMemoryLocationImpl::initialize(A);
8838  Function *F = getAssociatedFunction();
8839  if (!F || F->isDeclaration())
8840  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
8841  }
8842 
8843  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
8844  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
8845  // TODO: Once we have call site specific value information we can provide
8846  // call site specific liveness liveness information and then it makes
8847  // sense to specialize attributes for call sites arguments instead of
8848  // redirecting requests to the callee argument.
8849  Function *F = getAssociatedFunction();
8850  const IRPosition &FnPos = IRPosition::function(*F);
8851  auto &FnAA =
8852  A.getAAFor<AAMemoryLocation>(*this, FnPos, DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
8853  bool Changed = false;
8854  auto AccessPred = [&](const Instruction *I, const Value *Ptr,
8855  AccessKind Kind, MemoryLocationsKind MLK) {
8856  updateStateAndAccessesMap(getState(), MLK, I, Ptr, Changed,
8857  getAccessKindFromInst(I));
8858  return true;
8859  };
8860  if (!FnAA.checkForAllAccessesToMemoryKind(AccessPred, ALL_LOCATIONS))
8861  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
8862  return Changed ? ChangeStatus::CHANGED : ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
8863  }
8864 
8865  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
8866  void trackStatistics() const override {
8867  if (isAssumedReadNone())
8868  STATS_DECLTRACK_CS_ATTR(readnone)
8869  }
8870 };
8871 } // namespace

8873 /// ------------------ Value Constant Range Attribute -------------------------
8874 
8875 namespace {
8876 struct AAValueConstantRangeImpl : AAValueConstantRange {
8877  using StateType = IntegerRangeState;
8878  AAValueConstantRangeImpl(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
8879  : AAValueConstantRange(IRP, A) {}
8880 
8881  /// See AbstractAttribute::initialize(..).
8882  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
8883  if (A.hasSimplificationCallback(getIRPosition())) {
8884  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
8885  return;
8886  }
8887 
8888  // Intersect a range given by SCEV.
8889  intersectKnown(getConstantRangeFromSCEV(A, getCtxI()));
8890 
8891  // Intersect a range given by LVI.
8892  intersectKnown(getConstantRangeFromLVI(A, getCtxI()));
8893  }
8894 
8895  /// See AbstractAttribute::getAsStr().
8896  const std::string getAsStr() const override {
8897  std::string Str;
8898  llvm::raw_string_ostream OS(Str);
8899  OS << "range(" << getBitWidth() << ")<";
8900  getKnown().print(OS);
8901  OS << " / ";
8902  getAssumed().print(OS);
8903  OS << ">";
8904  return OS.str();
8905  }
8906 
8907  /// Helper function to get a SCEV expr for the associated value at program
8908  /// point \p I.
8909  const SCEV *getSCEV(Attributor &A, const Instruction *I = nullptr) const {
8910  if (!getAnchorScope())
8911  return nullptr;
8912 
8913  ScalarEvolution *SE =
8914  A.getInfoCache().getAnalysisResultForFunction<ScalarEvolutionAnalysis>(
8915  *getAnchorScope());
8916 
8917  LoopInfo *LI = A.getInfoCache().getAnalysisResultForFunction<LoopAnalysis>(
8918  *getAnchorScope());
8919 
8920  if (!SE || !LI)
8921  return nullptr;
8922 
8923  const SCEV *S = SE->getSCEV(&getAssociatedValue());
8924  if (!I)
8925  return S;
8926 
8927  return SE->getSCEVAtScope(S, LI->getLoopFor(I->getParent()));
8928  }
8929 
8930  /// Helper function to get a range from SCEV for the associated value at
8931  /// program point \p I.
8932  ConstantRange getConstantRangeFromSCEV(Attributor &A,
8933  const Instruction *I = nullptr) const {
8934  if (!getAnchorScope())
8935  return getWorstState(getBitWidth());
8936 
8937  ScalarEvolution *SE =
8938  A.getInfoCache().getAnalysisResultForFunction<ScalarEvolutionAnalysis>(
8939  *getAnchorScope());
8940 
8941  const SCEV *S = getSCEV(A, I);
8942  if (!SE || !S)
8943  return getWorstState(getBitWidth());
8944 
8945  return SE->getUnsignedRange(S);
8946  }
8947 
8948  /// Helper function to get a range from LVI for the associated value at
8949  /// program point \p I.
8950  ConstantRange
8951  getConstantRangeFromLVI(Attributor &A,
8952  const Instruction *CtxI = nullptr) const {
8953  if (!getAnchorScope())
8954  return getWorstState(getBitWidth());
8955 
8956  LazyValueInfo *LVI =
8957  A.getInfoCache().getAnalysisResultForFunction<LazyValueAnalysis>(
8958  *getAnchorScope());
8959 
8960  if (!LVI || !CtxI)
8961  return getWorstState(getBitWidth());
8962  return LVI->getConstantRange(&getAssociatedValue(),
8963  const_cast<Instruction *>(CtxI));
8964  }
8965 
8966  /// Return true if \p CtxI is valid for querying outside analyses.
8967  /// This basically makes sure we do not ask intra-procedural analysis
8968  /// about a context in the wrong function or a context that violates
8969  /// dominance assumptions they might have. The \p AllowAACtxI flag indicates
8970  /// if the original context of this AA is OK or should be considered invalid.
8971  bool isValidCtxInstructionForOutsideAnalysis(Attributor &A,
8972  const Instruction *CtxI,
8973  bool AllowAACtxI) const {
8974  if (!CtxI || (!AllowAACtxI && CtxI == getCtxI()))
8975  return false;
8976 
8977  // Our context might be in a different function, neither intra-procedural
8978  // analysis (ScalarEvolution nor LazyValueInfo) can handle that.
8979  if (!AA::isValidInScope(getAssociatedValue(), CtxI->getFunction()))
8980  return false;
8981 
8982  // If the context is not dominated by the value there are paths to the
8983  // context that do not define the value. This cannot be handled by
8984  // LazyValueInfo so we need to bail.
8985  if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(&getAssociatedValue())) {
8986  InformationCache &InfoCache = A.getInfoCache();
8987  const DominatorTree *DT =
8988  InfoCache.getAnalysisResultForFunction<DominatorTreeAnalysis>(
8989  *I->getFunction());
8990  return DT && DT->dominates(I, CtxI);
8991  }
8992 
8993  return true;
8994  }
8995 
8996  /// See AAValueConstantRange::getKnownConstantRange(..).
8997  ConstantRange
8998  getKnownConstantRange(Attributor &A,
8999  const Instruction *CtxI = nullptr) const override {
9000  if (!isValidCtxInstructionForOutsideAnalysis(A, CtxI,
9001  /* AllowAACtxI */ false))
9002  return getKnown();
9003 
9004  ConstantRange LVIR = getConstantRangeFromLVI(A, CtxI);
9005  ConstantRange SCEVR = getConstantRangeFromSCEV(A, CtxI);
9006  return getKnown().intersectWith(SCEVR).intersectWith(LVIR);
9007  }
9008 
9009  /// See AAValueConstantRange::getAssumedConstantRange(..).
9010  ConstantRange
9011  getAssumedConstantRange(Attributor &A,
9012  const Instruction *CtxI = nullptr) const override {
9013  // TODO: Make SCEV use Attributor assumption.
9014  // We may be able to bound a variable range via assumptions in
9015  // Attributor. ex.) If x is assumed to be in [1, 3] and y is known to
9016  // evolve to x^2 + x, then we can say that y is in [2, 12].
9017  if (!isValidCtxInstructionForOutsideAnalysis(A, CtxI,
9018  /* AllowAACtxI */ false))
9019  return getAssumed();
9020 
9021  ConstantRange LVIR = getConstantRangeFromLVI(A, CtxI);
9022  ConstantRange SCEVR = getConstantRangeFromSCEV(A, CtxI);
9023  return getAssumed().intersectWith(SCEVR).intersectWith(LVIR);
9024  }
9025 
9026  /// Helper function to create MDNode for range metadata.
9027  static MDNode *
9028  getMDNodeForConstantRange(Type *Ty, LLVMContext &Ctx,
9029  const ConstantRange &AssumedConstantRange) {
9030  Metadata *LowAndHigh[] = {ConstantAsMetadata::get(ConstantInt::get(
9031  Ty, AssumedConstantRange.getLower())),
9032  ConstantAsMetadata::get(ConstantInt::get(
9033  Ty, AssumedConstantRange.getUpper()))};
9034  return MDNode::get(Ctx, LowAndHigh);
9035  }
9036 
9037  /// Return true if \p Assumed is included in \p KnownRanges.
9038  static bool isBetterRange(const ConstantRange &Assumed, MDNode *KnownRanges) {
9039 
9040  if (Assumed.isFullSet())
9041  return false;
9042 
9043  if (!KnownRanges)
9044  return true;
9045 
9046  // If multiple ranges are annotated in IR, we give up to annotate assumed
9047  // range for now.
9048 
9049  // TODO: If there exists a known range which containts assumed range, we
9050  // can say assumed range is better.
9051  if (KnownRanges->getNumOperands() > 2)
9052  return false;
9053 
9054  ConstantInt *Lower =
9055  mdconst::extract<ConstantInt>(KnownRanges->getOperand(0));
9056  ConstantInt *Upper =
9057  mdconst::extract<ConstantInt>(KnownRanges->getOperand(1));
9058 
9059  ConstantRange Known(Lower->getValue(), Upper->getValue());
9060  return Known.contains(Assumed) && Known != Assumed;
9061  }
9062 
9063  /// Helper function to set range metadata.
9064  static bool
9065  setRangeMetadataIfisBetterRange(Instruction *I,
9066  const ConstantRange &AssumedConstantRange) {
9067  auto *OldRangeMD = I->getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_range);
9068  if (isBetterRange(AssumedConstantRange, OldRangeMD)) {
9069  if (!AssumedConstantRange.isEmptySet()) {
9070  I->setMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_range,
9071  getMDNodeForConstantRange(I->getType(), I->getContext(),
9072  AssumedConstantRange));
9073  return true;
9074  }
9075  }
9076  return false;
9077  }
9078 
9079  /// See AbstractAttribute::manifest()
9080  ChangeStatus manifest(Attributor &A) override {
9081  ChangeStatus Changed = ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
9082  ConstantRange AssumedConstantRange = getAssumedConstantRange(A);
9083  assert(!AssumedConstantRange.isFullSet() && "Invalid state");
9084 
9085  auto &V = getAssociatedValue();
9086  if (!AssumedConstantRange.isEmptySet() &&
9087  !AssumedConstantRange.isSingleElement()) {
9088  if (Instruction *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(&V)) {
9089  assert(I == getCtxI() && "Should not annotate an instruction which is "
9090  "not the context instruction");
9091  if (isa<CallInst>(I) || isa<LoadInst>(I))
9092  if (setRangeMetadataIfisBetterRange(I, AssumedConstantRange))
9093  Changed = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
9094  }
9095  }
9096 
9097  return Changed;
9098  }
9099 };

9116  Base::initialize(A);

9133  AAValueConstantRangeImpl,

9147 
9148 struct AAValueConstantRangeFloating : AAValueConstantRangeImpl {
9149  AAValueConstantRangeFloating(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
9150  : AAValueConstantRangeImpl(IRP, A) {}
9151 
9152  /// See AbstractAttribute::initialize(...).
9153  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
9154  AAValueConstantRangeImpl::initialize(A);
9155  if (isAtFixpoint())
9156  return;
9157 
9158  Value &V = getAssociatedValue();
9159 
9160  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(&V)) {
9161  unionAssumed(ConstantRange(C->getValue()));
9162  indicateOptimisticFixpoint();
9163  return;
9164  }
9165 
9166  if (isa<UndefValue>(&V)) {
9167  // Collapse the undef state to 0.
9168  unionAssumed(ConstantRange(APInt(getBitWidth(), 0)));
9169  indicateOptimisticFixpoint();
9170  return;
9171  }
9172 
9173  if (isa<CallBase>(&V))
9174  return;
9175 
9176  if (isa<BinaryOperator>(&V) || isa<CmpInst>(&V) || isa<CastInst>(&V))
9177  return;
9178 
9179  // If it is a load instruction with range metadata, use it.
9180  if (LoadInst *LI = dyn_cast<LoadInst>(&V))
9181  if (auto *RangeMD = LI->getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_range)) {
9182  intersectKnown(getConstantRangeFromMetadata(*RangeMD));
9183  return;
9184  }
9185 
9186  // We can work with PHI and select instruction as we traverse their operands
9187  // during update.
9188  if (isa<SelectInst>(V) || isa<PHINode>(V))
9189  return;
9190 
9191  // Otherwise we give up.
9192  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
9193 
9194  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAValueConstantRange] We give up: "
9195  << getAssociatedValue() << "\n");
9196  }
9197 
9198  bool calculateBinaryOperator(
9199  Attributor &A, BinaryOperator *BinOp, IntegerRangeState &T,
9200  const Instruction *CtxI,
9201  SmallVectorImpl<const AAValueConstantRange *> &QuerriedAAs) {
9202  Value *LHS = BinOp->getOperand(0);
9203  Value *RHS = BinOp->getOperand(1);
9204 
9205  // Simplify the operands first.
9206  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
9207  const auto &SimplifiedLHS = A.getAssumedSimplified(
9208  IRPosition::value(*LHS, getCallBaseContext()), *this,
9209  UsedAssumedInformation, AA::Interprocedural);
9210  if (!SimplifiedLHS.has_value())
9211  return true;
9212  if (!*SimplifiedLHS)
9213  return false;
9214  LHS = *SimplifiedLHS;
9215 
9216  const auto &SimplifiedRHS = A.getAssumedSimplified(
9217  IRPosition::value(*RHS, getCallBaseContext()), *this,
9218  UsedAssumedInformation, AA::Interprocedural);
9219  if (!SimplifiedRHS.has_value())
9220  return true;
9221  if (!*SimplifiedRHS)
9222  return false;
9223  RHS = *SimplifiedRHS;
9224 
9225  // TODO: Allow non integers as well.
9226  if (!LHS->getType()->isIntegerTy() || !RHS->getType()->isIntegerTy())
9227  return false;
9228 
9229  auto &LHSAA = A.getAAFor<AAValueConstantRange>(
9230  *this, IRPosition::value(*LHS, getCallBaseContext()),
9231  DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
9232  QuerriedAAs.push_back(&LHSAA);
9233  auto LHSAARange = LHSAA.getAssumedConstantRange(A, CtxI);
9234 
9235  auto &RHSAA = A.getAAFor<AAValueConstantRange>(
9236  *this, IRPosition::value(*RHS, getCallBaseContext()),
9237  DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
9238  QuerriedAAs.push_back(&RHSAA);
9239  auto RHSAARange = RHSAA.getAssumedConstantRange(A, CtxI);
9240 
9241  auto AssumedRange = LHSAARange.binaryOp(BinOp->getOpcode(), RHSAARange);
9242 
9243  T.unionAssumed(AssumedRange);
9244 
9245  // TODO: Track a known state too.
9246 
9247  return T.isValidState();
9248  }
9249 
9250  bool calculateCastInst(
9251  Attributor &A, CastInst *CastI, IntegerRangeState &T,
9252  const Instruction *CtxI,
9253  SmallVectorImpl<const AAValueConstantRange *> &QuerriedAAs) {
9254  assert(CastI->getNumOperands() == 1 && "Expected cast to be unary!");
9255  // TODO: Allow non integers as well.
9256  Value *OpV = CastI->getOperand(0);
9257 
9258  // Simplify the operand first.
9259  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
9260  const auto &SimplifiedOpV = A.getAssumedSimplified(
9261  IRPosition::value(*OpV, getCallBaseContext()), *this,
9262  UsedAssumedInformation, AA::Interprocedural);
9263  if (!SimplifiedOpV.has_value())
9264  return true;
9265  if (!*SimplifiedOpV)
9266  return false;
9267  OpV = *SimplifiedOpV;
9268 
9269  if (!OpV->getType()->isIntegerTy())
9270  return false;
9271 
9272  auto &OpAA = A.getAAFor<AAValueConstantRange>(
9273  *this, IRPosition::value(*OpV, getCallBaseContext()),
9274  DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
9275  QuerriedAAs.push_back(&OpAA);
9276  T.unionAssumed(
9277  OpAA.getAssumed().castOp(CastI->getOpcode(), getState().getBitWidth()));
9278  return T.isValidState();
9279  }
9280 
9281  bool
9282  calculateCmpInst(Attributor &A, CmpInst *CmpI, IntegerRangeState &T,
9283  const Instruction *CtxI,
9284  SmallVectorImpl<const AAValueConstantRange *> &QuerriedAAs) {
9285  Value *LHS = CmpI->getOperand(0);
9286  Value *RHS = CmpI->getOperand(1);
9287 
9288  // Simplify the operands first.
9289  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
9290  const auto &SimplifiedLHS = A.getAssumedSimplified(
9291  IRPosition::value(*LHS, getCallBaseContext()), *this,
9292  UsedAssumedInformation, AA::Interprocedural);
9293  if (!SimplifiedLHS.has_value())
9294  return true;
9295  if (!*SimplifiedLHS)
9296  return false;
9297  LHS = *SimplifiedLHS;
9298 
9299  const auto &SimplifiedRHS = A.getAssumedSimplified(
9300  IRPosition::value(*RHS, getCallBaseContext()), *this,
9301  UsedAssumedInformation, AA::Interprocedural);
9302  if (!SimplifiedRHS.has_value())
9303  return true;
9304  if (!*SimplifiedRHS)
9305  return false;
9306  RHS = *SimplifiedRHS;
9307 
9308  // TODO: Allow non integers as well.
9309  if (!LHS->getType()->isIntegerTy() || !RHS->getType()->isIntegerTy())
9310  return false;
9311 
9312  auto &LHSAA = A.getAAFor<AAValueConstantRange>(
9313  *this, IRPosition::value(*LHS, getCallBaseContext()),
9314  DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
9315  QuerriedAAs.push_back(&LHSAA);
9316  auto &RHSAA = A.getAAFor<AAValueConstantRange>(
9317  *this, IRPosition::value(*RHS, getCallBaseContext()),
9318  DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
9319  QuerriedAAs.push_back(&RHSAA);
9320  auto LHSAARange = LHSAA.getAssumedConstantRange(A, CtxI);
9321  auto RHSAARange = RHSAA.getAssumedConstantRange(A, CtxI);
9322 
9323  // If one of them is empty set, we can't decide.
9324  if (LHSAARange.isEmptySet() || RHSAARange.isEmptySet())
9325  return true;
9326 
9327  bool MustTrue = false, MustFalse = false;
9328 
9329  auto AllowedRegion =
9330  ConstantRange::makeAllowedICmpRegion(CmpI->getPredicate(), RHSAARange);
9331 
9332  if (AllowedRegion.intersectWith(LHSAARange).isEmptySet())
9333  MustFalse = true;
9334 
9335  if (LHSAARange.icmp(CmpI->getPredicate(), RHSAARange))
9336  MustTrue = true;
9337 
9338  assert((!MustTrue || !MustFalse) &&
9339  "Either MustTrue or MustFalse should be false!");
9340 
9341  if (MustTrue)
9342  T.unionAssumed(ConstantRange(APInt(/* numBits */ 1, /* val */ 1)));
9343  else if (MustFalse)
9344  T.unionAssumed(ConstantRange(APInt(/* numBits */ 1, /* val */ 0)));
9345  else
9346  T.unionAssumed(ConstantRange(/* BitWidth */ 1, /* isFullSet */ true));
9347 
9348  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAValueConstantRange] " << *CmpI << " " << LHSAA
9349  << " " << RHSAA << "\n");
9350 
9351  // TODO: Track a known state too.
9352  return T.isValidState();
9353  }
9354 
9355  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
9356  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
9357 
9358  IntegerRangeState T(getBitWidth());
9359  auto VisitValueCB = [&](Value &V, const Instruction *CtxI) -> bool {
9360  Instruction *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(&V);
9361  if (!I || isa<CallBase>(I)) {
9362 
9363  // Simplify the operand first.
9364  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
9365  const auto &SimplifiedOpV = A.getAssumedSimplified(
9366  IRPosition::value(V, getCallBaseContext()), *this,
9367  UsedAssumedInformation, AA::Interprocedural);
9368  if (!SimplifiedOpV.has_value())
9369  return true;
9370  if (!*SimplifiedOpV)
9371  return false;
9372  Value *VPtr = *SimplifiedOpV;
9373 
9374  // If the value is not instruction, we query AA to Attributor.
9375  const auto &AA = A.getAAFor<AAValueConstantRange>(
9376  *this, IRPosition::value(*VPtr, getCallBaseContext()),
9377  DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
9378 
9379  // Clamp operator is not used to utilize a program point CtxI.
9380  T.unionAssumed(AA.getAssumedConstantRange(A, CtxI));
9381 
9382  return T.isValidState();
9383  }
9384 
9385  SmallVector<const AAValueConstantRange *, 4> QuerriedAAs;
9386  if (auto *BinOp = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(I)) {
9387  if (!calculateBinaryOperator(A, BinOp, T, CtxI, QuerriedAAs))
9388  return false;
9389  } else if (auto *CmpI = dyn_cast<CmpInst>(I)) {
9390  if (!calculateCmpInst(A, CmpI, T, CtxI, QuerriedAAs))
9391  return false;
9392  } else if (auto *CastI = dyn_cast<CastInst>(I)) {
9393  if (!calculateCastInst(A, CastI, T, CtxI, QuerriedAAs))
9394  return false;
9395  } else {
9396  // Give up with other instructions.
9397  // TODO: Add other instructions
9398 
9399  T.indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
9400  return false;
9401  }
9402 
9403  // Catch circular reasoning in a pessimistic way for now.
9404  // TODO: Check how the range evolves and if we stripped anything, see also
9405  // AADereferenceable or AAAlign for similar situations.
9406  for (const AAValueConstantRange *QueriedAA : QuerriedAAs) {
9407  if (QueriedAA != this)
9408  continue;
9409  // If we are in a stady state we do not need to worry.
9410  if (T.getAssumed() == getState().getAssumed())
9411  continue;
9412  T.indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
9413  }
9414 
9415  return T.isValidState();
9416  };
9417 
9418  if (!VisitValueCB(getAssociatedValue(), getCtxI()))
9419  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
9420 
9421  // Ensure that long def-use chains can't cause circular reasoning either by
9422  // introducing a cutoff below.
9423  if (clampStateAndIndicateChange(getState(), T) == ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED)
9424  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
9425  if (++NumChanges > MaxNumChanges) {
9426  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAValueConstantRange] performed " << NumChanges
9427  << " but only " << MaxNumChanges
9428  << " are allowed to avoid cyclic reasoning.");
9429  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
9430  }
9431  return ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
9432  }
9433 
9434  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
9435  void trackStatistics() const override {
9436  STATS_DECLTRACK_FLOATING_ATTR(value_range)
9437  }
9438 
9439  /// Tracker to bail after too many widening steps of the constant range.
9440  int NumChanges = 0;
9441 
9442  /// Upper bound for the number of allowed changes (=widening steps) for the
9443  /// constant range before we give up.
9444  static constexpr int MaxNumChanges = 5;
9445 };
9446

9449  : AAValueConstantRangeImpl(IRP, A) {}
9450 
9451  /// See AbstractAttribute::initialize(...).
9452  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
9453  llvm_unreachable("AAValueConstantRange(Function|CallSite)::updateImpl will "
9454  "not be called");
9455  }
9456

9458  void trackStatistics() const override { STATS_DECLTRACK_FN_ATTR(value_range) }

9515 namespace {
9516 struct AAPotentialConstantValuesImpl : AAPotentialConstantValues {
9517  using StateType = PotentialConstantIntValuesState;
9518 
9519  AAPotentialConstantValuesImpl(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
9520  : AAPotentialConstantValues(IRP, A) {}
9521 
9522  /// See AbstractAttribute::initialize(..).
9523  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
9524  if (A.hasSimplificationCallback(getIRPosition()))
9525  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
9526  else
9527  AAPotentialConstantValues::initialize(A);
9528  }
9529 
9530  bool fillSetWithConstantValues(Attributor &A, const IRPosition &IRP, SetTy &S,
9531  bool &ContainsUndef, bool ForSelf) {
9532  SmallVector<AA::ValueAndContext> Values;
9533  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
9534  if (!A.getAssumedSimplifiedValues(IRP, *this, Values, AA::Interprocedural,
9535  UsedAssumedInformation)) {
9536  // Avoid recursion when the caller is computing constant values for this
9537  // IRP itself.
9538  if (ForSelf)
9539  return false;
9540  if (!IRP.getAssociatedType()->isIntegerTy())
9541  return false;
9542  auto &PotentialValuesAA = A.getAAFor<AAPotentialConstantValues>(
9543  *this, IRP, DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
9544  if (!PotentialValuesAA.getState().isValidState())
9545  return false;
9546  ContainsUndef = PotentialValuesAA.getState().undefIsContained();
9547  S = PotentialValuesAA.getState().getAssumedSet();
9548  return true;
9549  }
9550 
9551  // Copy all the constant values, except UndefValue. ContainsUndef is true
9552  // iff Values contains only UndefValue instances. If there are other known
9553  // constants, then UndefValue is dropped.
9554  ContainsUndef = false;
9555  for (auto &It : Values) {
9556  if (isa<UndefValue>(It.getValue())) {
9557  ContainsUndef = true;
9558  continue;
9559  }
9560  auto *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(It.getValue());
9561  if (!CI)
9562  return false;
9563  S.insert(CI->getValue());
9564  }
9565  ContainsUndef &= S.empty();
9566 
9567  return true;
9568  }
9569 
9570  /// See AbstractAttribute::getAsStr().
9571  const std::string getAsStr() const override {
9572  std::string Str;
9573  llvm::raw_string_ostream OS(Str);
9574  OS << getState();
9575  return OS.str();
9576  }
9577 
9578  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
9579  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
9580  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
9581  }
9582 };
9583

9597  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
9598  } else {
9599  Base::initialize(A);
9600  }
9601  }

9623 struct AAPotentialConstantValuesFloating : AAPotentialConstantValuesImpl {
9624  AAPotentialConstantValuesFloating(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
9625  : AAPotentialConstantValuesImpl(IRP, A) {}
9626 
9627  /// See AbstractAttribute::initialize(..).
9628  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
9629  AAPotentialConstantValuesImpl::initialize(A);
9630  if (isAtFixpoint())
9631  return;
9632 
9633  Value &V = getAssociatedValue();
9634 
9635  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(&V)) {
9636  unionAssumed(C->getValue());
9637  indicateOptimisticFixpoint();
9638  return;
9639  }
9640 
9641  if (isa<UndefValue>(&V)) {
9642  unionAssumedWithUndef();
9643  indicateOptimisticFixpoint();
9644  return;
9645  }
9646 
9647  if (isa<BinaryOperator>(&V) || isa<ICmpInst>(&V) || isa<CastInst>(&V))
9648  return;
9649 
9650  if (isa<SelectInst>(V) || isa<PHINode>(V) || isa<LoadInst>(V))
9651  return;
9652 
9653  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
9654 
9655  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAPotentialConstantValues] We give up: "
9656  << getAssociatedValue() << "\n");
9657  }
9658 
9659  static bool calculateICmpInst(const ICmpInst *ICI, const APInt &LHS,
9660  const APInt &RHS) {
9661  return ICmpInst::compare(LHS, RHS, ICI->getPredicate());
9662  }
9663 
9664  static APInt calculateCastInst(const CastInst *CI, const APInt &Src,
9665  uint32_t ResultBitWidth) {
9666  Instruction::CastOps CastOp = CI->getOpcode();
9667  switch (CastOp) {
9668  default:
9669  llvm_unreachable("unsupported or not integer cast");
9670  case Instruction::Trunc:
9671  return Src.trunc(ResultBitWidth);
9672  case Instruction::SExt:
9673  return Src.sext(ResultBitWidth);
9674  case Instruction::ZExt:
9675  return Src.zext(ResultBitWidth);
9676  case Instruction::BitCast:
9677  return Src;
9678  }
9679  }
9680 
9681  static APInt calculateBinaryOperator(const BinaryOperator *BinOp,
9682  const APInt &LHS, const APInt &RHS,
9683  bool &SkipOperation, bool &Unsupported) {
9684  Instruction::BinaryOps BinOpcode = BinOp->getOpcode();
9685  // Unsupported is set to true when the binary operator is not supported.
9686  // SkipOperation is set to true when UB occur with the given operand pair
9687  // (LHS, RHS).
9688  // TODO: we should look at nsw and nuw keywords to handle operations
9689  // that create poison or undef value.
9690  switch (BinOpcode) {
9691  default:
9692  Unsupported = true;
9693  return LHS;
9694  case Instruction::Add:
9695  return LHS + RHS;
9696  case Instruction::Sub:
9697  return LHS - RHS;
9698  case Instruction::Mul:
9699  return LHS * RHS;
9700  case Instruction::UDiv:
9701  if (RHS.isZero()) {
9702  SkipOperation = true;
9703  return LHS;
9704  }
9705  return LHS.udiv(RHS);
9706  case Instruction::SDiv:
9707  if (RHS.isZero()) {
9708  SkipOperation = true;
9709  return LHS;
9710  }
9711  return LHS.sdiv(RHS);
9712  case Instruction::URem:
9713  if (RHS.isZero()) {
9714  SkipOperation = true;
9715  return LHS;
9716  }
9717  return LHS.urem(RHS);
9718  case Instruction::SRem:
9719  if (RHS.isZero()) {
9720  SkipOperation = true;
9721  return LHS;
9722  }
9723  return LHS.srem(RHS);
9724  case Instruction::Shl:
9725  return LHS.shl(RHS);
9726  case Instruction::LShr:
9727  return LHS.lshr(RHS);
9728  case Instruction::AShr:
9729  return LHS.ashr(RHS);
9730  case Instruction::And:
9731  return LHS & RHS;
9732  case Instruction::Or:
9733  return LHS | RHS;
9734  case Instruction::Xor:
9735  return LHS ^ RHS;
9736  }
9737  }
9738 
9739  bool calculateBinaryOperatorAndTakeUnion(const BinaryOperator *BinOp,
9740  const APInt &LHS, const APInt &RHS) {
9741  bool SkipOperation = false;
9742  bool Unsupported = false;
9743  APInt Result =
9744  calculateBinaryOperator(BinOp, LHS, RHS, SkipOperation, Unsupported);
9745  if (Unsupported)
9746  return false;
9747  // If SkipOperation is true, we can ignore this operand pair (L, R).
9748  if (!SkipOperation)
9749  unionAssumed(Result);
9750  return isValidState();
9751  }
9752 
9753  ChangeStatus updateWithICmpInst(Attributor &A, ICmpInst *ICI) {
9754  auto AssumedBefore = getAssumed();
9755  Value *LHS = ICI->getOperand(0);
9756  Value *RHS = ICI->getOperand(1);
9757 
9758  bool LHSContainsUndef = false, RHSContainsUndef = false;
9759  SetTy LHSAAPVS, RHSAAPVS;
9760  if (!fillSetWithConstantValues(A, IRPosition::value(*LHS), LHSAAPVS,
9761  LHSContainsUndef, /* ForSelf */ false) ||
9762  !fillSetWithConstantValues(A, IRPosition::value(*RHS), RHSAAPVS,
9763  RHSContainsUndef, /* ForSelf */ false))
9764  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
9765 
9766  // TODO: make use of undef flag to limit potential values aggressively.
9767  bool MaybeTrue = false, MaybeFalse = false;
9768  const APInt Zero(RHS->getType()->getIntegerBitWidth(), 0);
9769  if (LHSContainsUndef && RHSContainsUndef) {
9770  // The result of any comparison between undefs can be soundly replaced
9771  // with undef.
9772  unionAssumedWithUndef();
9773  } else if (LHSContainsUndef) {
9774  for (const APInt &R : RHSAAPVS) {
9775  bool CmpResult = calculateICmpInst(ICI, Zero, R);
9776  MaybeTrue |= CmpResult;
9777  MaybeFalse |= !CmpResult;
9778  if (MaybeTrue & MaybeFalse)
9779  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
9780  }
9781  } else if (RHSContainsUndef) {
9782  for (const APInt &L : LHSAAPVS) {
9783  bool CmpResult = calculateICmpInst(ICI, L, Zero);
9784  MaybeTrue |= CmpResult;
9785  MaybeFalse |= !CmpResult;
9786  if (MaybeTrue & MaybeFalse)
9787  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
9788  }
9789  } else {
9790  for (const APInt &L : LHSAAPVS) {
9791  for (const APInt &R : RHSAAPVS) {
9792  bool CmpResult = calculateICmpInst(ICI, L, R);
9793  MaybeTrue |= CmpResult;
9794  MaybeFalse |= !CmpResult;
9795  if (MaybeTrue & MaybeFalse)
9796  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
9797  }
9798  }
9799  }
9800  if (MaybeTrue)
9801  unionAssumed(APInt(/* numBits */ 1, /* val */ 1));
9802  if (MaybeFalse)
9803  unionAssumed(APInt(/* numBits */ 1, /* val */ 0));
9804  return AssumedBefore == getAssumed() ? ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED
9805  : ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
9806  }
9807 
9808  ChangeStatus updateWithSelectInst(Attributor &A, SelectInst *SI) {
9809  auto AssumedBefore = getAssumed();
9810  Value *LHS = SI->getTrueValue();
9811  Value *RHS = SI->getFalseValue();
9812 
9813  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
9814  std::optional<Constant *> C = A.getAssumedConstant(
9815  *SI->getCondition(), *this, UsedAssumedInformation);
9816 
9817  // Check if we only need one operand.
9818  bool OnlyLeft = false, OnlyRight = false;
9819  if (C && *C && (*C)->isOneValue())
9820  OnlyLeft = true;
9821  else if (C && *C && (*C)->isZeroValue())
9822  OnlyRight = true;
9823 
9824  bool LHSContainsUndef = false, RHSContainsUndef = false;
9825  SetTy LHSAAPVS, RHSAAPVS;
9826  if (!OnlyRight &&
9827  !fillSetWithConstantValues(A, IRPosition::value(*LHS), LHSAAPVS,
9828  LHSContainsUndef, /* ForSelf */ false))
9829  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
9830 
9831  if (!OnlyLeft &&
9832  !fillSetWithConstantValues(A, IRPosition::value(*RHS), RHSAAPVS,
9833  RHSContainsUndef, /* ForSelf */ false))
9834  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
9835 
9836  if (OnlyLeft || OnlyRight) {
9837  // select (true/false), lhs, rhs
9838  auto *OpAA = OnlyLeft ? &LHSAAPVS : &RHSAAPVS;
9839  auto Undef = OnlyLeft ? LHSContainsUndef : RHSContainsUndef;
9840 
9841  if (Undef)
9842  unionAssumedWithUndef();
9843  else {
9844  for (const auto &It : *OpAA)
9845  unionAssumed(It);
9846  }
9847 
9848  } else if (LHSContainsUndef && RHSContainsUndef) {
9849  // select i1 *, undef , undef => undef
9850  unionAssumedWithUndef();
9851  } else {
9852  for (const auto &It : LHSAAPVS)
9853  unionAssumed(It);
9854  for (const auto &It : RHSAAPVS)
9855  unionAssumed(It);
9856  }
9857  return AssumedBefore == getAssumed() ? ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED
9858  : ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
9859  }
9860 
9861  ChangeStatus updateWithCastInst(Attributor &A, CastInst *CI) {
9862  auto AssumedBefore = getAssumed();
9863  if (!CI->isIntegerCast())
9864  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
9865  assert(CI->getNumOperands() == 1 && "Expected cast to be unary!");
9866  uint32_t ResultBitWidth = CI->getDestTy()->getIntegerBitWidth();
9867  Value *Src = CI->getOperand(0);
9868 
9869  bool SrcContainsUndef = false;
9870  SetTy SrcPVS;
9871  if (!fillSetWithConstantValues(A, IRPosition::value(*Src), SrcPVS,
9872  SrcContainsUndef, /* ForSelf */ false))
9873  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
9874 
9875  if (SrcContainsUndef)
9876  unionAssumedWithUndef();
9877  else {
9878  for (const APInt &S : SrcPVS) {
9879  APInt T = calculateCastInst(CI, S, ResultBitWidth);
9880  unionAssumed(T);
9881  }
9882  }
9883  return AssumedBefore == getAssumed() ? ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED
9884  : ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
9885  }
9886 
9887  ChangeStatus updateWithBinaryOperator(Attributor &A, BinaryOperator *BinOp) {
9888  auto AssumedBefore = getAssumed();
9889  Value *LHS = BinOp->getOperand(0);
9890  Value *RHS = BinOp->getOperand(1);
9891 
9892  bool LHSContainsUndef = false, RHSContainsUndef = false;
9893  SetTy LHSAAPVS, RHSAAPVS;
9894  if (!fillSetWithConstantValues(A, IRPosition::value(*LHS), LHSAAPVS,
9895  LHSContainsUndef, /* ForSelf */ false) ||
9896  !fillSetWithConstantValues(A, IRPosition::value(*RHS), RHSAAPVS,
9897  RHSContainsUndef, /* ForSelf */ false))
9898  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
9899 
9900  const APInt Zero = APInt(LHS->getType()->getIntegerBitWidth(), 0);
9901 
9902  // TODO: make use of undef flag to limit potential values aggressively.
9903  if (LHSContainsUndef && RHSContainsUndef) {
9904  if (!calculateBinaryOperatorAndTakeUnion(BinOp, Zero, Zero))
9905  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
9906  } else if (LHSContainsUndef) {
9907  for (const APInt &R : RHSAAPVS) {
9908  if (!calculateBinaryOperatorAndTakeUnion(BinOp, Zero, R))
9909  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
9910  }
9911  } else if (RHSContainsUndef) {
9912  for (const APInt &L : LHSAAPVS) {
9913  if (!calculateBinaryOperatorAndTakeUnion(BinOp, L, Zero))
9914  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
9915  }
9916  } else {
9917  for (const APInt &L : LHSAAPVS) {
9918  for (const APInt &R : RHSAAPVS) {
9919  if (!calculateBinaryOperatorAndTakeUnion(BinOp, L, R))
9920  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
9921  }
9922  }
9923  }
9924  return AssumedBefore == getAssumed() ? ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED
9925  : ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
9926  }
9927 
9928  ChangeStatus updateWithInstruction(Attributor &A, Instruction *Inst) {
9929  auto AssumedBefore = getAssumed();
9930  SetTy Incoming;
9931  bool ContainsUndef;
9932  if (!fillSetWithConstantValues(A, IRPosition::value(*Inst), Incoming,
9933  ContainsUndef, /* ForSelf */ true))
9934  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
9935  if (ContainsUndef) {
9936  unionAssumedWithUndef();
9937  } else {
9938  for (const auto &It : Incoming)
9939  unionAssumed(It);
9940  }
9941  return AssumedBefore == getAssumed() ? ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED
9942  : ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
9943  }
9944 
9945  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
9946  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
9947  Value &V = getAssociatedValue();
9948  Instruction *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(&V);
9949 
9950  if (auto *ICI = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(I))
9951  return updateWithICmpInst(A, ICI);
9952 
9953  if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(I))
9954  return updateWithSelectInst(A, SI);
9955 
9956  if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<CastInst>(I))
9957  return updateWithCastInst(A, CI);
9958 
9959  if (auto *BinOp = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(I))
9960  return updateWithBinaryOperator(A, BinOp);
9961 
9962  if (isa<PHINode>(I) || isa<LoadInst>(I))
9963  return updateWithInstruction(A, I);
9964 
9965  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
9966  }
9967 
9968  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
9969  void trackStatistics() const override {
9970  STATS_DECLTRACK_FLOATING_ATTR(potential_values)
9971  }
9972 };
9973

10060 /// ------------------------ NoUndef Attribute ---------------------------------
10061 struct AANoUndefImpl : AANoUndef {
10062  AANoUndefImpl(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A) : AANoUndef(IRP, A) {}
10063 
10064  /// See AbstractAttribute::initialize(...).
10065  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
10066  if (getIRPosition().hasAttr({Attribute::NoUndef})) {
10067  indicateOptimisticFixpoint();
10068  return;
10069  }
10070  Value &V = getAssociatedValue();
10071  if (isa<UndefValue>(V))
10072  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
10073  else if (isa<FreezeInst>(V))
10074  indicateOptimisticFixpoint();
10075  else if (getPositionKind() != IRPosition::IRP_RETURNED &&
10076  isGuaranteedNotToBeUndefOrPoison(&V))
10077  indicateOptimisticFixpoint();
10078  else
10079  AANoUndef::initialize(A);
10080  }
10081 
10082  /// See followUsesInMBEC
10083  bool followUseInMBEC(Attributor &A, const Use *U, const Instruction *I,
10084  AANoUndef::StateType &State) {
10085  const Value *UseV = U->get();
10086  const DominatorTree *DT = nullptr;
10087  AssumptionCache *AC = nullptr;
10088  InformationCache &InfoCache = A.getInfoCache();
10089  if (Function *F = getAnchorScope()) {
10090  DT = InfoCache.getAnalysisResultForFunction<DominatorTreeAnalysis>(*F);
10091  AC = InfoCache.getAnalysisResultForFunction<AssumptionAnalysis>(*F);
10092  }
10093  State.setKnown(isGuaranteedNotToBeUndefOrPoison(UseV, AC, I, DT));
10094  bool TrackUse = false;
10095  // Track use for instructions which must produce undef or poison bits when
10096  // at least one operand contains such bits.
10097  if (isa<CastInst>(*I) || isa<GetElementPtrInst>(*I))
10098  TrackUse = true;
10099  return TrackUse;
10100  }
10101 
10102  /// See AbstractAttribute::getAsStr().
10103  const std::string getAsStr() const override {
10104  return getAssumed() ? "noundef" : "may-undef-or-poison";
10105  }
10106 
10107  ChangeStatus manifest(Attributor &A) override {
10108  // We don't manifest noundef attribute for dead positions because the
10109  // associated values with dead positions would be replaced with undef
10110  // values.
10111  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
10112  if (A.isAssumedDead(getIRPosition(), nullptr, nullptr,
10113  UsedAssumedInformation))
10114  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
10115  // A position whose simplified value does not have any value is
10116  // considered to be dead. We don't manifest noundef in such positions for
10117  // the same reason above.
10118  if (!A.getAssumedSimplified(getIRPosition(), *this, UsedAssumedInformation,
10119  AA::Interprocedural)
10120  .has_value())
10121  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
10122  return AANoUndef::manifest(A);
10123  }
10124 };
10125 
10126 struct AANoUndefFloating : public AANoUndefImpl {
10127  AANoUndefFloating(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
10128  : AANoUndefImpl(IRP, A) {}
10129 
10130  /// See AbstractAttribute::initialize(...).
10131  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
10132  AANoUndefImpl::initialize(A);
10133  if (!getState().isAtFixpoint())
10134  if (Instruction *CtxI = getCtxI())
10135  followUsesInMBEC(*this, A, getState(), *CtxI);
10136  }
10137 
10138  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
10139  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
10140 
10141  SmallVector<AA::ValueAndContext> Values;
10142  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
10143  if (!A.getAssumedSimplifiedValues(getIRPosition(), *this, Values,
10144  AA::AnyScope, UsedAssumedInformation)) {
10145  Values.push_back({getAssociatedValue(), getCtxI()});
10146  }
10147 
10148  StateType T;
10149  auto VisitValueCB = [&](Value &V, const Instruction *CtxI) -> bool {
10150  const auto &AA = A.getAAFor<AANoUndef>(*this, IRPosition::value(V),
10151  DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
10152  if (this == &AA) {
10153  T.indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
10154  } else {
10155  const AANoUndef::StateType &S =
10156  static_cast<const AANoUndef::StateType &>(AA.getState());
10157  T ^= S;
10158  }
10159  return T.isValidState();
10160  };
10161 
10162  for (const auto &VAC : Values)
10163  if (!VisitValueCB(*VAC.getValue(), VAC.getCtxI()))
10164  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
10165 
10166  return clampStateAndIndicateChange(getState(), T);
10167  }
10168 
10169  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
10170  void trackStatistics() const override { STATS_DECLTRACK_FNRET_ATTR(noundef) }
10171 };
