10208 struct AACallEdgesImpl : public AACallEdges {
10209  AACallEdgesImpl(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A) : AACallEdges(IRP, A) {}
10210 
10211  const SetVector<Function *> &getOptimisticEdges() const override {
10212  return CalledFunctions;
10213  }
10214 
10215  bool hasUnknownCallee() const override { return HasUnknownCallee; }
10216 
10217  bool hasNonAsmUnknownCallee() const override {
10218  return HasUnknownCalleeNonAsm;
10219  }
10220 
10221  const std::string getAsStr() const override {
10222  return "CallEdges[" + std::to_string(HasUnknownCallee) + "," +
10223  std::to_string(CalledFunctions.size()) + "]";
10224  }
10225 
10226  void trackStatistics() const override {}
10227 
10228 protected:
10229  void addCalledFunction(Function *Fn, ChangeStatus &Change) {
10230  if (CalledFunctions.insert(Fn)) {
10231  Change = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
10232  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AACallEdges] New call edge: " << Fn->getName()
10233  << "\n");
10234  }
10235  }
10236 
10237  void setHasUnknownCallee(bool NonAsm, ChangeStatus &Change) {
10238  if (!HasUnknownCallee)
10239  Change = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
10240  if (NonAsm && !HasUnknownCalleeNonAsm)
10241  Change = ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
10242  HasUnknownCalleeNonAsm |= NonAsm;
10243  HasUnknownCallee = true;
10244  }
10245 
10246 private:
10247  /// Optimistic set of functions that might be called by this position.
10248  SetVector<Function *> CalledFunctions;
10249 
10250  /// Is there any call with a unknown callee.
10251  bool HasUnknownCallee = false;
10252 
10253  /// Is there any call with a unknown callee, excluding any inline asm.
10254  bool HasUnknownCalleeNonAsm = false;
10255 };
10256 
10257 struct AACallEdgesCallSite : public AACallEdgesImpl {
10258  AACallEdgesCallSite(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
10259  : AACallEdgesImpl(IRP, A) {}
10260  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
10261  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
10262  ChangeStatus Change = ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
10263 
10264  auto VisitValue = [&](Value &V, const Instruction *CtxI) -> bool {
10265  if (Function *Fn = dyn_cast<Function>(&V)) {
10266  addCalledFunction(Fn, Change);
10267  } else {
10268  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AACallEdges] Unrecognized value: " << V << "\n");
10269  setHasUnknownCallee(true, Change);
10270  }
10271 
10272  // Explore all values.
10273  return true;
10274  };
10275 
10276  SmallVector<AA::ValueAndContext> Values;
10277  // Process any value that we might call.
10278  auto ProcessCalledOperand = [&](Value *V, Instruction *CtxI) {
10279  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
10280  Values.clear();
10281  if (!A.getAssumedSimplifiedValues(IRPosition::value(*V), *this, Values,
10282  AA::AnyScope, UsedAssumedInformation)) {
10283  Values.push_back({*V, CtxI});
10284  }
10285  for (auto &VAC : Values)
10286  VisitValue(*VAC.getValue(), VAC.getCtxI());
10287  };
10288 
10289  CallBase *CB = cast<CallBase>(getCtxI());
10290 
10291  if (auto *IA = dyn_cast<InlineAsm>(CB->getCalledOperand())) {
10292  if (IA->hasSideEffects() &&
10293  !hasAssumption(*CB->getCaller(), "ompx_no_call_asm") &&
10294  !hasAssumption(*CB, "ompx_no_call_asm")) {
10295  setHasUnknownCallee(false, Change);
10296  }
10297  return Change;
10298  }
10299 
10300  // Process callee metadata if available.
10301  if (auto *MD = getCtxI()->getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_callees)) {
10302  for (const auto &Op : MD->operands()) {
10303  Function *Callee = mdconst::dyn_extract_or_null<Function>(Op);
10304  if (Callee)
10305  addCalledFunction(Callee, Change);
10306  }
10307  return Change;
10308  }
10309 
10310  // The most simple case.
10311  ProcessCalledOperand(CB->getCalledOperand(), CB);
10312 
10313  // Process callback functions.
10314  SmallVector<const Use *, 4u> CallbackUses;
10315  AbstractCallSite::getCallbackUses(*CB, CallbackUses);
10316  for (const Use *U : CallbackUses)
10317  ProcessCalledOperand(U->get(), CB);
10318 
10319  return Change;
10320  }
10321 };
10322 
10323 struct AACallEdgesFunction : public AACallEdgesImpl {
10324  AACallEdgesFunction(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
10325  : AACallEdgesImpl(IRP, A) {}
10326 
10327  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
10328  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
10329  ChangeStatus Change = ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
10330 
10331  auto ProcessCallInst = [&](Instruction &Inst) {
10332  CallBase &CB = cast<CallBase>(Inst);
10333 
10334  auto &CBEdges = A.getAAFor<AACallEdges>(
10335  *this, IRPosition::callsite_function(CB), DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
10336  if (CBEdges.hasNonAsmUnknownCallee())
10337  setHasUnknownCallee(true, Change);
10338  if (CBEdges.hasUnknownCallee())
10339  setHasUnknownCallee(false, Change);
10340 
10341  for (Function *F : CBEdges.getOptimisticEdges())
10342  addCalledFunction(F, Change);
10343 
10344  return true;
10345  };
10346 
10347  // Visit all callable instructions.
10348  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
10349  if (!A.checkForAllCallLikeInstructions(ProcessCallInst, *this,
10350  UsedAssumedInformation,
10351  /* CheckBBLivenessOnly */ true)) {
10352  // If we haven't looked at all call like instructions, assume that there
10353  // are unknown callees.
10354  setHasUnknownCallee(true, Change);
10355  }
10356 
10357  return Change;
10358  }
10359 };
10360 
10361 /// -------------------AAInterFnReachability Attribute--------------------------
10362 
10363 struct AAInterFnReachabilityFunction
10364  : public CachedReachabilityAA<AAInterFnReachability, Function> {
10365  AAInterFnReachabilityFunction(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
10366  : CachedReachabilityAA<AAInterFnReachability, Function>(IRP, A) {}
10367 
10368  bool instructionCanReach(
10369  Attributor &A, const Instruction &From, const Function &To,
10370  const AA::InstExclusionSetTy *ExclusionSet,
10371  SmallPtrSet<const Function *, 16> *Visited) const override {
10372  assert(From.getFunction() == getAnchorScope() && "Queried the wrong AA!");
10373  auto *NonConstThis = const_cast<AAInterFnReachabilityFunction *>(this);
10374 
10375  RQITy StackRQI(A, From, To, ExclusionSet, false);
10376  typename RQITy::Reachable Result;
10377  if (!NonConstThis->checkQueryCache(A, StackRQI, Result))
10378  return NonConstThis->isReachableImpl(A, StackRQI);
10379  return Result == RQITy::Reachable::Yes;
10380  }
10381 
10382  bool isReachableImpl(Attributor &A, RQITy &RQI) override {
10383  return isReachableImpl(A, RQI, nullptr);
10384  }
10385 
10386  bool isReachableImpl(Attributor &A, RQITy &RQI,
10387  SmallPtrSet<const Function *, 16> *Visited) {
10388 
10389  SmallPtrSet<const Function *, 16> LocalVisited;
10390  if (!Visited)
10391  Visited = &LocalVisited;
10392 
10393  auto CheckReachableCallBase = [&](CallBase *CB) {
10394  auto &CBEdges = A.getAAFor<AACallEdges>(
10395  *this, IRPosition::callsite_function(*CB), DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
10396  if (!CBEdges.getState().isValidState())
10397  return false;
10398  // TODO Check To backwards in this case.
10399  if (CBEdges.hasUnknownCallee())
10400  return false;
10401 
10402  for (Function *Fn : CBEdges.getOptimisticEdges()) {
10403  if (Fn == RQI.To)
10404  return false;
10405  if (!Visited->insert(Fn).second)
10406  continue;
10407  if (Fn->isDeclaration()) {
10408  if (Fn->hasFnAttribute(Attribute::NoCallback))
10409  continue;
10410  // TODO Check To backwards in this case.
10411  return false;
10412  }
10413 
10414  const AAInterFnReachability *InterFnReachability = this;
10415  if (Fn != getAnchorScope())
10416  InterFnReachability = &A.getAAFor<AAInterFnReachability>(
10417  *this, IRPosition::function(*Fn), DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
10418 
10419  const Instruction &FnFirstInst = Fn->getEntryBlock().front();
10420  if (InterFnReachability->instructionCanReach(A, FnFirstInst, *RQI.To,
10421  RQI.ExclusionSet, Visited))
10422  return false;
10423  }
10424  return true;
10425  };
10426 
10427  const auto &IntraFnReachability = A.getAAFor<AAIntraFnReachability>(
10428  *this, IRPosition::function(*RQI.From->getFunction()),
10429  DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
10430 
10431  // Determine call like instructions that we can reach from the inst.
10432  auto CheckCallBase = [&](Instruction &CBInst) {
10433  if (!IntraFnReachability.isAssumedReachable(A, *RQI.From, CBInst,
10434  RQI.ExclusionSet))
10435  return true;
10436  return CheckReachableCallBase(cast<CallBase>(&CBInst));
10437  };
10438 
10439  bool UsedExclusionSet = /* conservative */ true;
10440  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
10441  if (!A.checkForAllCallLikeInstructions(CheckCallBase, *this,
10442  UsedAssumedInformation,
10443  /* CheckBBLivenessOnly */ true))
10444  return rememberResult(A, RQITy::Reachable::Yes, RQI, UsedExclusionSet);
10445 
10446  return rememberResult(A, RQITy::Reachable::No, RQI, UsedExclusionSet);
10447  }
10448 
10449  void trackStatistics() const override {}
10450 
10451 private:
10452  SmallVector<RQITy *> QueryVector;
10453  DenseSet<RQITy *> QueryCache;
10454 };
10455 } // namespace
10456 
10457 template <typename AAType>
10458 static std::optional<Constant *>
10459 askForAssumedConstant(Attributor &A, const AbstractAttribute &QueryingAA,
10460  const IRPosition &IRP, Type &Ty) {
10461  if (!Ty.isIntegerTy())
10462  return nullptr;
10463 
10464  // This will also pass the call base context.
10465  const auto &AA = A.getAAFor<AAType>(QueryingAA, IRP, DepClassTy::NONE);
10466 
10467  std::optional<Constant *> COpt = AA.getAssumedConstant(A);
10468 
10469  if (!COpt.has_value()) {
10470  A.recordDependence(AA, QueryingAA, DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
10471  return std::nullopt;
10472  }
10473  if (auto *C = *COpt) {
10474  A.recordDependence(AA, QueryingAA, DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
10475  return C;
10476  }
10477  return nullptr;
10478 }
10479 
10480 Value *AAPotentialValues::getSingleValue(
10481  Attributor &A, const AbstractAttribute &AA, const IRPosition &IRP,
10482  SmallVectorImpl<AA::ValueAndContext> &Values) {
10483  Type &Ty = *IRP.getAssociatedType();
10484  std::optional<Value *> V;
10485  for (auto &It : Values) {
10486  V = AA::combineOptionalValuesInAAValueLatice(V, It.getValue(), &Ty);
10487  if (V.has_value() && !*V)
10488  break;
10489  }
10490  if (!V.has_value())
10491  return UndefValue::get(&Ty);
10492  return *V;
10493 }
10494 
10495 namespace {
10496 struct AAPotentialValuesImpl : AAPotentialValues {
10497  using StateType = PotentialLLVMValuesState;
10498 
10499  AAPotentialValuesImpl(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
10500  : AAPotentialValues(IRP, A) {}
10501 
10502  /// See AbstractAttribute::initialize(..).
10503  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
10504  if (A.hasSimplificationCallback(getIRPosition())) {
10505  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
10506  return;
10507  }
10508  Value *Stripped = getAssociatedValue().stripPointerCasts();
10509  auto *CE = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(Stripped);
10510  if (isa<Constant>(Stripped) &&
10511  (!CE || CE->getOpcode() != Instruction::ICmp)) {
10512  addValue(A, getState(), *Stripped, getCtxI(), AA::AnyScope,
10513  getAnchorScope());
10514  indicateOptimisticFixpoint();
10515  return;
10516  }
10517  AAPotentialValues::initialize(A);
10518  }
10519 
10520  /// See AbstractAttribute::getAsStr().
10521  const std::string getAsStr() const override {
10522  std::string Str;
10523  llvm::raw_string_ostream OS(Str);
10524  OS << getState();
10525  return OS.str();
10526  }
10527 
10528  template <typename AAType>
10529  static std::optional<Value *> askOtherAA(Attributor &A,
10530  const AbstractAttribute &AA,
10531  const IRPosition &IRP, Type &Ty) {
10532  if (isa<Constant>(IRP.getAssociatedValue()))
10533  return &IRP.getAssociatedValue();
10534  std::optional<Constant *> C = askForAssumedConstant<AAType>(A, AA, IRP, Ty);
10535  if (!C)
10536  return std::nullopt;
10537  if (*C)
10538  if (auto *CC = AA::getWithType(**C, Ty))
10539  return CC;
10540  return nullptr;
10541  }
10542 
10543  void addValue(Attributor &A, StateType &State, Value &V,
10544  const Instruction *CtxI, AA::ValueScope S,
10545  Function *AnchorScope) const {
10546 
10547  IRPosition ValIRP = IRPosition::value(V);
10548  if (auto *CB = dyn_cast_or_null<CallBase>(CtxI)) {
10549  for (const auto &U : CB->args()) {
10550  if (U.get() != &V)
10551  continue;
10552  ValIRP = IRPosition::callsite_argument(*CB, CB->getArgOperandNo(&U));
10553  break;
10554  }
10555  }
10556 
10557  Value *VPtr = &V;
10558  if (ValIRP.getAssociatedType()->isIntegerTy()) {
10559  Type &Ty = *getAssociatedType();
10560  std::optional<Value *> SimpleV =
10561  askOtherAA<AAValueConstantRange>(A, *this, ValIRP, Ty);
10562  if (SimpleV.has_value() && !*SimpleV) {
10563  auto &PotentialConstantsAA = A.getAAFor<AAPotentialConstantValues>(
10564  *this, ValIRP, DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
10565  if (PotentialConstantsAA.isValidState()) {
10566  for (const auto &It : PotentialConstantsAA.getAssumedSet())
10567  State.unionAssumed({{*ConstantInt::get(&Ty, It), nullptr}, S});
10568  if (PotentialConstantsAA.undefIsContained())
10569  State.unionAssumed({{*UndefValue::get(&Ty), nullptr}, S});
10570  return;
10571  }
10572  }
10573  if (!SimpleV.has_value())
10574  return;
10575 
10576  if (*SimpleV)
10577  VPtr = *SimpleV;
10578  }
10579 
10580  if (isa<ConstantInt>(VPtr))
10581  CtxI = nullptr;
10582  if (!AA::isValidInScope(*VPtr, AnchorScope))
10583  S = AA::ValueScope(S | AA::Interprocedural);
10584 
10585  State.unionAssumed({{*VPtr, CtxI}, S});
10586  }
10587 
10588  /// Helper struct to tie a value+context pair together with the scope for
10589  /// which this is the simplified version.
10590  struct ItemInfo {
10591  AA::ValueAndContext I;
10592  AA::ValueScope S;
10593 
10594  bool operator==(const ItemInfo &II) const {
10595  return II.I == I && II.S == S;
10596  };
10597  bool operator<(const ItemInfo &II) const {
10598  if (I == II.I)
10599  return S < II.S;
10600  return I < II.I;
10601  };
10602  };
10603 
10604  bool recurseForValue(Attributor &A, const IRPosition &IRP, AA::ValueScope S) {
10605  SmallMapVector<AA::ValueAndContext, int, 8> ValueScopeMap;
10606  for (auto CS : {AA::Intraprocedural, AA::Interprocedural}) {
10607  if (!(CS & S))
10608  continue;
10609 
10610  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
10611  SmallVector<AA::ValueAndContext> Values;
10612  if (!A.getAssumedSimplifiedValues(IRP, this, Values, CS,
10613  UsedAssumedInformation))
10614  return false;
10615 
10616  for (auto &It : Values)
10617  ValueScopeMap[It] += CS;
10618  }
10619  for (auto &It : ValueScopeMap)
10620  addValue(A, getState(), *It.first.getValue(), It.first.getCtxI(),
10621  AA::ValueScope(It.second), getAnchorScope());
10622 
10623  return true;
10624  }
10625 
10626  void giveUpOnIntraprocedural(Attributor &A) {
10627  auto NewS = StateType::getBestState(getState());
10628  for (const auto &It : getAssumedSet()) {
10629  if (It.second == AA::Intraprocedural)
10630  continue;
10631  addValue(A, NewS, *It.first.getValue(), It.first.getCtxI(),
10632  AA::Interprocedural, getAnchorScope());
10633  }
10634  assert(!undefIsContained() && "Undef should be an explicit value!");
10635  addValue(A, NewS, getAssociatedValue(), getCtxI(), AA::Intraprocedural,
10636  getAnchorScope());
10637  getState() = NewS;
10638  }
10639 
10640  /// See AbstractState::indicatePessimisticFixpoint(...).
10641  ChangeStatus indicatePessimisticFixpoint() override {
10642  getState() = StateType::getBestState(getState());
10643  getState().unionAssumed({{getAssociatedValue(), getCtxI()}, AA::AnyScope});
10644  AAPotentialValues::indicateOptimisticFixpoint();
10645  return ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
10646  }
10647 
10648  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
10649  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
10650  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
10651  }
10652 
10653  /// See AbstractAttribute::manifest(...).
10654  ChangeStatus manifest(Attributor &A) override {
10655  SmallVector<AA::ValueAndContext> Values;
10656  for (AA::ValueScope S : {AA::Interprocedural, AA::Intraprocedural}) {
10657  Values.clear();
10658  if (!getAssumedSimplifiedValues(A, Values, S))
10659  continue;
10660  Value &OldV = getAssociatedValue();
10661  if (isa<UndefValue>(OldV))
10662  continue;
10663  Value *NewV = getSingleValue(A, *this, getIRPosition(), Values);
10664  if (!NewV || NewV == &OldV)
10665  continue;
10666  if (getCtxI() &&
10667  !AA::isValidAtPosition({*NewV, *getCtxI()}, A.getInfoCache()))
10668  continue;
10669  if (A.changeAfterManifest(getIRPosition(), *NewV))
10670  return ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
10671  }
10672  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
10673  }
10674 
10675  bool getAssumedSimplifiedValues(Attributor &A,
10676  SmallVectorImpl<AA::ValueAndContext> &Values,
10677  AA::ValueScope S) const override {
10678  if (!isValidState())
10679  return false;
10680  for (const auto &It : getAssumedSet())
10681  if (It.second & S)
10682  Values.push_back(It.first);
10683  assert(!undefIsContained() && "Undef should be an explicit value!");
10684  return true;
10685  }
10686 };
10687 
10688 struct AAPotentialValuesFloating : AAPotentialValuesImpl {
10689  AAPotentialValuesFloating(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
10690  : AAPotentialValuesImpl(IRP, A) {}
10691 
10692  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
10693  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
10694  auto AssumedBefore = getAssumed();
10695 
10696  genericValueTraversal(A);
10697 
10698  return (AssumedBefore == getAssumed()) ? ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED
10699  : ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
10700  }
10701 
10702  /// Helper struct to remember which AAIsDead instances we actually used.
10703  struct LivenessInfo {
10704  const AAIsDead *LivenessAA = nullptr;
10705  bool AnyDead = false;
10706  };
10707 
10708  /// Check if \p Cmp is a comparison we can simplify.
10709  ///
10710  /// We handle multiple cases, one in which at least one operand is an
10711  /// (assumed) nullptr. If so, try to simplify it using AANonNull on the other
10712  /// operand. Return true if successful, in that case Worklist will be updated.
10713  bool handleCmp(Attributor &A, Value &Cmp, Value *LHS, Value *RHS,
10714  CmpInst::Predicate Pred, ItemInfo II,
10715  SmallVectorImpl<ItemInfo> &Worklist) {
10716 
10717  // Simplify the operands first.
10718  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
10719  const auto &SimplifiedLHS = A.getAssumedSimplified(
10720  IRPosition::value(*LHS, getCallBaseContext()), *this,
10721  UsedAssumedInformation, AA::Intraprocedural);
10722  if (!SimplifiedLHS.has_value())
10723  return true;
10724  if (!*SimplifiedLHS)
10725  return false;
10726  LHS = *SimplifiedLHS;
10727 
10728  const auto &SimplifiedRHS = A.getAssumedSimplified(
10729  IRPosition::value(*RHS, getCallBaseContext()), *this,
10730  UsedAssumedInformation, AA::Intraprocedural);
10731  if (!SimplifiedRHS.has_value())
10732  return true;
10733  if (!*SimplifiedRHS)
10734  return false;
10735  RHS = *SimplifiedRHS;
10736 
10737  LLVMContext &Ctx = LHS->getContext();
10738  // Handle the trivial case first in which we don't even need to think about
10739  // null or non-null.
10740  if (LHS == RHS &&
10741  (CmpInst::isTrueWhenEqual(Pred) || CmpInst::isFalseWhenEqual(Pred))) {
10742  Constant *NewV = ConstantInt::get(Type::getInt1Ty(Ctx),
10743  CmpInst::isTrueWhenEqual(Pred));
10744  addValue(A, getState(), *NewV, /* CtxI */ nullptr, II.S,
10745  getAnchorScope());
10746  return true;
10747  }
10748 
10749  // From now on we only handle equalities (==, !=).
10750  if (!CmpInst::isEquality(Pred))
10751  return false;
10752 
10753  bool LHSIsNull = isa<ConstantPointerNull>(LHS);
10754  bool RHSIsNull = isa<ConstantPointerNull>(RHS);
10755  if (!LHSIsNull && !RHSIsNull)
10756  return false;
10757 
10758  // Left is the nullptr ==/!= non-nullptr case. We'll use AANonNull on the
10759  // non-nullptr operand and if we assume it's non-null we can conclude the
10760  // result of the comparison.
10761  assert((LHSIsNull || RHSIsNull) &&
10762  "Expected nullptr versus non-nullptr comparison at this point");
10763 
10764  // The index is the operand that we assume is not null.
10765  unsigned PtrIdx = LHSIsNull;
10766  auto &PtrNonNullAA = A.getAAFor<AANonNull>(
10767  *this, IRPosition::value(*(PtrIdx ? RHS : LHS)), DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
10768  if (!PtrNonNullAA.isAssumedNonNull())
10769  return false;
10770 
10771  // The new value depends on the predicate, true for != and false for ==.
10772  Constant *NewV =
10773  ConstantInt::get(Type::getInt1Ty(Ctx), Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_NE);
10774  addValue(A, getState(), *NewV, /* CtxI */ nullptr, II.S, getAnchorScope());
10775  return true;
10776  }
10777 
10778  bool handleSelectInst(Attributor &A, SelectInst &SI, ItemInfo II,
10779  SmallVectorImpl<ItemInfo> &Worklist) {
10780  const Instruction *CtxI = II.I.getCtxI();
10781  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
10782 
10783  std::optional<Constant *> C =
10784  A.getAssumedConstant(*SI.getCondition(), *this, UsedAssumedInformation);
10785  bool NoValueYet = !C.has_value();
10786  if (NoValueYet || isa_and_nonnull<UndefValue>(*C))
10787  return true;
10788  if (auto *CI = dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantInt>(*C)) {
10789  if (CI->isZero())
10790  Worklist.push_back({{*SI.getFalseValue(), CtxI}, II.S});
10791  else
10792  Worklist.push_back({{*SI.getTrueValue(), CtxI}, II.S});
10793  } else if (&SI == &getAssociatedValue()) {
10794  // We could not simplify the condition, assume both values.
10795  Worklist.push_back({{*SI.getTrueValue(), CtxI}, II.S});
10796  Worklist.push_back({{*SI.getFalseValue(), CtxI}, II.S});
10797  } else {
10798  std::optional<Value *> SimpleV = A.getAssumedSimplified(
10799  IRPosition::inst(SI), *this, UsedAssumedInformation, II.S);
10800  if (!SimpleV.has_value())
10801  return true;
10802  if (*SimpleV) {
10803  addValue(A, getState(), **SimpleV, CtxI, II.S, getAnchorScope());
10804  return true;
10805  }
10806  return false;
10807  }
10808  return true;
10809  }
10810 
10811  bool handleLoadInst(Attributor &A, LoadInst &LI, ItemInfo II,
10812  SmallVectorImpl<ItemInfo> &Worklist) {
10813  SmallSetVector<Value *, 4> PotentialCopies;
10814  SmallSetVector<Instruction *, 4> PotentialValueOrigins;
10815  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
10816  if (!AA::getPotentiallyLoadedValues(A, LI, PotentialCopies,
10817  PotentialValueOrigins, *this,
10818  UsedAssumedInformation,
10819  /* OnlyExact */ true)) {
10820  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAPotentialValues] Failed to get potentially "
10821  "loaded values for load instruction "
10822  << LI << "\n");
10823  return false;
10824  }
10825 
10826  // Do not simplify loads that are only used in llvm.assume if we cannot also
10827  // remove all stores that may feed into the load. The reason is that the
10828  // assume is probably worth something as long as the stores are around.
10829  InformationCache &InfoCache = A.getInfoCache();
10830  if (InfoCache.isOnlyUsedByAssume(LI)) {
10831  if (!llvm::all_of(PotentialValueOrigins, [&](Instruction *I) {
10832  if (!I)
10833  return true;
10834  if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(I))
10835  return A.isAssumedDead(SI->getOperandUse(0), this,
10836  /* LivenessAA */ nullptr,
10837  UsedAssumedInformation,
10838  /* CheckBBLivenessOnly */ false);
10839  return A.isAssumedDead(*I, this, /* LivenessAA */ nullptr,
10840  UsedAssumedInformation,
10841  /* CheckBBLivenessOnly */ false);
10842  })) {
10843  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAPotentialValues] Load is onl used by assumes "
10844  "and we cannot delete all the stores: "
10845  << LI << "\n");
10846  return false;
10847  }
10848  }
10849 
10850  // Values have to be dynamically unique or we loose the fact that a
10851  // single llvm::Value might represent two runtime values (e.g.,
10852  // stack locations in different recursive calls).
10853  const Instruction *CtxI = II.I.getCtxI();
10854  bool ScopeIsLocal = (II.S & AA::Intraprocedural);
10855  bool AllLocal = ScopeIsLocal;
10856  bool DynamicallyUnique = llvm::all_of(PotentialCopies, [&](Value *PC) {
10857  AllLocal &= AA::isValidInScope(*PC, getAnchorScope());
10858  return AA::isDynamicallyUnique(A, *this, *PC);
10859  });
10860  if (!DynamicallyUnique) {
10861  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "[AAPotentialValues] Not all potentially loaded "
10862  "values are dynamically unique: "
10863  << LI << "\n");
10864  return false;
10865  }
10866 
10867  for (auto *PotentialCopy : PotentialCopies) {
10868  if (AllLocal) {
10869  Worklist.push_back({{*PotentialCopy, CtxI}, II.S});
10870  } else {
10871  Worklist.push_back({{*PotentialCopy, CtxI}, AA::Interprocedural});
10872  }
10873  }
10874  if (!AllLocal && ScopeIsLocal)
10875  addValue(A, getState(), LI, CtxI, AA::Intraprocedural, getAnchorScope());
10876  return true;
10877  }
10878 
10879  bool handlePHINode(
10880  Attributor &A, PHINode &PHI, ItemInfo II,
10881  SmallVectorImpl<ItemInfo> &Worklist,
10882  SmallMapVector<const Function *, LivenessInfo, 4> &LivenessAAs) {
10883  auto GetLivenessInfo = [&](const Function &F) -> LivenessInfo & {
10884  LivenessInfo &LI = LivenessAAs[&F];
10885  if (!LI.LivenessAA)
10886  LI.LivenessAA = &A.getAAFor<AAIsDead>(*this, IRPosition::function(F),
10887  DepClassTy::NONE);
10888  return LI;
10889  };
10890 
10891  if (&PHI == &getAssociatedValue()) {
10892  LivenessInfo &LI = GetLivenessInfo(*PHI.getFunction());
10893  for (unsigned u = 0, e = PHI.getNumIncomingValues(); u < e; u++) {
10894  BasicBlock *IncomingBB = PHI.getIncomingBlock(u);
10895  if (LI.LivenessAA->isEdgeDead(IncomingBB, PHI.getParent())) {
10896  LI.AnyDead = true;
10897  continue;
10898  }
10899  Worklist.push_back(
10900  {{*PHI.getIncomingValue(u), IncomingBB->getTerminator()}, II.S});
10901  }
10902  return true;
10903  }
10904 
10905  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
10906  std::optional<Value *> SimpleV = A.getAssumedSimplified(
10907  IRPosition::inst(PHI), *this, UsedAssumedInformation, II.S);
10908  if (!SimpleV.has_value())
10909  return true;
10910  if (!(*SimpleV))
10911  return false;
10912  addValue(A, getState(), **SimpleV, &PHI, II.S, getAnchorScope());
10913  return true;
10914  }
10915 
10916  /// Use the generic, non-optimistic InstSimplfy functionality if we managed to
10917  /// simplify any operand of the instruction \p I. Return true if successful,
10918  /// in that case Worklist will be updated.
10919  bool handleGenericInst(Attributor &A, Instruction &I, ItemInfo II,
10920  SmallVectorImpl<ItemInfo> &Worklist) {
10921  bool SomeSimplified = false;
10922  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
10923 
10924  SmallVector<Value *, 8> NewOps(I.getNumOperands());
10925  int Idx = 0;
10926  for (Value *Op : I.operands()) {
10927  const auto &SimplifiedOp = A.getAssumedSimplified(
10928  IRPosition::value(*Op, getCallBaseContext()), *this,
10929  UsedAssumedInformation, AA::Intraprocedural);
10930  // If we are not sure about any operand we are not sure about the entire
10931  // instruction, we'll wait.
10932  if (!SimplifiedOp.has_value())
10933  return true;
10934 
10935  if (*SimplifiedOp)
10936  NewOps[Idx] = *SimplifiedOp;
10937  else
10938  NewOps[Idx] = Op;
10939 
10940  SomeSimplified |= (NewOps[Idx] != Op);
10941  ++Idx;
10942  }
10943 
10944  // We won't bother with the InstSimplify interface if we didn't simplify any
10945  // operand ourselves.
10946  if (!SomeSimplified)
10947  return false;
10948 
10949  InformationCache &InfoCache = A.getInfoCache();
10950  Function *F = I.getFunction();
10951  const auto *DT =
10952  InfoCache.getAnalysisResultForFunction<DominatorTreeAnalysis>(*F);
10953  const auto *TLI = A.getInfoCache().getTargetLibraryInfoForFunction(*F);
10954  auto *AC = InfoCache.getAnalysisResultForFunction<AssumptionAnalysis>(*F);
10955  OptimizationRemarkEmitter *ORE = nullptr;
10956 
10957  const DataLayout &DL = I.getModule()->getDataLayout();
10958  SimplifyQuery Q(DL, TLI, DT, AC, &I);
10959  Value *NewV = simplifyInstructionWithOperands(&I, NewOps, Q, ORE);
10960  if (!NewV || NewV == &I)
10961  return false;
10962 
10963  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Generic inst " << I << " assumed simplified to "
10964  << *NewV << "\n");
10965  Worklist.push_back({{*NewV, II.I.getCtxI()}, II.S});
10966  return true;
10967  }
10968 
10969  bool simplifyInstruction(
10970  Attributor &A, Instruction &I, ItemInfo II,
10971  SmallVectorImpl<ItemInfo> &Worklist,
10972  SmallMapVector<const Function *, LivenessInfo, 4> &LivenessAAs) {
10973  if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<CmpInst>(&I))
10974  if (handleCmp(A, *CI, CI->getOperand(0), CI->getOperand(1),
10975  CI->getPredicate(), II, Worklist))
10976  return true;
10977 
10978  switch (I.getOpcode()) {
10979  case Instruction::Select:
10980  return handleSelectInst(A, cast<SelectInst>(I), II, Worklist);
10981  case Instruction::PHI:
10982  return handlePHINode(A, cast<PHINode>(I), II, Worklist, LivenessAAs);
10983  case Instruction::Load:
10984  return handleLoadInst(A, cast<LoadInst>(I), II, Worklist);
10985  default:
10986  return handleGenericInst(A, I, II, Worklist);
10987  };
10988  return false;
10989  }
10990 
10991  void genericValueTraversal(Attributor &A) {
10992  SmallMapVector<const Function *, LivenessInfo, 4> LivenessAAs;
10993 
10994  Value *InitialV = &getAssociatedValue();
10995  SmallSet<ItemInfo, 16> Visited;
10996  SmallVector<ItemInfo, 16> Worklist;
10997  Worklist.push_back({{*InitialV, getCtxI()}, AA::AnyScope});
10998 
10999  int Iteration = 0;
11000  do {
11001  ItemInfo II = Worklist.pop_back_val();
11002  Value *V = II.I.getValue();
11003  assert(V);
11004  const Instruction *CtxI = II.I.getCtxI();
11005  AA::ValueScope S = II.S;
11006 
11007  // Check if we should process the current value. To prevent endless
11008  // recursion keep a record of the values we followed!
11009  if (!Visited.insert(II).second)
11010  continue;
11011 
11012  // Make sure we limit the compile time for complex expressions.
11013  if (Iteration++ >= MaxPotentialValuesIterations) {
11014  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Generic value traversal reached iteration limit: "
11015  << Iteration << "!\n");
11016  addValue(A, getState(), *V, CtxI, S, getAnchorScope());
11017  continue;
11018  }
11019 
11020  // Explicitly look through calls with a "returned" attribute if we do
11021  // not have a pointer as stripPointerCasts only works on them.
11022  Value *NewV = nullptr;
11023  if (V->getType()->isPointerTy()) {
11024  NewV = AA::getWithType(*V->stripPointerCasts(), *V->getType());
11025  } else {
11026  auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(V);
11027  if (CB && CB->getCalledFunction()) {
11028  for (Argument &Arg : CB->getCalledFunction()->args())
11029  if (Arg.hasReturnedAttr()) {
11030  NewV = CB->getArgOperand(Arg.getArgNo());
11031  break;
11032  }
11033  }
11034  }
11035  if (NewV && NewV != V) {
11036  Worklist.push_back({{*NewV, CtxI}, S});
11037  continue;
11038  }
11039 
11040  if (auto *CE = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(V)) {
11041  if (CE->getOpcode() == Instruction::ICmp)
11042  if (handleCmp(A, *CE, CE->getOperand(0), CE->getOperand(1),
11043  CmpInst::Predicate(CE->getPredicate()), II, Worklist))
11044  continue;
11045  }
11046 
11047  if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)) {
11048  if (simplifyInstruction(A, *I, II, Worklist, LivenessAAs))
11049  continue;
11050  }
11051 
11052  if (V != InitialV || isa<Argument>(V))
11053  if (recurseForValue(A, IRPosition::value(*V), II.S))
11054  continue;
11055 
11056  // If we haven't stripped anything we give up.
11057  if (V == InitialV && CtxI == getCtxI()) {
11058  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
11059  return;
11060  }
11061 
11062  addValue(A, getState(), *V, CtxI, S, getAnchorScope());
11063  } while (!Worklist.empty());
11064 
11065  // If we actually used liveness information so we have to record a
11066  // dependence.
11067  for (auto &It : LivenessAAs)
11068  if (It.second.AnyDead)
11069  A.recordDependence(*It.second.LivenessAA, *this, DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
11070  }
11071 
11072  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
11073  void trackStatistics() const override {
11074  STATS_DECLTRACK_FLOATING_ATTR(potential_values)
11075  }
11076 };
11077 
11078 struct AAPotentialValuesArgument final : AAPotentialValuesImpl {
11079  using Base = AAPotentialValuesImpl;
11080  AAPotentialValuesArgument(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
11081  : Base(IRP, A) {}
11082 
11083  /// See AbstractAttribute::initialize(..).
11084  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
11085  auto &Arg = cast<Argument>(getAssociatedValue());
11086  if (Arg.hasPointeeInMemoryValueAttr())
11087  indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
11088  }
11089 
11090  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
11091  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
11092  auto AssumedBefore = getAssumed();
11093 
11094  unsigned CSArgNo = getCallSiteArgNo();
11095 
11096  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
11097  SmallVector<AA::ValueAndContext> Values;
11098  auto CallSitePred = [&](AbstractCallSite ACS) {
11099  const auto CSArgIRP = IRPosition::callsite_argument(ACS, CSArgNo);
11100  if (CSArgIRP.getPositionKind() == IRP_INVALID)
11101  return false;
11102 
11103  if (!A.getAssumedSimplifiedValues(CSArgIRP, this, Values,
11104  AA::Interprocedural,
11105  UsedAssumedInformation))
11106  return false;
11107 
11108  return isValidState();
11109  };
11110 
11111  if (!A.checkForAllCallSites(CallSitePred, *this,
11112  /* RequireAllCallSites */ true,
11113  UsedAssumedInformation))
11114  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
11115 
11116  Function *Fn = getAssociatedFunction();
11117  bool AnyNonLocal = false;
11118  for (auto &It : Values) {
11119  if (isa<Constant>(It.getValue())) {
11120  addValue(A, getState(), *It.getValue(), It.getCtxI(), AA::AnyScope,
11121  getAnchorScope());
11122  continue;
11123  }
11124  if (!AA::isDynamicallyUnique(A, *this, *It.getValue()))
11125  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
11126 
11127  if (auto *Arg = dyn_cast<Argument>(It.getValue()))
11128  if (Arg->getParent() == Fn) {
11129  addValue(A, getState(), *It.getValue(), It.getCtxI(), AA::AnyScope,
11130  getAnchorScope());
11131  continue;
11132  }
11133  addValue(A, getState(), *It.getValue(), It.getCtxI(), AA::Interprocedural,
11134  getAnchorScope());
11135  AnyNonLocal = true;
11136  }
11137  assert(!undefIsContained() && "Undef should be an explicit value!");
11138  if (AnyNonLocal)
11139  giveUpOnIntraprocedural(A);
11140 
11141  return (AssumedBefore == getAssumed()) ? ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED
11142  : ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
11143  }
11144 
11145  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
11146  void trackStatistics() const override {
11147  STATS_DECLTRACK_ARG_ATTR(potential_values)
11148  }
11149 };
11150

11170  }

11198 struct AAPotentialValuesCallSite : AAPotentialValuesFunction {
11199  AAPotentialValuesCallSite(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
11200  : AAPotentialValuesFunction(IRP, A) {}
11201

11203  void trackStatistics() const override {
11204  STATS_DECLTRACK_CS_ATTR(potential_values)

11208 struct AAPotentialValuesCallSiteReturned : AAPotentialValuesImpl {
11209  AAPotentialValuesCallSiteReturned(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
11210  : AAPotentialValuesImpl(IRP, A) {}
11211 
11212  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
11213  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
11214  auto AssumedBefore = getAssumed();
11215 
11216  Function *Callee = getAssociatedFunction();
11217  if (!Callee)
11218  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
11219 
11220  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
11221  auto *CB = cast<CallBase>(getCtxI());
11222  if (CB->isMustTailCall() &&
11223  !A.isAssumedDead(IRPosition::inst(*CB), this, nullptr,
11224  UsedAssumedInformation))
11225  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
11226 
11227  SmallVector<AA::ValueAndContext> Values;
11228  if (!A.getAssumedSimplifiedValues(IRPosition::returned(*Callee), this,
11229  Values, AA::Intraprocedural,
11230  UsedAssumedInformation))
11231  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
11232 
11233  Function *Caller = CB->getCaller();
11234 
11235  bool AnyNonLocal = false;
11236  for (auto &It : Values) {
11237  Value *V = It.getValue();
11238  std::optional<Value *> CallerV = A.translateArgumentToCallSiteContent(
11239  V, *CB, *this, UsedAssumedInformation);
11240  if (!CallerV.has_value()) {
11241  // Nothing to do as long as no value was determined.
11242  continue;
11243  }
11244  V = *CallerV ? *CallerV : V;
11245  if (AA::isDynamicallyUnique(A, *this, *V) &&
11246  AA::isValidInScope(*V, Caller)) {
11247  if (*CallerV) {
11248  SmallVector<AA::ValueAndContext> ArgValues;
11249  IRPosition IRP = IRPosition::value(*V);
11250  if (auto *Arg = dyn_cast<Argument>(V))
11251  if (Arg->getParent() == CB->getCalledFunction())
11252  IRP = IRPosition::callsite_argument(*CB, Arg->getArgNo());
11253  if (recurseForValue(A, IRP, AA::AnyScope))
11254  continue;
11255  }
11256  addValue(A, getState(), *V, CB, AA::AnyScope, getAnchorScope());
11257  } else {
11258  AnyNonLocal = true;
11259  break;
11260  }
11261  }
11262  if (AnyNonLocal) {
11263  Values.clear();
11264  if (!A.getAssumedSimplifiedValues(IRPosition::returned(*Callee), this,
11265  Values, AA::Interprocedural,
11266  UsedAssumedInformation))
11267  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
11268  AnyNonLocal = false;
11269  getState() = PotentialLLVMValuesState::getBestState();
11270  for (auto &It : Values) {
11271  Value *V = It.getValue();
11272  if (!AA::isDynamicallyUnique(A, *this, *V))
11273  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
11274  if (AA::isValidInScope(*V, Caller)) {
11275  addValue(A, getState(), *V, CB, AA::AnyScope, getAnchorScope());
11276  } else {
11277  AnyNonLocal = true;
11278  addValue(A, getState(), *V, CB, AA::Interprocedural,
11279  getAnchorScope());
11280  }
11281  }
11282  if (AnyNonLocal)
11283  giveUpOnIntraprocedural(A);
11284  }
11285  return (AssumedBefore == getAssumed()) ? ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED
11286  : ChangeStatus::CHANGED;
11287  }
11288 
11289  ChangeStatus indicatePessimisticFixpoint() override {
11290  return AAPotentialValues::indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
11291  }
11292 
11293  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
11294  void trackStatistics() const override {
11295  STATS_DECLTRACK_CSRET_ATTR(potential_values)
11296  }
11297 };

11310 /// ---------------------- Assumption Propagation ------------------------------
11311 namespace {
11312 struct AAAssumptionInfoImpl : public AAAssumptionInfo {
11313  AAAssumptionInfoImpl(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A,
11314  const DenseSet<StringRef> &Known)
11315  : AAAssumptionInfo(IRP, A, Known) {}
11316 
11317  bool hasAssumption(const StringRef Assumption) const override {
11318  return isValidState() && setContains(Assumption);
11319  }
11320 
11321  /// See AbstractAttribute::getAsStr()
11322  const std::string getAsStr() const override {
11323  const SetContents &Known = getKnown();
11324  const SetContents &Assumed = getAssumed();
11325 
11326  const std::string KnownStr =
11327  llvm::join(Known.getSet().begin(), Known.getSet().end(), ",");
11328  const std::string AssumedStr =
11329  (Assumed.isUniversal())
11330  ? "Universal"
11331  : llvm::join(Assumed.getSet().begin(), Assumed.getSet().end(), ",");
11332 
11333  return "Known [" + KnownStr + "]," + " Assumed [" + AssumedStr + "]";
11334  }
11335 };
11336 
11337 /// Propagates assumption information from parent functions to all of their
11338 /// successors. An assumption can be propagated if the containing function
11339 /// dominates the called function.
11340 ///
11341 /// We start with a "known" set of assumptions already valid for the associated
11342 /// function and an "assumed" set that initially contains all possible
11343 /// assumptions. The assumed set is inter-procedurally updated by narrowing its
11344 /// contents as concrete values are known. The concrete values are seeded by the
11345 /// first nodes that are either entries into the call graph, or contains no
11346 /// assumptions. Each node is updated as the intersection of the assumed state
11347 /// with all of its predecessors.
11348 struct AAAssumptionInfoFunction final : AAAssumptionInfoImpl {
11349  AAAssumptionInfoFunction(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
11350  : AAAssumptionInfoImpl(IRP, A,
11351  getAssumptions(*IRP.getAssociatedFunction())) {}
11352 
11353  /// See AbstractAttribute::manifest(...).
11354  ChangeStatus manifest(Attributor &A) override {
11355  const auto &Assumptions = getKnown();
11356 
11357  // Don't manifest a universal set if it somehow made it here.
11358  if (Assumptions.isUniversal())
11359  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
11360 
11361  Function *AssociatedFunction = getAssociatedFunction();
11362 
11363  bool Changed = addAssumptions(*AssociatedFunction, Assumptions.getSet());
11364 
11365  return Changed ? ChangeStatus::CHANGED : ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
11366  }
11367 
11368  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
11369  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
11370  bool Changed = false;
11371 
11372  auto CallSitePred = [&](AbstractCallSite ACS) {
11373  const auto &AssumptionAA = A.getAAFor<AAAssumptionInfo>(
11374  *this, IRPosition::callsite_function(*ACS.getInstruction()),
11375  DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
11376  // Get the set of assumptions shared by all of this function's callers.
11377  Changed |= getIntersection(AssumptionAA.getAssumed());
11378  return !getAssumed().empty() || !getKnown().empty();
11379  };
11380 
11381  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
11382  // Get the intersection of all assumptions held by this node's predecessors.
11383  // If we don't know all the call sites then this is either an entry into the
11384  // call graph or an empty node. This node is known to only contain its own
11385  // assumptions and can be propagated to its successors.
11386  if (!A.checkForAllCallSites(CallSitePred, *this, true,
11387  UsedAssumedInformation))
11388  return indicatePessimisticFixpoint();
11389 
11390  return Changed ? ChangeStatus::CHANGED : ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
11391  }
11392 
11393  void trackStatistics() const override {}
11394 };
11395 
11396 /// Assumption Info defined for call sites.
11397 struct AAAssumptionInfoCallSite final : AAAssumptionInfoImpl {
11398 
11399  AAAssumptionInfoCallSite(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A)
11400  : AAAssumptionInfoImpl(IRP, A, getInitialAssumptions(IRP)) {}
11401 
11402  /// See AbstractAttribute::initialize(...).
11403  void initialize(Attributor &A) override {
11404  const IRPosition &FnPos = IRPosition::function(*getAnchorScope());
11405  A.getAAFor<AAAssumptionInfo>(*this, FnPos, DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
11406  }
11407 
11408  /// See AbstractAttribute::manifest(...).
11409  ChangeStatus manifest(Attributor &A) override {
11410  // Don't manifest a universal set if it somehow made it here.
11411  if (getKnown().isUniversal())
11412  return ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
11413 
11414  CallBase &AssociatedCall = cast<CallBase>(getAssociatedValue());
11415  bool Changed = addAssumptions(AssociatedCall, getAssumed().getSet());
11416 
11417  return Changed ? ChangeStatus::CHANGED : ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
11418  }
11419 
11420  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
11421  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
11422  const IRPosition &FnPos = IRPosition::function(*getAnchorScope());
11423  auto &AssumptionAA =
11424  A.getAAFor<AAAssumptionInfo>(*this, FnPos, DepClassTy::REQUIRED);
11425  bool Changed = getIntersection(AssumptionAA.getAssumed());
11426  return Changed ? ChangeStatus::CHANGED : ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
11427  }
11428 
11429  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
11430  void trackStatistics() const override {}
11431 
11432 private:
11433  /// Helper to initialized the known set as all the assumptions this call and
11434  /// the callee contain.
11435  DenseSet<StringRef> getInitialAssumptions(const IRPosition &IRP) {
11436  const CallBase &CB = cast<CallBase>(IRP.getAssociatedValue());
11437  auto Assumptions = getAssumptions(CB);
11438  if (const Function *F = CB.getCaller())
11439  set_union(Assumptions, getAssumptions(*F));
11440  if (Function *F = IRP.getAssociatedFunction())
11441  set_union(Assumptions, getAssumptions(*F));
11442  return Assumptions;
11443  }
11444 };
11445 } // namespace

11447 AACallGraphNode *AACallEdgeIterator::operator*() const {
11448  return static_cast<AACallGraphNode *>(const_cast<AACallEdges *>(
11449  &A.getOrCreateAAFor<AACallEdges>(IRPosition::function(**I))));
11450 }

11454 /// ------------------------ UnderlyingObjects ---------------------------------
11455 
11456 namespace {
11457 struct AAUnderlyingObjectsImpl
11458  : StateWrapper<BooleanState, AAUnderlyingObjects> {
11459  using BaseTy = StateWrapper<BooleanState, AAUnderlyingObjects>;
11460  AAUnderlyingObjectsImpl(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A) : BaseTy(IRP) {}
11461 
11462  /// See AbstractAttribute::getAsStr().
11463  const std::string getAsStr() const override {
11464  return std::string("UnderlyingObjects ") +
11465  (isValidState()
11466  ? (std::string("inter #") +
11467  std::to_string(InterAssumedUnderlyingObjects.size()) +
11468  " objs" + std::string(", intra #") +
11469  std::to_string(IntraAssumedUnderlyingObjects.size()) +
11470  " objs")
11471  : "<invalid>");
11472  }
11473 
11474  /// See AbstractAttribute::trackStatistics()
11475  void trackStatistics() const override {}
11476 
11477  /// See AbstractAttribute::updateImpl(...).
11478  ChangeStatus updateImpl(Attributor &A) override {
11479  auto &Ptr = getAssociatedValue();
11480 
11481  auto DoUpdate = [&](SmallSetVector<Value *, 8> &UnderlyingObjects,
11482  AA::ValueScope Scope) {
11483  bool UsedAssumedInformation = false;
11484  SmallPtrSet<Value *, 8> SeenObjects;
11485  SmallVector<AA::ValueAndContext> Values;
11486 
11487  if (!A.getAssumedSimplifiedValues(IRPosition::value(Ptr), *this, Values,
11488  Scope, UsedAssumedInformation))
11489  return UnderlyingObjects.insert(&Ptr);
11490 
11491  bool Changed = false;
11492 
11493  for (unsigned I = 0; I < Values.size(); ++I) {
11494  auto &VAC = Values[I];
11495  auto *Obj = VAC.getValue();
11496  Value *UO = getUnderlyingObject(Obj);
11497  if (UO && UO != VAC.getValue() && SeenObjects.insert(UO).second) {
11498  const auto &OtherAA = A.getAAFor<AAUnderlyingObjects>(
11499  *this, IRPosition::value(*UO), DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
11500  auto Pred = [&Values](Value &V) {
11501  Values.emplace_back(V, nullptr);
11502  return true;
11503  };
11504 
11505  if (!OtherAA.forallUnderlyingObjects(Pred, Scope))
11506  llvm_unreachable(
11507  "The forall call should not return false at this position");
11508 
11509  continue;
11510  }
11511 
11512  if (isa<SelectInst>(Obj) || isa<PHINode>(Obj)) {
11513  Changed |= handleIndirect(A, *Obj, UnderlyingObjects, Scope);
11514  continue;
11515  }
11516 
11517  Changed |= UnderlyingObjects.insert(Obj);
11518  }
11519 
11520  return Changed;
11521  };
11522 
11523  bool Changed = false;
11524  Changed |= DoUpdate(IntraAssumedUnderlyingObjects, AA::Intraprocedural);
11525  Changed |= DoUpdate(InterAssumedUnderlyingObjects, AA::Interprocedural);
11526 
11527  return Changed ? ChangeStatus::CHANGED : ChangeStatus::UNCHANGED;
11528  }
11529 
11530  bool forallUnderlyingObjects(
11531  function_ref<bool(Value &)> Pred,
11532  AA::ValueScope Scope = AA::Interprocedural) const override {
11533  if (!isValidState())
11534  return Pred(getAssociatedValue());
11535 
11536  auto &AssumedUnderlyingObjects = Scope == AA::Intraprocedural
11537  ? IntraAssumedUnderlyingObjects
11538  : InterAssumedUnderlyingObjects;
11539  for (Value *Obj : AssumedUnderlyingObjects)
11540  if (!Pred(*Obj))
11541  return false;
11542 
11543  return true;
11544  }
11545 
11546 private:
11547  /// Handle the case where the value is not the actual underlying value, such
11548  /// as a phi node or a select instruction.
11549  bool handleIndirect(Attributor &A, Value &V,
11550  SmallSetVector<Value *, 8> &UnderlyingObjects,
11551  AA::ValueScope Scope) {
11552  bool Changed = false;
11553  const auto &AA = A.getAAFor<AAUnderlyingObjects>(
11554  *this, IRPosition::value(V), DepClassTy::OPTIONAL);
11555  auto Pred = [&](Value &V) {
11556  Changed |= UnderlyingObjects.insert(&V);
11557  return true;
11558  };
11559  if (!AA.forallUnderlyingObjects(Pred, Scope))
11560  llvm_unreachable(
11561  "The forall call should not return false at this position");
11562  return Changed;
11563  }
11564 
11565  /// All the underlying objects collected so far via intra procedural scope.
11566  SmallSetVector<Value *, 8> IntraAssumedUnderlyingObjects;
11567  /// All the underlying objects collected so far via inter procedural scope.
11568  SmallSetVector<Value *, 8> InterAssumedUnderlyingObjects;
11569 };
11570

11573  : AAUnderlyingObjectsImpl(IRP, A) {}
11574 };

11641 #define SWITCH_PK_INV(CLASS, PK, POS_NAME) \
11642  case IRPosition::PK: \
11643  llvm_unreachable("Cannot create " #CLASS " for a " POS_NAME " position!");
11644 
11645 #define SWITCH_PK_CREATE(CLASS, IRP, PK, SUFFIX) \
11646  case IRPosition::PK: \
11647  AA = new (A.Allocator) CLASS##SUFFIX(IRP, A); \
11648  ++NumAAs; \
11649  break;
11650 
11651 #define CREATE_FUNCTION_ABSTRACT_ATTRIBUTE_FOR_POSITION(CLASS) \
11652  CLASS &CLASS::createForPosition(const IRPosition &IRP, Attributor &A) { \
11653  CLASS *AA = nullptr; \
11654  switch (IRP.getPositionKind()) { \
11655  SWITCH_PK_INV(CLASS, IRP_INVALID, "invalid") \
11656  SWITCH_PK_INV(CLASS, IRP_FLOAT, "floating") \
11657  SWITCH_PK_INV(CLASS, IRP_ARGUMENT, "argument") \
11658  SWITCH_PK_INV(CLASS, IRP_RETURNED, "returned") \
11659  SWITCH_PK_INV(CLASS, IRP_CALL_SITE_RETURNED, "call site returned") \
11660  SWITCH_PK_INV(CLASS, IRP_CALL_SITE_ARGUMENT, "call site argument") \
11661  SWITCH_PK_CREATE(CLASS, IRP, IRP_FUNCTION, Function) \
11662  SWITCH_PK_CREATE(CLASS, IRP, IRP_CALL_SITE, CallSite) \
11663  } \
11664  return *AA; \
11665  }
